(6, 504, 'Alex', 'a.kathleen.collins@gmail.com', '', '166.137.100.26', '2013-04-01 20:28:45', '2013-04-01 20:28:45', 'Do you think Carina is too light for dark skin?', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(7, 504, 'sarahappleby', 'Sarah@sarahappleby.com', 'http://sarahappleby.com', '100.2.185.76', '2013-04-02 22:17:49', '2013-04-02 22:17:49', 'Alex! Lighter shades with matte texture are tricky, as some will come off a bit chalky on darker skin tones. By adding a little sheen/lip gloss or balm in the center of the lips after it has set you will darken the color slightly, but add a more natural texture. Hope that helps. X', 0, '1', '', '', 6, 1),
(8, 505, 'Breanne', 'natashareaney@gmail.com', '', '24.114.26.47', '2013-03-25 22:56:37', '2013-03-25 22:56:37', 'Loving juicing! I''ve dealt with acne for at least 12 years and I''ve done everything to try and repair my skin. I''ve seen the greatest results with green smoothies (and now juices!) along with a healthier diet overall (i.e. I''m eating lots of veggies, minimal sugar and little to no dairy and gluten. I''ve also been meat free for 8 years). Thanks for the glow tips SA!  And for pushing for support for farmers markets.\n\nCheers. Bre', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(9, 505, 'sarahappleby', 'Sarah@sarahappleby.com', 'http://sarahappleby.com', '100.2.185.76', '2013-03-26 12:32:47', '2013-03-26 12:32:47', 'YES! Love that. Only thing to caution when juicing, is the sugar intake.. Keep me posted on your fave recipes you discover too! X', 0, '1', '', '', 8, 1),
(10, 505, 'Rachel', 'rachel@gmail.com', '', '142.255.75.110', '2013-03-27 17:38:46', '2013-03-27 17:38:46', 'Thanks for the great post! I love getting to the farmers markets also. So important to support local farmers, eat seasonally and minimise the impact on the environment.', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
