(365, 1, '2015-01-27 05:14:07', '2015-01-27 05:14:07', 'Last week I had the opportunity to shoot an editorial story with Geoff Barrenger + model Anastasiya Burachevskaya. It was a chilly day up on the Hudson, stylist Melissa Infante played with muted palettes + cozy textures. I did both hair + makeup, keeping it effortless + natural with the hair + playing with contours on the skinâ€¦\r\n\r\nFor makeup, I used all natural tones. Anastasiya already has beautiful strong brows but I shaped + refined them with the Anastasia Beverly Hills <a href="http://anastasiabeverlyhills.com/dipbrow-pomade-waterproof-color-brow-sculp.html">Dipbrow Pomade in Light Brown</a>. I used Makeup For Everâ€™s <a href="http://www.makeupforever.com/int/en-int/make-up/face/powder/sculpting-kit?sku=6131">Contour Kit</a> in Gold on her skin + used MAC Cosmeticâ€™s <a href="http://www.maccosmetics.com/product/shaded/156/316/Products/Face/Cheek/Cream-Colour-Base/index.tmpl">Cream Colour Base in Mid Tone Sepia</a> on the lids + around the eye, followed with <a href="http://www.maccosmetics.com/product/shaded/2146/363/Bestsellers/Eye-Shadow/index.tmpl">Espresso eyeshadow </a>for intensity over the cream.\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n\r\n<a href="http://182.71.22.42/sarah/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/3a.jpg"><img data-id="479"  src="http://182.71.22.42/sarah/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/3a-804x1024.jpg" alt="3a" width="650" height="827" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-479" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://182.71.22.42/sarah/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/3b.jpg"><img data-id="480"  src="http://182.71.22.42/sarah/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/3b-1024x651.jpg" alt="3b" width="650" height="413" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-480" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://182.71.22.42/sarah/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/3c.jpg"><img data-id="481"  src="http://182.71.22.42/sarah/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/3c-804x1024.jpg" alt="3c" width="650" height="827" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-481" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://182.71.22