(454, 1, '2015-01-27 07:48:17', '2015-01-27 07:48:17', 'Last nite I had the opportunity to hear Skin + Dermatologist legend, <a href="http://www.murad.com/murad-insider">Dr. Howard Murad</a> speak over dinner at The London Hotel here in NYC. Going into the evening, I thought we were going to talk about skincare, new products + how to use them. I was pleasantly surprised to see that not only has he written a new book <a href="http://www.murad.com/blog/stress-less-and-live-young-introducing-dr-murads-next-bestseller/">[Conquering Cultural Stress: The Ultimate Guide to Anti-Aging and Happiness]</a>, but he was wholeheartedly sharing all about it. He is the most genuine, lovely, gentleman. Such an honour to spend an evening with him + his team from California. A few thoughts + snaps from the niteâ€¦\r\n\r\nThe makeup look for the evening, a little cat eye + some contoured skin.\r\n<a href="http://182.71.22.42/sarah/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/2015_EVENT_DR_MURAD_LONDON_HOTEL_POST_7.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-392" src="http://182.71.22.42/sarah/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/2015_EVENT_DR_MURAD_LONDON_HOTEL_POST_7-1024x658.jpg" alt="2015_EVENT_DR_MURAD_LONDON_HOTEL_POST_7" width="850" height="" data-id="392" /></a>\r\n<br />\r\nDr. Murad has 365 mantras in the book to continue inspiring you over the year. Here are some of my favorites:\r\n\r\nâ€¢Eighty percent of health leads in the brain\r\n\r\nâ€¢Turn the rest of your life into the best of your life\r\n\r\nâ€¢Increase simplicity in your life\r\n\r\nâ€¢Reality not rhetoric\r\n\r\nâ€¢Enjoy the privilege of doing purposeful work\r\n\r\nâ€¢Replenish your passion\r\n\r\nâ€¢Have intentions to improve\r\n\r\nâ€¢Happiness means finding beauty everyday\r\n<br />\r\n<a href="http://182.71.22.42/sarah/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/2015_EVENT_DR_MURAD_LONDON_HOTEL_POST_4.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-393" src="http://182.71.22.42/sarah/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/2015_EVENT_DR_MURAD_LONDON_HOTEL_POST_4-300x158.jpg" alt="2015_EVENT_DR_MURAD_LONDON_HOTEL_POST_4" width="800" height="" data-id="393" /></a>\r\n<br />\r\n<a href="http://182.71.22.42/sarah/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/2015_EVENT_DR_MURAD_LONDON_HOTEL_POST_5.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-394" src="http://182.71.22.42/sarah/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/2015_EVENT_DR_MURAD_LONDON_HOTEL_POST_5-300x145.jpg" alt="2015_EVENT_DR_MURAD_LONDON_HOTEL_POST_5" width="800" height="" data-id="394" /></a>\r\n<br />\r\nDr. Murad + myself, so happy about new beginnings to conquer Cultural Stress. What a journey this will be! Naturally I loved this mantra above, â€˜treat yourself like royaltyâ€™. Done!\r\n\r\nThe nite was encouraging + inspiring. Dr. Murad focuses on us becoming our truest selves [he gave the analogy that at 1.5yrs old we were carefree, artistic + we were not phased by cultural stress]. Now, in NYC in 2015, we all feel the everyday cultural pressures: perfection, success, followers, likes, being with the latest trends, fitting in, + so much more. We are bombarded everyday by these pressures. His book, which I am excited to dive into this afternoon, is a go to for dealing with it all. Afterall, Dr. Murad has done many studies which directly link our life, stress, eating habits to our skin. Our skin is a reflection of our inside. Starting to focus on our inside self for a minute + adjusting our lifestyle accordingly, being intentional about how we are treating our bodies is the first way to better skin. Perhaps the second is following Muradâ€™s suited skin care regime.. More on that another day.\r\n<br />\r\nOne of my gal pals, amazing MUA Ashley Rebecca joined with me- always a good time.\r\n<a href="http://182.71.22.42/sarah/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/2015_EVENT_DR_MURAD_LONDON_HOTEL_POST_ASHLEY_REBECCA_6.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-397" src="http://182.71.22.42/sarah/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/2015_EVENT_DR_MURAD_LONDON_HOTEL_POST_ASHLEY_REBECCA_6-300x201.jpg" alt="2015_EVENT_DR_MURAD_LONDON_HOTEL_POST_ASHLEY_REBECCA_6" width="800" height="" data-id="397" /></a>\r\n\r\nThis morning I am reveling in the goodies from last nite. All body focused products, I will be breaking down my thoughts in future posts. Canâ€™t wait to dig in!\r\n<a href="http://182.71.22.42/sarah/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/2015_EVENT_DR_MURAD_LONDON_HOTEL_1.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-395" src="http://182.71.22.42/sarah/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/2015_EVENT_DR_MURAD_LONDON_HOTEL_1-300x200.jpg" alt="2015_EVENT_DR_MURAD_LONDON_HOTEL_1" width="800" height="" data-id="395" /></a>\r\n<br />\r\n+ Opening my book to this: the sweetest note from Dr. Murad:\r\n\r\nSarah\r\n\r\nâ€˜Find beauty everywhereâ€™ Wishing you + yours Youth, Health, Happiness + Joy.\r\n<br />\r\n<a href="http://182.71.22.42/sarah/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/2015_EVENT_DR_MURAD_LONDON_HOTEL_POST_2.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-396" src="http://182.71.22.42/sarah/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/2015_EVENT_DR_MURAD_LONDON_HOTEL_POST_2-300x180.jpg" alt="2015_EVENT_DR_MURAD_LONDON_HOTEL_POST_2" width="800" height="" data-id="396" /></a>\r\n<br />\r\n\r\nThose are some wishes to live byâ€¦ XXX', 'Skin + Cultural Stress: Dr. Murad hosts event at The London Hotel in NYC', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '93-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-27 07:48:17', '2015-01-27 07:48:17', '', 93, 'http://182.71.22.42/sarah/?p=454', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
