(507, 1, '2013-04-02 07:30:28', '2013-04-02 07:30:28', 'I am a huge fan of glowy, gorgeous, flawless skin [aren''t we all!]. Recently, I worked with talented Photographer Wendy Cassidy on a job, + in this post is model Amanda with her glowy creamy cheeks [These photos are unretouched!]! Of course amazing skin helps... Step by Step to get the rosy glow...<!--more-->\r\n\r\nâ€¢ LOVE YOUR SKIN WELL. You will always looks best when you are hydrated [H20!] + properly cleansing [YES, every AM+PM] + moisturizing generously.\r\n\r\nâ€¢ Get your foundation/tinted moisturizer etc. all over your face with your fingers or brushes, concealer on necessary areas for more coverage. You must take out all of the redness in order to make cheeks really pop + look intentional!\r\n\r\nâ€¢ If you want contoured cheeks for a more dramatic effect, apply a matte bronzer just below your cheekbones with a brush [I love <a href="http://www.essence.eu/us/usa/products/sun-club.html" target="_blank">Essence Sun Club Matte Bronzing Powder in Blonde</a>]\r\n\r\nâ€¢ Then using your fingers with the cream blush, dab product in a circular motion around the apples of your cheeks, blending up + out, diffusing the color toward the top of your cheekbones. [I love <a href="http://www.maccosmetics.com/product/shaded/156/15668/Products/Face/Cheek/Cremeblend-Blush/index.tmpl" target="_blank">MAC Cosmetics Cremeblend Blush in So Sweet</a>]\r\n\r\nâ€¢ Don''t be afraid if the color is not completely even! The very best trick to get it all blended + flawless is to use a touch of your foundation on a brush + blend around edges of cheek color to diffuse cheek color.\r\n\r\nâ€¢ I also love the cream blushes with a hint of shimmer in them, so fun in the summer to add that extra sheen!\r\n\r\nGet cheeky! X\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Amanda61.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-395" alt="Amanda6" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Amanda61.jpg" width="650" height="835" /></a>', 'How to: Creamy Pretty Cheeks', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'how-to-creamy-cheeks', '', '', '2015-01-28 06:37:30', '2015-01-28 06:37:30', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=392', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(508, 1, '2013-04-03 11:46:47', '2013-04-03 11:46:47', 'It''s true, there may be a few things you are believing about the way you do your makeup that [gasp!] M A Y be wrong. Oop! You know, the time the gal at the makeup counter fed you lies to get you to buy 4 things instead of 1. Or when that friend of a friend complimented you on your skin + you stopped wearing foundation altogether.... Five myths to be noted:<!--more-->\r\n\r\nâ€¢ <strong>You can''t wear bold lip color</strong>. YES, you can. No matter the skin tone or lip size, there is a bold lip color for you. Try lip stains first [I love the <a href="http://www.revlon.com/Revlon-Home/Products/Lips/lipstain/Just-Bitten-Lip-Stain.aspx" target="_blank">Revlon Just Bitten Lipstains</a>], to ease you into the change of color, then you can move on up to a classic, bombshell classic red [<a href="http://www.neimanmarcus.com/p/Tom-Ford-Beauty-Jasmine-Rouge-Lip-Color-and-Eau-de-Parfum/prod154010042/" target="_blank">Tom Ford Jasmine Rouge Lip Color in Narcotic</a>], or a fun fuschia [<a href="http://www.sephora.com/be-legendary-lipstick-P304704?om_mmc=Googlepla,_requestid=42976,cm_mmc=us_search-_-GG-_-pla-_-,ci_src=17588969,ci_sku=1387182" target="_blank">Smashbox Legendary Lipstick in Fuchsia Flash Matte</a>]! All the boys that say they don''t ''like'' lipstick on a girl. I think it''s more like us gals need to be applying it properly... Make certain your skin is flawless, no redness around the mouth or nose! Etc!\r\n\r\nâ€¢ <strong>Your skin is so pretty, you don''t need foundation</strong>. YES, you do. I don''t understand why foundation gets such a bad rap. Maybe the gal in high school that wore it caked on her skin, minimum of 3 shades darker with that line along her jawline? Maybe. But I got over that real quickly. Who doesn''t want gorgeous, even glowy skin. Time to get yourself to the beauty counter. Foundation can also be as easy + light as tinted moisturizer [<a href="http://www.lauramercier.com/store/shop/Step%202:%20Apply%20Foundation_Tinted%20Moisturizer%20SPF%2020_prod210061" target="_blank">Laura Mercier Tinter Moisturizer</a>], foundation powder [<a href="http://www.narscosmetics.com/complexion/foundation/~/powder-foundation" target="_blank">Nars Powder Foundation</a>], etc. You need to give your face a clean canvas. I don''t think it looks right when I can see unevenness on the skin + then there''s eyeshadow + liner + mascara + lipgloss! Hectic. Start with the skin...\r\n\r\nâ€¢ <strong>You don''t have time for beautiful makeup</strong>. Yes, you do. Like anything, if you invest in learning/practicing, you will get better + faster. Depending on how early my call time is, I can take as little as 10 minutes for both my hair + makeup. Really. Being a woman is fancy + fun, live like it! Take pride in yourself + don''t be afraid to take a few extra minutes to try something new. More to come...\r\n\r\nâ€¢ <strong>You can''t wear black liner, your eyes are too small</strong>. Yep- you can! For any type of eye shape, black liner [<a href="http://www.sephora.com/long-wear-gel-eyeliner-P270539?om_mmc=Googlepla,_requestid=42976,cm_mmc=us_search-_-GG-_-pla-_-,ci_src=17588969,ci_sku=1287432" target="_blank">Bobbi Brown Long-Wear Gel Liner</a>] works. If your eyes are close together, only use the liner on the outer top + bottom corners pulling the eyes outwards. Keeping it light + bright in the inner corners will make your eyes pop!\r\n\r\nâ€¢ <strong>You take 48 different products in your mu bag every day, you need them all.</strong> No! You don''t! Back in the day, I had a brief stint at a Retail Cosmetics store. I was sat down numerous times because I would suggest ways to use the products differently maximizing their functionality. Most products are multiuse, but not according to their sales people [I get it, business!]. Use your lipstick for blush, creamy shadow as a highlight above your lip, mascara for liner, foundation for changing lip/eye colors, the list goes on. Get creative + see which products you can double up the use + leave the rest at home!', 'Oh! A few myths about makeup... ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'oh-a-few-myths-about-m-a-k-e-u-p', '', '', '2015-01-28 06:38:31', '2015-01-28 06:38:31', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=411', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(509, 1, '2013-04-06 14:20:17', '2013-04-06 14:20:17', '&nbsp;\r\n\r\nYesterday, had the pleasure of working with a very talented crew + my new favorite photographer. We ran around NYC shooting all sorts of amazingness. Second shoot day is tomorrow! Helicopters + BK oh my! I will keep the details to myself until images are released, but here are a few snaps from the day...<!--more--><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/photo-1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-429" alt="photo 1" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/photo-1.jpg" width="2139" height="3209" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/photo-4.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-432" alt="photo 4" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/photo-4.jpg" width="2176" height="3264" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/photo-3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-431" alt="photo 3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/photo-3.jpg" width="2080" height="3119" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/photo-5.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-433" alt="photo 5" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/photo-5.jpg" width="2176" height="3264" /></a>', 'Behind the Scenes: Working NYC', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'behind-the-scenes-working-nyc', '', '', '2015-01-28 06:32:25', '2015-01-28 06:32:25', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=428', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(510, 1, '2013-04-10 15:01:08', '2013-04-10 15:01:08', 'Every girl wants to believe they do not need any makeup. That is nice. However, loving your skin well, you understand your flaws + take a minute [or three] to perfect them. So the next time you are rushing out, take three minutes, here is your routine...<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/photo-21.jpg"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-445" alt="photo 2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/photo-21.jpg" width="391" height="960" /></a>After moisturizing your face [SPF too!], apply <a href="http://www.bergdorfgoodman.com/p/Kevyn-Aucoin-Sensual-Skin-Tinted-Balm/prod84720052/?ecid=BGCIGoogleProductAds&amp;ci_src=17588969&amp;ci_sku=prod84720052skuSB02" target="_blank">Kevyn Aucoin''s Sensual Skin Tinted Balm</a>. I am loving this new product, it''s smooth + velvety, with light coverage leaving your skin with a dewy glow [please note the gorgeous packaging]. *Leave all tint off of your eyelids, it will give you a beautiful natural contour. Then open your eyes up with the <a href="http://www.ulta.com/ulta/browse/productDetail.jsp?skuId=2116560&amp;productId=prod2116560&amp;navAction=push&amp;navCount=1&amp;subdoc=98augbonuspoints&amp;categoryId=cat970001%20cat80086" target="_blank">Japonesque Power Lash Curler</a> + lightly fill in your brows with <a href="http://www.essence.eu/us/usa/products/eyes/eye-pencil.html" target="_blank">Essence Brow Pencil</a>. A little <a href="http://www.bigelowchemists.com/c-o-bigelow-mentha-lip-shine-spearmint-no-1191.html" target="_blank">C.O. Bigelow Mentha Lip Shine</a> + you are out the door! Flawless + Spring ready.</p>', 'Three Minute Makeup/ Au Natural', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'three-minute-makeup-au-natural', '', '', '2015-01-28 06:35:50', '2015-01-28 06:35:50', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=442', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(511, 1, '2013-04-11 16:58:07', '2013-04-11 16:58:07', 'Springtime makes me want to surround myself with flowers + shrubs + greenery. I spent the morning visiting my local garden shop, Natty''s Garden in Brooklyn, it is just around the corner from me. There is something so life giving about plants + flowers. I want my home to feel alive; I took a few little planters + an old candle holder + a can painted black to do just that...<!--more-->\r\n\r\nI have always said if I could go back to my teenage years, I would have loved to work at a floral shop. Never too late, I know. Perhaps amidst painting faces, some greenery/floral arrangement classes will suffice. Don''t ask me the names/types of the beauties I found + planted. I went by the shape + color + texture + then factored in what Cory said was least needy [note *before photo above, with my dead moss in the silver planter- oops]...! We shall see how I go. They are all so pretty, the colors + textures are inspiring.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/photo-31.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-459" alt="photo 3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/photo-31.jpg" width="720" height="960" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/photo-22.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-458" alt="photo 2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/photo-22.jpg" width="621" height="828" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/photo-51.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-456" alt="photo 5" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/photo-51.jpg" width="676" height="902" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/photo-41.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-460" alt="photo 4" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/photo-41.jpg" width="639" height="851" /></a>\r\n\r\nPart of feeling vibrant is surrounding yourself with beauty. I love a space that reflects life + light. This Spring, get yourself to your nearest garden store [support your local businesses!] + give your space some life! Happy Potting! X', 'HOME/ Living Beauties', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'home-living-beauties', '', '', '2015-01-28 06:36:25', '2015-01-28 06:36:25', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=454', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(521, 1, '2013-04-22 10:00:20', '2013-04-22 10:00:20', '&nbsp;\r\n\r\nI had the pleasure of working with Photographer Luzena Adams on an editorial for Beautiful Savage magazine. I played up the creamy poppy lips + turquoise eyes. Makes me anxious for long summer days + nites! Here are my favorites from the story...<!--more--><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/summermakeup5.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-526" alt="summermakeup5" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/summermakeup5.jpg" width="650" height="827" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/summermakeup4.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-525" alt="summermakeup4" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/summermakeup4.jpg" width="650" height="827" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/summermakeup2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-523" alt="summermakeup2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/summermakeup2.jpg" width="650" height="827" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/summermakeup3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-524" alt="summermakeup3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/summermakeup3.jpg" width="650" height="827" /></a><em>MAKEUP/</em> Sarah Appleby Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  <em>STYLING/</em> Morgan GibbonsÂ Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â <em>HAIR/</em> Jennifer Brent Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â <em>PROPS/</em> Alex Brannian', 'New Work/ Summer Love, editorial', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'new-work-summer-love-editorial', '', '', '2015-01-28 06:31:50', '2015-01-28 06:31:50', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=521', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(533, 1, '2013-04-24 17:54:13', '2013-04-24 17:54:13', 'I love traveling for work. I''m currently on the west coast doing some work with German makeup company, Essence Cosmetics. I am definitely one to take full advantage of every hour I am not working to discover restaurants, cafes, bars whilst snapping landscapes + architecture. It is all so inspiring. It also helps that this time around, the city is warm + sunny + blooming with Spring...<!--more--> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/image2.jpg"><img src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/image2.jpg" alt="image" width="1024" height="769" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-538" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/image1.jpg"><img src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/image1.jpg" alt="image" width="1024" height="768" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-537" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/image6.jpg"><img src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/image6.jpg" alt="image" width="1024" height="768" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-542" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/image7.jpg"><img src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/image7.jpg" alt="image" width="1024" height="768" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-543" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/image4.jpg"><img src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/image4.jpg" alt="image" width="1024" height="768" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-540" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/image5.jpg"><img src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/image5.jpg" alt="image" width="1024" height="768" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-541" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/image9.jpg"><img src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/image9.jpg" alt="image" width="1024" height="768" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-545" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/image8.jpg"><img src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/image8.jpg" alt="image" width="1024" height="768" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-544" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/image10.jpg"><img src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/image10.jpg" alt="image" width="1024" height="769" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-546" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/image.jpg"><img src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/image.jpg" alt="image" width="1024" height="769" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-536" /></a> My three days have been filled strolling the Pearl District + the Eastside, consuming copious amounts of delicious coffee + juice, floral cocktails, food, + vino! Portland is a town full of wonderful people + thriving businesses that are doing food + drink right. Prasad, Maglia Rosa, Barista, Voodoo, Andina, LePigeon, Clyde Common all contributed. Now, back to work, en route to Seattle!', 'Work Trip/ portland photo diary', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'work-trip-portland-photo-diary', '', '', '2015-01-28 06:22:46', '2015-01-28 06:22:46', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=533', 0, 'post', '', 1),
