(591, 1, '2013-05-02 12:00:12', '2013-05-02 12:00:12', 'For all of us beauty junkies, a good product isn''t difficult to come by. However an experience in helping create the product is the very best! I have talked about french skin care line, Caudalie, before + here is yet another reason to say ''oui!'' to their incredible products...<!--more--><img title="More..." alt="" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-includes/js/tinymce/plugins/wordpress/img/trans.gif" />\r\n\r\nI recently found myself in the flagship store on Bleecker street + while perusing the new goodies I was encouraged to try the Crushed Cabernet Scrub. So I rolled up my sleeves + got right into scrubbing my hands. They were left feeling soft + supple + smelled beyond delicious. In that moment I thought of my client''s + how delicious it would be if my hands smelled like that while working on their face! The store''s concoction was made of Rosemary + Lemon... It was divine! + Yes! All Vino inspired, using grapes + grapeseeds. They hand make each scrub for their clients; made with honey, grapeseed, sugar + scented oils [all natural of course!]. You get to choose your special mix of oils to add. As I am one that is obsessed with all things floral, I went with Geranium + Lemongrass. It is now a staple! I keep mine by the sink so I can wash my hands with it, but it is also a perfect scrub for the body. Merci Beaucoup! Make your way to Bleecker St {If you can''t get over there soon enough, you can order their<a href="http://www.sephora.com/crushed-cabernet-scrub-P100101" target="_blank"> Premade Cabernet Scrub</a>} + enjoy!<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/caudaliescrub2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-601" alt="caudaliescrub2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/caudaliescrub2.jpg" width="1561" height="2081" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/caudaliescrub1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-600" alt="caudaliescrub1" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/caudaliescrub1.jpg" width="2448" height="3264" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/caudaliescrub.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-599" alt="caudaliescrub" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/caudaliescrub.jpg" width="2175" height="2899" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Must Have/ Crushed Cabernet Scrub by Caudalie', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'must-have-crushed-cabernet-scrub-by-caudalie', '', '', '2015-01-28 06:21:35', '2015-01-28 06:21:35', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=591', 0, 'post', '', 2),
(607, 1, '2013-05-06 10:00:10', '2013-05-06 10:00:10', 'I recently spent some time at the Ian Potter Centre in Melbourne, Australia. It was a treat of a day as I showed up solo to attend a group ''tour'' of the gallery, to find out I was the only one! I spent nearly an hour with a woman who showed me around the museum + shared with me a vast amount of knowledge about the museum, history + pieces. It was up there in one of my favorite museum experiences...<!--more--><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/NGVlivingwater2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-609" alt="NGVlivingwater2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/NGVlivingwater2.jpg" width="2314" height="1736" /></a>I especially loved the exhibit, <a href="http://www.ngv.vic.gov.au/whats-on/exhibitions/exhibitions/living-water" target="_blank">Living Water</a>, it''s the most beautiful series of pieces, each having rich meaning. An excerpt from the Exhibition about ''Living Water'': {<em>Aboriginal people from across the Western Desert use the term â€˜living waterâ€™ to describe water sources, including rock holes and soakage waters that are fed by underground springs. The path of these springs was created by the ancestral beings of the tjukurrpa (Dreaming) as they themselves journeyed underground, their entry into the earth often marking the site of current day water sources. â€˜Living waterâ€™ is revered also because it does not seem to be affected by the harsh conditions above the ground that the people themselves have to endure</em>.}. Life giving, inspiring!<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/NGVlivingwater3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-610" alt="NGVlivingwater3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/NGVlivingwater3.jpg" width="1536" height="1152" /></a>The artist''s lives + communities were built around the water wells, represented by the black circles. The colors + patterns in the paintings were very inspiring + learning the meanings behind shapes, colors + the textures the artists chose were all representative of their way of life. Not to mention how visually appealing they all are.\r\n\r\nMuseums are something I thoroughly enjoy, but too rarely make time for. I always wonder why I can''t fit more gallery/exhibit openings into my life. There are so many incredible exhibits popping up every week in Manhattan, no reason not to pop in after work once a week! You know where to find me Thursday eve...', 'Traveling + Adventuring/ Melbourne: Ian Potter Centre', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'traveling-adventuring-melbourne-ian-potter-centre', '', '', '2015-01-28 06:20:57', '2015-01-28 06:20:57', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=607', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(620, 1, '2013-05-08 13:59:42', '2013-05-08 13:59:42', 'Fragrance is huge for me. I may be one of those people that have a finely tuned nose or perhaps I have been around so many fragrances + now I just can''t live without it. I love it when I walk into a space; a boutique, park, spa, home etc. + I am greeted with a cloud of aroma. With that said, I also love it when you walk up to someone + find their fragrance. {Yes, at times I am surely that girl with maybe one or two sprays too many of my perfume!}. Along with being a perfume junkie, I am obsessed with products that make my home + space fragrant. Some favorites...<!--more-->\r\n\r\nâ€¢<a href="http://www.sephora.com/candelina-collection-P377322?skuId=1498393" target="_blank">Tocca Candle in Florence</a>: this candle smells like European Garden rose known aka Centifolias, combined with iris root. When I have this burning in my apartment it makes me feel like I am in a garden! There is something so magical about floral scents to me, I am obsessed.\r\n\r\nâ€¢<a href="http://balenciagafragrance.com/en/balenciaga-paris" target="_blank">Balenciaga Paris Perfume</a>: my summer staple [yes, seasons change as should your fragrance!], this week at least! It''s fresh + floral + light + airy. Notes of Violet Leaf, Pepper, Cedarwood, Patchouli, Vetiver.\r\n\r\nâ€¢<a href="http://www.sedafrance.com/product/Japanese-Quince-Classic-Toile-Liquid-Hand-Soap/Hand-Soap" target="_blank">Seda France Hand Soap in Japanese Quince</a>: Since I have been in NYC, I have loved this scent {candles + diffusers too!}. I find myself walking into so many shops that are filled with the Japanese Quince. I could never tire of this one... Notes: Rhubarb, Passion Fruit, Peach, Jasmine Petals. {FYI: the notes do not do it justice!}\r\n\r\nâ€¢Fresh Fleurs: I am an advocate for fresh flowers in the home at all times. Be it from a lovely gent, or my own stop by the florist en route home- it''s a must! I am mostly an all white flower gal, but this week I opted for a pop of pink, tulips are so pretty this time of year. Fresh flowers do something for me, visually + aromatically.\r\n\r\nIt''s all a part of living well + surrounding yourself with spaces + products that give you life. Breathe beauty.', 'A Fragrant Desire', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'a-fragrant-desire', '', '', '2015-01-28 06:20:34', '2015-01-28 06:20:34', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=620', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(634, 1, '2013-05-14 12:09:42', '2013-05-14 12:09:42', 'I am all about a lip, all the time. I just recently discovered the <em><a href="http://www.stilacosmetics.com/product/after+glow+lip+color.do" target="_blank">After Glow Lip Color</a></em> Crayons by Stila! Wearing Electric Pink above. They are a dream + come in five, you-need-them-all shades... <!--more--><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/stilaafterglow1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-636" alt="stilaafterglow1" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/stilaafterglow1.jpg" width="3264" height="2176" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/stilaafterglow2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-637" alt="stilaafterglow2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/stilaafterglow2.jpg" width="2619" height="1746" /></a>\r\n\r\nThese lip crayons give have a beautiful consistency, moisturizing + just the right amount of pigment, leaving your lips with the prettiest stain. Chunky crayon for easy application {poor Vivid Violet had a fall...} as well as great for on the go. Just remember when playing with color on your lips to moisturize + conceal around your mouth + nose for the maximum pop of color. Get to coloring! X', 'Makeup Musthave/ Stila After Glow Lip Color', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'makeup-musthave-stila-after-glow-lip-color', '', '', '2015-01-28 06:17:59', '2015-01-28 06:17:59', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=634', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(644, 1, '2013-05-16 11:23:37', '2013-05-16 11:23:37', 'Yesterday I spent the afternoon with my dear friend Megan {we spent our summers at her family''s lake house in Alberta Canada!}, chatting + laughing + playing pretty. She + brilliant man, Corin Roddick, make up the duo <a href="http://thepurityring.tumblr.com/" target="_blank">Purity Ring</a>. It''s been so much fun watching her + her career move, not to mention I am a huge fan of their <a href="https://itunes.apple.com/us/artist/purity-ring/id461030854" target="_blank">music</a>. She is known for her crazy, big, toussled hair, so after I gently passed on a few ''take care of your hair'' tips, we played...<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/tigibandbdavines.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-651" alt="tigibandbdavines" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/tigibandbdavines.jpg" width="3058" height="2040" /></a>Megan loves her hair with crazy texture, she hadn''t washed her hair in 2 days, which is perfect for styling. I started by combing through her hair + spraying in <a href="http://www.catwalkbytigi.com/the-catwalk-collection/styling-collection/session-series-styling-collection/transforming-dry-shampoo" target="_blank">Catwalk Transforming Dry Shampoo</a> generously in her roots + throughout the body of her hair. This will soak up any natural oils + turn it to matte texture. Then I separated her hair with clips in 4 horizontal sections, leaving the bottom section out. I sprayed <a href="http://www.bumbleandbumble.com/product/73/193/Products/Styling/Sprays/does-it-all-styling-spray/index.tmpl" target="_blank">Bumble and bumble does it All Styling Spray</a> throughout to help set.Â <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/meganjameshair2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-649" alt="meganjameshair2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/meganjameshair2.jpg" width="3264" height="2176" /></a>\r\n\r\nI used a flatiron to straighten the bottom 4 inches of her hair. Using a 1 inch curling iron I wrapped 1.5 inch sections, not using the clamp, around the iron in all different directions. *Depending on the way you hold your iron, horizontally or vertically, will give you a different finish. As well, which side you wrap the hair from. This will give it our desired messy, textured look... Here is the hair set: Â  <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/maganjameshair.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-647" alt="maganjameshair" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/maganjameshair.jpg" width="3264" height="2176" /></a>I left her hair for about 30 minutes {to do makeup! That How to is next week!}, + then flipped her hair over + shook it all up. We love that she is not afraid to go big! Finishing off the ends I put in <a href="http://www.davines.com/en/products/view/finest-oil-non-oil-n1" target="_blank">Davines Finest Oil Non Oil</a>, for wizards! This is the best oil, it brings the hair together to give it a dirty, natural look. Megan is a total babe + she owns her big hair, so much fun to play with this...<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/meganjameshairSA.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-652" alt="meganjameshairSA" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/meganjameshairSA.jpg" width="2448" height="3264" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/meganjamessarahappleby2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-653" alt="meganjamessarahappleby" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/meganjamessarahappleby2.jpg" width="3003" height="2002" /></a>More to come.... X', 'Hair: How To/ megan james of Purity Ring', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'hair-how-to-megan-james-of-purity-ring', '', '', '2015-01-28 06:17:07', '2015-01-28 06:17:07', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=644', 0, 'post', '', 4),
(660, 1, '2013-05-21 13:59:46', '2013-05-21 13:59:46', 'The last two weeks I have barely slept a wink past 630a + although at times I think my body could use a little more sleep, I will rise + take full advantage of the quiet. Being a morning person- a real one {!} I have become really good at making the most of the early hours.Â  Summer is near + I just set up my little bistro set on my balcony; I have a feeling many early mornings will be spent here...<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/davidstea.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-662" alt="davidstea" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/davidstea.jpg" width="2874" height="1916" /></a>I made some loose leaf <a href="http://www.davidstea.com/bravissimo-en?&amp;currid=usd&amp;LN=EN" target="_blank">David''s Tea in Bravissimo</a>, it''s the yummiest herbal infusion of chamomile/rosehip/gojiberries/orangepeel/peppermint.\r\n\r\nReading through <a href="http://www.amazon.com/Carine-Roitfeld-Irreverent/dp/0847833682" target="_blank">Carine Roitfeld''s Irreverent</a>, I know I am a little late on this one- but better late than never! I have a long love affair with Paris + the parisian culture, this book is not only visually beautiful but full of Carine''s musings about the Fashion industry, work, France, + all things beautiful. J''adore!\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/whitenails.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-663" alt="whitenails" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/whitenails.jpg" width="2824" height="1883" /></a>I paint my nails white. I have been using <a href="http://www.bloom.com/sephora-by-opi-nail-colour-white-hot.html" target="_blank">Sephora by Oâ€¢Pâ€¢I in White Hot</a>. It''s a stark white that lasts. I love freshly painted nails + when I don''t have time to make it to get a mani, I make it work!<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/whitehotopisephora.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-664" alt="whitehotopisephora" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/whitehotopisephora.jpg" width="2885" height="1923" /></a>\r\n\r\nWhile listening to <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Haim_%28band%29" target="_blank">Haim</a> I am thankful for the prettiest view of Brooklyn, the trees are lush + full of life. It''s going to be a good day... Now off to take Little White Lightening {my vintage Peugeot} to Williamsburg to meet the gals! X', 'Early Mornings/ + some favorite things', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'early-mornings-some-favorite-things', '', '', '2015-01-28 06:16:02', '2015-01-28 06:16:02', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=660', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(672, 1, '2013-05-22 20:53:09', '2013-05-22 20:53:09', 'Here''s the new beauty editorial I did for <a href="http://beautyhigh.com/" target="_blank">Beauty High</a>! Loved the team so much. Very fun being on jobs where all I do is hang out in a candy shop + play with color on pretty girls...<!--more--><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/COTL_COVER.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-673" alt="COTL_COVER" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/COTL_COVER.png" width="1027" height="770" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/COTL_SLIDE-5.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-677" alt="COTL_SLIDE-5" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/COTL_SLIDE-5.png" width="1027" height="770" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/COTL_SLIDE-2.png"><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/COTL_SLIDE-6.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-678" alt="COTL_SLIDE-6" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/COTL_SLIDE-6.png" width="1027" height="770" /></a><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-675" alt="COTL_SLIDE-2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/COTL_SLIDE-2.png" width="1027" height="770" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/COTL_CREDITS.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-674" alt="COTL_CREDITS" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/COTL_CREDITS.png" width="1027" height="770" /></a>Check out the <a href="http://beautyhigh.com/colored-hair-get-inspired-color-outside-the-lines/" target="_blank">full story</a> on Beauty High''s website, with my personal notes about the choices I made for makeup on the girls!', 'New Work/ coloring for beauty high', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'new-work-coloring-for-beauty-high', '', '', '2015-01-28 06:15:45', '2015-01-28 06:15:45', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=672', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(687, 1, '2013-05-24 16:19:05', '2013-05-24 16:19:05', 'It was five years ago today I packed up all of my belongings into 4 big boxes, 2 suitcases + left Vancouver, BC. It was five years ago that I felt anxious, nervous, scared, excited, liberated, crazy + free arriving in the big city starting everything new...<!--more-->\r\n\r\nI have been so blessed to have met the incredible people I have in my life here. It''s been a gift building a beautiful community of people I love who encourage + support me in the best times + hardest times. Getting to work with the most talented people in the industry; painting the most beautiful faces, meeting dynamic + inspiring people that make me want to be more + indulging in the most delicious restaurants + bars; makes me so incredibly thankful for my time here.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/NYILY1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-688" alt="NYILY1" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/NYILY1.jpg" width="901" height="901" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/NYILY.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-689" alt="NYILY" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/NYILY.jpg" width="1280" height="1280" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/NYILY3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-690" alt="NYILY3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/NYILY3.jpg" width="819" height="819" /></a>Â  <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/NYILY7.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-693" alt="NYILY7" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/NYILY7.jpg" width="960" height="960" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/NYILY4.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-691" alt="NYILY4" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/NYILY4.jpg" width="960" height="960" /></a> + To think there''s more! More dinner parties, crazy photoshoots, sunrises, late nite walks, long summer nites, beach trips, restaurant hops, + ETC! I can''t wait to see what the next 5 bring... Dear New York: I love you!', '5 Years/ Happy Anniversary New York!', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '5-years-happy-anniversary-new-york', '', '', '2015-01-28 06:14:55', '2015-01-28 06:14:55', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=687', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(702, 1, '2013-05-28 14:38:46', '2013-05-28 14:38:46', 'Part Deux! When I spent the <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/hair-how-to-megan-james-of-purity-ring/" target="_blank">afternoon with Megan</a> two weeks back, along with hair we did some pretty Spring makeup. Megan''s au natural during the day + some eyeliner by nite. I wanted to play up her light brown eyes + milky skin, here''s what we did...<!--more-->\r\n\r\nTo prep her {pretty much flawless} skin I used Jurlique Radiance Serum with a generous amount of Jurlique Herbal Recovery Eye Cream around her eyes + tops of her cheeks. I put some Reve de Miel Lip Balm on her lips + applied NARS Sheer Foundation which gives the perfect amount of coverage + a beautiful glowy texture to the skin. With the foundation I concentrated the application to the center of her face where she has minimal redness + then buffing it out to the outer edges.<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-706" alt="MJSAjurliquenars" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/MJSAjurliquenars.jpg" width="3264" height="2176" /> Our beauty before...<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-709" alt="meganjamessarahappleby6" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/meganjamessarahappleby6.jpg" width="2319" height="1546" /> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/narsstilaclinique.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-710" alt="narsstilaclinique" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/narsstilaclinique.jpg" width="3264" height="2174" /></a> â€¢Eyes/ Lined the top of her lids with <a href="http://www.maccosmetics.com/product/shaded/151/476/Products/Eyes/Liner/Powerpoint-Eye-Pencil/index.tmpl" target="_blank">MAC''s Powerpoint Pencil</a> in Out to Sea + blended it out with a firm synthetic brush. Added <a href="http://www.narscosmetics.com/color/eyes/larger-than-life-long-wear-eyeliner/barrow-street" target="_blank">NARS Larger Than Life Long-Wear Eyeliner</a> in Seafoam Green to the inner corner top + bottom. Again, blendedÂ  together with the darker, stronger teal. I focused the seafoam color on the bottom of her lashes. Applied <a href="http://www.stilacosmetics.com/product/glamoureyes-mascara.do" target="_blank">Stila glamoureyes mascara</a> giving volume + definition.\r\n\r\nâ€¢Eyebrows/ Megan has such great big brows! I love the <a href="http://www.clinique.com/product/1595/4799/Makeup/Brows/Brow-Keeper/index.tmpl" target="_blank">Clinique Brow Keeper in Honey</a> + built in some shape for a more structured look. Then used the other end of the pencil to brush up the eyebrows to open her eyes a little more.\r\n\r\nâ€¢Lips/ The new <a href="http://www.stilacosmetics.com/product/color+balm+lipstick.do?sortby=ourPicks&amp;page=2" target="_blank">Stila Color Balm lipsticks</a> are the perfect amount of saturation. Gabrielle is a nudey pink which suited Meg''s looks perfectly.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/meganjamessarahappleby21.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-703" alt="meganjamessarahappleby2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/meganjamessarahappleby21.jpg" width="3264" height="2174" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/meganjamessarahappleby7.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-708" alt="meganjamessarahappleby7" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/meganjamessarahappleby7.jpg" width="3264" height="2174" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/meganjamessarahappleby8.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-705" alt="meganjamessarahappleby8" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/meganjamessarahappleby8.jpg" width="3264" height="2174" /></a>+ Voila! A poppy teal eye + subtle everything else makes for the perfect Summer day-to-eve look. Love this gal. X<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/meganjamessarahappleby5.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-713" alt="meganjamessarahappleby" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/meganjamessarahappleby5.jpg" width="3264" height="2176" /></a>', 'Makeup: How to/ megan james of purity ring', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'makeup-how-to-megan-james-of-purity-ring', '', '', '2015-01-28 06:14:23', '2015-01-28 06:14:23', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=702', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(719, 1, '2013-06-04 07:00:11', '2013-06-04 07:00:11', 'Summer is upon us + all the gals want the bronze smudgy eyes. I just discovered the new Clinique Chubby Stick for eyes + it is the perfect partner for this makeup. So easy to use + blendable. Here is how you get the look...<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/cliniqueeyesproduct.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-759" alt="cliniqueeyesproduct" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/cliniqueeyesproduct.jpg" width="4319" height="3274" /></a> You will need:\r\n<div>â€¢<a href="http://www.clinique.com/product/1595/5634/Makeup/Brows/Brow-Shaper/index.tmpl" target="_blank">Clinique Brow Shaper </a>I use a mix of Wheat + Soft Brown</div>\r\n<div>â€¢<a href="http://www.clinique.com/cms/whats_new/chubbystick/wn_index.tmpl" target="_blank">Clinique Chubby Stick Shadow Tint for Eyes</a> in Bountiful Beige/Lots o'' Latte/Fuller Fudge</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\nâ€¢Once your skin is flawless {using foundation, tinted moisturizer, powder, whichever you prefer} I use an angle brush to <em>fill in my brows</em>. Mixing the two colors to give the brow some depth, + flicking the brush up with the product into your brows will have them looking natural. Don''t overdo it. + Don''t stress out, <em>your brows are not symmetrical</em>!<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-723" alt="cliniquebrows" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/cliniquebrows.jpg" width="4416" height="3312" />â€¢<em>Apply Lots o'' Latte all over the base of your eye</em> + blend out the top edges with your finger.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/sarahapplebymakeup3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-725" alt="sarahapplebymakeup3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/sarahapplebymakeup3.jpg" width="4416" height="3312" /></a>â€¢Using <em>Bountiful Beige color along your brow bone</em> +<em> inner corner of the eye to highlight</em>. Blend the colors together. {We love that these are so blendable + do not get muddy!}<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-722" alt="sarahapplebymakeup4" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/sarahapplebymakeup4.jpg" width="4416" height="3312" />â€¢<em>Use Fuller Fudge + color a generous line around your entire eye, along with inside your waterline</em>. Blend into the other colors. Putting the dark on last + closest to the lashline gives the eyes a diffused look.<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-721" alt="cliniquesarahappleby" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/cliniquesarahappleby.jpg" width="4416" height="3312" />â€¢<em>Curl your lashes + add some chunky mascara</em> + you are ready for your day or evening out! <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/sarahapplebymua.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-757" alt="sarahapplebymua" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/sarahapplebymua.jpg" width="2944" height="4416" /></a>Embrace the Summer of Bronze Beauty! X', 'MAKEUP/ how to: bronze/smudgy eyes', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'makeup-how-to-bronzesmudgy-eyes', '', '', '2015-01-28 06:07:43', '2015-01-28 06:07:43', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=719', 0, 'post', '', 2),
(734, 1, '2013-05-30 09:00:30', '2013-05-30 09:00:30', 'I have really fine hair, but lots of it. I have learned throughout years of styling hair, that although I''d like a little wave or a little more hair- I can do more with this texture than most {it''s flexible!}. Whatever your hair type, learn to work with it. You''ll find it will respond to different products + styling tools differently; so if you aren''t getting the results you want, switch it up! Here''s my step by step from just out of the shower + squeaky clean, fine hair...<!--more--><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-729" alt="phytovolume" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/phytovolume.jpg" width="4249" height="2832" />When your hair is towel dried {no need to make your hair or the product work harder than it has to} I spray a generous amount of <a href="http://www.sephora.com/phytovolume-actif-volumizing-spray-P2910?skuId=1512334" target="_blank">Phytovolume Actif Volumizing Spray</a> into my roots + work into the hair.<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-730" alt="salontechdryer" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/salontechdryer.jpg" width="4416" height="2944" />Then I use my <a href="http://www.folica.com/tools/hair-dryers/salon-tech-2800-featherlight-hair-dryer" target="_blank">Salontech Featherweight Blow dryer</a> {beware: it gets really hot! But good for less time on your hair} along with my <a href="http://www.sephora.com/large-round-brush-P241317?om_mmc=Googlepla,_requestid=42976,cm_mmc=us_search-_-GG-_-pla-_-,ci_src=17588969,ci_sku=1170489" target="_blank">Large Round Brush from Sephora</a> + take sections of 1.5in to blow dry at a time, really focusing on the roots + getting a lift.<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-731" alt="sephoraroundbrush" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/sephoraroundbrush.jpg" width="4416" height="2944" />I spray about four pumps of my favorite <a href="http://www.davines.com/en/products/view/sea-salt" target="_blank">Davines Sea Salt Primer</a> {for wizards thank you!} into the body of my hair + rub in with my fingers creating friction + texture.<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-728" alt="hairproducts" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/hairproducts.jpg" width="2110" height="2110" />Tada! Products above, {they are all used!} it''s all you need for some messy textured hair... X<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-733" alt="texturedhair2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/texturedhair2.jpg" width="3705" height="2470" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'HAIR/ how to: texture+mess with oh so fine hair ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'hair-how-to-texturemess-with-oh-so-fine-hair', '', '', '2015-01-28 06:14:30', '2015-01-28 06:14:30', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=734', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(744, 1, '2013-05-31 08:24:22', '2013-05-31 08:24:22', '\r\n\r\nLast nite I had the privilege to attend Ellen von Unwerth''s exhibition opening of Playdate at the Staley Wise Gallery SoHo. It officially opens tonite + showing through July 12. Images, as always, were beyond beautiful, quirky + playful. A few {black+white} snaps from the eve...<!--more--><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/ellenvonunwerth6.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-745" alt="ellenvonunwerth6" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/ellenvonunwerth6.jpg" width="2448" height="1632" /></a>Â  <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/ellenvonunwerth4.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-747" alt="ellenvonunwerth4" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/ellenvonunwerth4.jpg" width="2449" height="1633" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/ellenvonunwerth3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-748" alt="ellenvonunwerth3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/ellenvonunwerth3.jpg" width="3264" height="2174" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/ellenvonunwerth2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-749" alt="ellenvonunwerth2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/ellenvonunwerth2.jpg" width="2448" height="1632" /></a> <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-750" alt="ellenvonunwerth1" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/ellenvonunwerth1.jpg" width="2335" height="1557" />Had a minute to chat with Ellen + she is indeed just as lovely as she is talented. <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/ellenvonunwerth.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-751" alt="ellenvonunwerth" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/ellenvonunwerth.jpg" width="2640" height="1760" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/ellenvonunwerth7.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-752" alt="ellenvonunwerth7" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/ellenvonunwerth7.jpg" width="2448" height="1632" /></a>Her photography is impactful, captivating + empowering. It was an inspiring evening. She is one of the tops in my books. X', 'Art Opening/ ellen von unwerth: playdate', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'art-opening-ellen-von-unwerth-playdate', '', '', '2015-01-28 06:13:15', '2015-01-28 06:13:15', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=744', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(771, 1, '2013-06-06 20:14:01', '2013-06-06 20:14:01', 'Heading to Harbour Island tomorrow for a little work + probably a lot more play! Beauty Essentials aside {that''s coming...}, here are a few of my must haves for some dreamy downtime on the pink sand beaches...<!--more-->\r\n\r\n{L-R}\r\n\r\nâ€¢My <em>faded blue denim hat;</em> I don''t need to go into why hats are necessary, we all know how important it is to protect yourself when in the sun. Also, a fun bikini accessory!\r\n\r\nâ€¢<em>Tom Ford Samuel Sunnies;</em> These are the sunnies to be out in the sun. A dark lens to protect my overly sensitive eyes + fun circular shape.\r\n\r\nâ€¢<em>FujiFilm Underwater Quicksnap;</em> Need I say more? Ready for the dolphins beauty shot...\r\n\r\nâ€¢PASSPORT! + I carry it around with my pretty <em>Celine Passport Holder.</em>\r\n\r\nâ€¢<em>Girl Land by Caitlin Flanagan;Â </em>I just got it + considering I am being joined on this work trip my three of my fave gal pals, reading into ''what it means for girls to leave childhood behind {VOGUE}'' should be some good beach reading!\r\n\r\nâ€¢<em>Tocca Florence travel candle</em>; hotels are hit or miss with scent, I''d prefer to play it safe + bring my own candle to keep it all smelling lovely.\r\n\r\nâ€¢<em>Goody Elastics;</em> These nude + black twisty ones are my favorite for keeping my hair out of my face at the beach.\r\n\r\nâ€¢<em>Turkish Beach Towel;</em> I got 8 of these towels on my last trip to Turkey + they are a dream. Beautiful fabrics + lightweight so easy to tote around + quick drying. The best.\r\n\r\nâ€¢<em>Moleskin Journal</em>. I love writing in my journal; thoughts, dreams, musings, quotes of the trip + more. I love the Ocean colored Sharpie too.\r\n\r\nAll packed up + ready for some fun in the sun! Happy June! X', 'Bahamamama Essentials/ packing for beachtown', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'beachbabetown-bahamama-essentials', '', '', '2015-01-28 06:07:41', '2015-01-28 06:07:41', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=771', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(778, 1, '2013-06-13 09:00:47', '2013-06-13 09:00:47', 'I was lucky enough to be asked to do my dear friend Karina''s makeup + hair {those details coming!} for her incredible wedding this past weekend in Harbour Island, Bahamas. The cherry on top was having three of my favorite galpals in tow! Happily traded the subway in New York for my golf cart in the Bahamas for a few days. There is something about tropical places that has me stirring with creativity; perhaps the teal, salmon, pink, or aqua colored homes. Or the crystal clear waters. The pink sand beaches. Or maybe the sky that is saturated with stars! I could go on + on.Â  It was refreshing + inspiring in every sense. Here is how I see it...<!--more--><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/harbourislandbeauty10.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-788" alt="harbourislandbeauty10" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/harbourislandbeauty10.jpg" width="3264" height="2174" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/harbourislandbeauty5.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-783" alt="harbourislandbeauty5" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/harbourislandbeauty5.jpg" width="3264" height="2174" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/harbourislandbeauty3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-781" alt="harbourislandbeauty3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/harbourislandbeauty3.jpg" width="2448" height="2448" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/harbourislandbeauty1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-779" alt="harbourislandbeauty1" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/harbourislandbeauty1.jpg" width="2448" height="3264" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/harbourislandbeauty2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-