(853, 1, '2013-07-09 15:30:48', '2013-07-09 15:30:48', 'It''s time for some new summer staples, here are a few fun things I am loving + can''t live without! All suited for summer adventuring in NYC...\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<br /><br /><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/20130709-110149.jpg"><img src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/20130709-110149.jpg" alt="20130709-110149.jpg" class="alignnone size-full" /></a><em>House of Harlow flats</em>: I haven''t had a pair of HoH shoes before. Was drawn to the gold, black + white beading + patterns of lions! I love these flats, they are the perfect transitional pair from day to nite. \r\n\r\n<br /><br /><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/20130709-110527.jpg"><img src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/20130709-110527.jpg" alt="20130709-110527.jpg" class="alignnone size-full" /></a><br /> <br /><br /><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/20130709-110617.jpg"><img src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/20130709-110617.jpg" alt="20130709-110617.jpg" class="alignnone size-full" /></a>\r\n<em>Natural nails</em>: I know I know, how many beauty mags are talking about the color of nails for summer... Well, I am loving my natural nails. I''ve just started using the NailTek system which is mega strengthening + the base + top coat together gives me that healthy sheen.\r\n\r\n<br /><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/20130709-110632.jpg"><img src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/20130709-110632.jpg" alt="20130709-110632.jpg" class="alignnone size-full" /></a><em>Fujifilm Instant Mini 25S camera: This camera! Must have. The original insta pic! I have been taking photos non stop, pinning them </em>all around the apt. Best for capturing summer''s best!\r\n\r\n<br /><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/20130709-110607.jpg"><img src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/20130709-110607.jpg" alt="20130709-110607.jpg" class="alignnone size-full" /></a><br /><em>Fringe</em>! I did it. I chopped my hair, embracing my natural color. It''s good to switch it up every once in a while, + although anxious at first- I am loving the playful new do. \r\n\r\n<br /><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/20130709-110559.jpg"><img src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/20130709-110559.jpg" alt="20130709-110559.jpg" class="alignnone size-full" /></a><br /><em>Loeffler Randall Rider bag</em>: I needed a new summer bag that I could tote around, throw in my bike basket + be durable enough for the summer fun. This is the winner! Love the mint green color + really functional with so many pockets inside as well as the optional strap. \r\n\r\nWhat are you favorite summer accessories? Your can''t-live-withouts? X', 'Summer Loving/ my new favorite accessories', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'summer-loving-my-new-favorite-accessories', '', '', '2015-01-28 06:04:05', '2015-01-28 06:04:05', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=853', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(859, 1, '2013-07-15 16:02:10', '2013-07-15 16:02:10', '&nbsp;\r\n\r\nI am not typically a huge fan of colored mascaras, perhaps the baby blue from the 80''s throws me a bit. But I have to say <em>CHANEL has done it right</em>. Oh + a <em>life changing {gals, for real!} new skin product</em> that really makes flawless so easy. Here is a 5 minute summer look...<!--more--><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/SAmakeupfavorites.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-862" alt="SAmakeupfavorites" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/SAmakeupfavorites.jpg" width="2278" height="2278" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/kevynaucoinmakeup.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-860" alt="kevynaucoinmakeup" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/kevynaucoinmakeup.jpg" width="1180" height="852" /></a>Step by step:\r\n\r\n<em>1/ Cleanse, Moisturize</em>\r\n\r\n<em>2/ Conceal+Correct</em>: Using only a dab of <a href="http://www.bergdorfgoodman.com/p/Kevyn-Aucoin-Sensual-Skin-Enhancer-Face/prod82310065_cat400803__/?icid=&amp;searchType=EndecaDrivenCat&amp;rte=%252Fcategory.jsp%253FitemId%253Dcat400803%2526pageSize%253D30%2526No%253D0%2526refinements%253D&amp;eItemId=prod82310065&amp;cmCat=product" target="_blank">Kevyn Aucoin''s Sensual Skin Enhancer</a> {I am SX10}, I use my fingers to tap + blend around my eyes, nose + mouth. This is definitely more than a concealer + not so much a foundation, it is a brilliant whipped formula that makes covering up any pigmentation, spots or darkness a total breeze! I feel crazy being so excited about this. It''s a skin revelation. The above photo is with the tiniest bit of Skin Enhancer, bedhair + early eyes!\r\n\r\n<em>3/ Curl+Color/</em> I love the <a href="http://www.japonesque.com/catalogue.cfm" target="_blank">Japonesque Lash Curler</a> to curl my lashes. I just discovered le volume de CHANEL in 30-Prune! It''s subtle {the final look does not do the color on my lashes justice, I am not a photo pro!} + pretty. I load it on! I love a textured looking eye, *not to be confused with clumpy though. This prune will bring out the yellow undertones in brown eyes + pop any blue/green eyes too! It''s a fun new way to pop a little color in the makeup.\r\n\r\n<em>4/ Define the brows</em>/ I used <a href="http://www.maccosmetics.com/product/shaded/149/263/Products/Eyes/Brow/Eye-Brows/index.tmpl" target="_blank">MAC eye brow pencil in Lingering</a> to lightly sharpen my brows, then brush through.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/chanelprunemascara.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-861" alt="chanelprunemascara" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/chanelprunemascara.jpg" width="1280" height="960" /></a>\r\n\r\nThat''s the look! Summer poppy prune eyes we love...X\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'New Obsession/ Colored Mascara', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'new-obsession-colored-mascara', '', '', '2015-01-28 06:03:32', '2015-01-28 06:03:32', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=859', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(867, 1, '2013-07-18 01:23:44', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/homemadealmondmilk.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-868" alt="homemadealmondmilk" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/homemadealmondmilk.jpg" width="3070" height="2303" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/homemadealmondmilk1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-869" alt="homemadealmondmilk1" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/homemadealmondmilk1.jpg" width="3264" height="2176" /></a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/homemadealmondmilk7.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-871" alt="homemadealmondmilk7" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/homemadealmondmilk7.jpg" width="3263" height="2448" /></a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/homemadealmondmilk3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-872" alt="homemadealmondmilk3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/homemadealmondmilk3.jpg" width="2448" height="2448" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/homemadealmondmilk6.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-875" alt="homemadealmondmilk6" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/homemadealmondmilk6.jpg" width="2894" height="2169" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/homemadealmondmilk2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-870" alt="homemadealmondmilk2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/homemadealmondmilk2.jpg" width="2590" height="1943" /></a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;', '', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2013-07-18 01:23:44', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=867', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(876, 1, '2013-07-18 02:05:06', '2013-07-18 02:05:06', 'I do love my almond milk. Along with being delicious, almond milk has many health benefits! + It is oh so easy to make yourself at home. Here''s my step by step to make the yummiest vanilla almond milk...<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/homemadealmondmilk7.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-871" alt="homemadealmondmilk7" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/homemadealmondmilk7.jpg" width="3263" height="2448" /></a><em>What you''ll need</em> {above}:\r\n\r\n2 cups of raw almonds {soaked for 8 hrs}\r\n\r\n1 vanilla bean {vanilla extract CAN be used, but not nearly as delicious!}\r\n\r\nA pinch of Cinnamon\r\n\r\nA pinch of Himalayan Sea Salt\r\n\r\nBlender {I love my <a href="http://www.brevilleusa.com/hemisphere-control.html">Breville</a>}\r\n\r\nNut bag {I got mine off of <a href="http://www.amazon.com/Samson-Nut-Milk-Sprouting-Bag/dp/B009AZ20FE/ref=sr_1_4?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1374112622&amp;sr=8-4&amp;keywords=nut+bag">Amazon</a>}\r\n\r\n7 cups of water\r\n\r\nI am basing these measurements on how I like my almond milk, you can adjust the measurements as to how thick, sweet, salty you like it!\r\n\r\n<strong>1/ Soak your raw almonds for a minimum of 8 hours. This gets the nuts nice + plump + for optimal milk</strong><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/homemadealmondmilk5.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-874" alt="homemadealmondmilk5" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/homemadealmondmilk5.jpg" width="3264" height="2176" /></a><strong>2/ Blend the almonds for 45 seconds + then put on liquify mode for 15 seconds</strong>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/homemadealmondmilk1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-869" alt="homemadealmondmilk1" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/homemadealmondmilk1.jpg" width="3264" height="2176" /></a><strong>3/ Pour the almond milk through the nut bag. This is a slow process, you have to be patient as the milk seeps through the bag. You can gently squeeze the bag to get the excess milk out.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/homemadealmondmilk6.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-875" alt="homemadealmondmilk6" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/homemadealmondmilk6.jpg" width="2894" height="2169" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/homemadealmondmilk.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-868" alt="homemadealmondmilk" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/homemadealmondmilk.jpg" width="3070" height="2303" /></a>4/ Then pour the almond milk back into the blender + add your vanilla bean, salt + cinnamon, blend for 30 seconds. </strong>{You can use your almond skins and extras to make almond meal, granola, muffins, cookies etc!}<strong><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/homemadealmondmilk3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-872" alt="homemadealmondmilk3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/homemadealmondmilk3.jpg" width="2448" height="2448" /></a></strong>Voila! There you have it. The milk, stored in an air tight container, will last {I use milk jars + mason jars} for 3-4 days. I love using it for breakfast, over granola, in my smoothies, to drink alone, for dessert over berries + the list goes on! <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/homemadealmondmilk2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-870" alt="homemadealmondmilk2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/homemadealmondmilk2.jpg" width="2590" height="1943" /></a>\r\n\r\nNot only does almond milk provide great health benefits; reducing the risks of heart disease, maintaining balance in cholesterol, assisting in weight loss, but! It has some amazing beauty benefits too. Vitamin E, present in almond milk, protects the skin from the harmful effects of free radicals; this makes our skin healthy and younger looking. There is also an abundance of Vitamin B2, also known as riboflavin, which helps the tissues of the skin, hair and nails to use oxygen. Therefore, healthier, hydrated hair, skin + nails! I will absolutely drink to that... X', 'Drink to Beauty/ homemade vanilla almond milk', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'drinking-beauty-homemade-almond-milk', '', '', '2015-01-28 06:03:35', '2015-01-28 06:03:35', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=876', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(883, 1, '2013-07-31 12:00:06', '2013-07-31 12:00:06', 'I work with many beautiful guys + gals, it''s a pleasure {most of the time!} to work in such an intimate capacity with complete strangers. As I work on so many different models, I see such complexity in the structure of the face. Cheekbones, hairline, lips, brow bone, nose, chin, jawline, eyes, skin color, texture, are just a few things that set us apart. Here are a few new faces I would like to get my hands {+brushes} on...<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<em>GRACE MAHARY:</em> Edmonton, Canada\r\n\r\nThis face! She hails from my hometown, Edmonton... So have to love her. She has a beautiful, symmetrical hairline, gorgeous cheekbones, + thin/wide brows that map what could be my favorite thick + structured brow, all highlighted by her prominent browbone. Gah! What a beauty.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Screen-shot-2013-07-30-at-10.12.36-PM.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-889" alt="Screen shot 2013-07-30 at 10.12.36 PM" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Screen-shot-2013-07-30-at-10.12.36-PM.png" width="815" height="658" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<em>IRINA LISS:Â </em>from Lukhovitsy, Russia\r\n\r\nI love her thin face, natural brows + straight nose. She has a beautiful complexion, can''t wait to see where she goes.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Screen-shot-2013-07-30-at-9.30.45-PM.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-884" alt="Screen shot 2013-07-30 at 9.30.45 PM" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Screen-shot-2013-07-30-at-9.30.45-PM.png" width="573" height="662" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<em>Eleanor Hayes</em>: London England\r\n\r\nEleanor has an interesting look. I love the freckles, interesting hairline + plump lips. This photo does not do her beauty justice..\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/eleanorhayes1.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-886" alt="eleanorhayes" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/eleanorhayes1.png" width="579" height="655" /></a>\r\n\r\n<em>Marikka Juhler</em>: Hammelev, Denmark\r\n\r\nLove Marikka''s thin brows, bright eyes + heart shaped lips. I would love to see her with bleached brows + a deep red lipstick. Perfection.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Screen-shot-2013-07-30-at-9.50.29-PM.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-887" alt="Screen shot 2013-07-30 at 9.50.29 PM" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Screen-shot-2013-07-30-at-9.50.29-PM.png" width="561" height="654" /></a>\r\n\r\n<em>Chiharu:</em> Japan\r\n\r\nWith razo sharp cheekbones, strong jawline + full lips, this one has already won the likes of Stella McCartney, Chanel + is currently featured in an editorial for Vogue Japan. She is one to watch! <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Screen-shot-2013-07-30-at-10.04.53-PM.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-888" alt="Screen shot 2013-07-30 at 10.04.53 PM" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/Screen-shot-2013-07-30-at-10.04.53-PM.png" width="674" height="634" /></a>\r\n\r\nAlthough I apply makeup for a living, I just love clean skin, when the natural features are the focus. A bare face is quite striking. However, when done properly, makeup will be your best friend to enhance it all. X\r\n\r\n*These photos are not my own, pulled from various fashion sites, shot by unknown photographers.', 'Some new faces I would like to paint.', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'some-new-faces-i-would-like-to-paint', '', '', '2015-01-28 05:57:39', '2015-01-28 05:57:39', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=883', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(896, 1, '2013-08-02 15:42:07', '2013-08-02 15:42:07', ' With the summer temperatures on high all month long, it is so important to keep hydrated. Here are a few of my favorite ways to not only feel hydrated but look it too...<!--more-->\r\n\r\nNumero Uno is H2O. I can''t get enough water, especially when I am running around in the heat. I find I drink so much more of it when I am drinking out of a straw, I love this <a href="http://www.amazon.com/Aladdin-20-Ounce-To-Tumbler-Clear/dp/B004Y3E40Q/ref=sr_1_3?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1375457769&amp;sr=8-3&amp;keywords=water+cup+with+straw+and+lid" target="_blank">water cup</a> I found on Amazon. I typically will add a few slices of cucumber or lemon to spruce it up.\r\n\r\nI am a huge fan of Jurlique products, especially the <a href="http://www.jurlique.com/products/r06/rose-body-oil" target="_blank">Rose Body Oil</a>. Jurlique works with all natural products, why I am convinced it works so well for everything your skin really needs. Straight after a bath or shower, I generously put it all over my body. Not only does it smell delightful + floral, but it leaves a pretty sheen too.\r\n\r\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-897" alt="jurliquehydration" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/jurliquehydration.jpg" width="3116" height="2250" />My new favorite lip product is from C.O.Bigelow. The <a href="http://www.bigelowchemists.com/c-o-bigelow-lemon-lip-cream-no-1420.html" target="_blank">Lemon Citron Lip Cream</a>. It is made from 100% lemon oil, + natural products to hydrate your lips. The cream also gives a nude tint to your lips, perfect for summer.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/glossylips.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-898" alt="glossylips" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/glossylips.jpg" width="1148" height="829" /></a>A little trick: the Lip Cream does not need to be limited to your lips, I love to place it with my finger on the brow bone + tops of my cheek bone for a pretty, dewy glow. Over top of that I will spritz <a href="http://www.skinstore.com/p-2872-skyn-iceland-arctic-face-mist-with-multivitamin-complex.aspx" target="_blank">Skyn''s Arctic Face Mist</a> which has loads of vitamins to tone + moisturize your skin whilst on the go...<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-899" alt="cobigelowhighlight" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/cobigelowhighlight.jpg" width="1087" height="785" />That''s all I need for a happy, hydrated summer, now if I could just make a beach appear near my brooklyn condo for daily dips! X\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Hydration: Beat the Heat!', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'hydration-for-the-heat', '', '', '2015-01-28 05:57:03', '2015-01-28 05:57:03', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=896', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(909, 1, '2013-08-05 16:47:40', '2013-08-05 16:47:40', 'So it''s summer + we are all about spending long days in the pool, surviving the heat. Well, what happens when your beauty blonde locks get attacked by some killer chlorine? I used one of my nearest + dearest, Brittany, to show you how you can recoop the babe hair...<!--more-->\r\n\r\nShe was sweet enough to let me use her tragedy for my heroic beauty fix! Here is the damage... When blonde hair is super processed, <em>the hair becomes porous + absorbs anything + everything</em> very quickly. The ends of her hair were a pretty shade of mint green. Yes, if you''re into it, those crazy pastels are trending at the moment. But if not, it''s time to get to work.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/greenhair.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-914" alt="greenhair" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/greenhair.jpg" width="464" height="464" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/bakingsodafix2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-913" alt="bakingsodafix2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/bakingsodafix2.jpg" width="480" height="480" /></a>\r\n\r\nStart by creating a <em>baking soda paste</em>. The amount you need depends on how much of your hair needs a little strip. For Brittany''s ends, 4 Tablespoons to 1 cup of water. You may need to add a little more of either to get a paste like consistency. Mix it + then generously apply to the damaged portion of the hair.Â  Leave on for 15 minutes. This process IS tough on your hair. You are stripping the green out, so don''t try + be a champ + keep it on for a long time, it will kill your hair.\r\n\r\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-911" alt="bakingsodaconditionfix" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/bakingsodaconditionfix.jpg" width="2279" height="2279" />\r\n\r\nNext, rinse baking soda thoroughly +<em> do a quick purple shampoo</em>, I love Magic Lights {which IS tricky to find in the USA hence why I stock up every time I am in Canada}. I say quick because again, your hair is already vulnerable + porous, but the purple will tone your color. Rinse with cold water. Then you need to rebuild your hair! I love the <a href="http://www.ojon.com/product/4735/15439/index.tmpl" target="_blank">Ojon Restorative Treatment</a>; warm the product in your fingers so it becomes emollient then apply to your damp hair, all over. Wrap your head with saran wrap + leave for 30 mins. Then rinse. If you find your hair is still a little fragile, follow up with Ojon again 3/4 days later.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/greenhairBT.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-910" alt="greenhairBT" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/greenhairBT.jpg" width="3264" height="2176" /></a>Here''s the babe hair rebuilt! HMU by me. + Next time you are dipping into a pool, consider using a hair protectant or sealant to keep the blonde hair bombshell! Here''s to happy blonde locks, hey <a href="http://okbrittanyt.tumblr.com/" target="_blank">Brittany</a>!... X\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'When great hair goes green.', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'when-great-hair-goes-green', '', '', '2015-01-28 05:56:29', '2015-01-28 05:56:29', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=909', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(921, 1, '2013-08-09 18:00:02', '2013-08-09 18:00:02', 'My brother {who will win every Jeopardy challenge because he is filled with many incredibly obscure facts} recently passed <a href="http://www.inquisitr.com/818716/soap-microbeads-filling-great-lakes/" target="_blank">this article </a>on to me. I think everyone should read it + be aware of the beauty products they are using + how it may affect us, the environment, + even little fish...<!--more-->\r\n\r\nRead the article! I discovered the tiny little plastic beads we have been using daily that are found in our scrubs + exfoliators have damaging affects on our environment + the little fish that make the Great Lakes their home. The plastic beads are slipping through drains + tiny enough to sift through water treatment plant filters filling the lakes with plastic.\r\n<div id="r1PostCPBlock"><em>"The Great Lakes survey found 600,000 microbeads per square kilometer in two separate Lake Erie samples. The researchers apparently didnâ€™t even know these microbeads where present because they are so small and they donâ€™t float on the surface of the water.</em>"</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>The environmental group, 5 Gyres is working with beauty companies, pleading that they take another look at alternatives to avoid this altogether.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div id="r1PostCPBlock">SO! We lovvve Body Shop, Lâ€™Oreal and Johnson &amp; Johnson whom have all agreed to stop the use of these tiny plastic beads. 5 Gyres are lobbying for all other mega beauty brands to follow suit!</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div>There are much friendlier alternatives as the article states such as, organic exfoliating materials like pumice stone, walnut husks + sand. I can''t say that every single product I use is benefitting the environment, however I would like to think I am aware of certain things to stay away from, this would now be one of them. We can all do our part by checking our beauty collection + see that nothing we are using have the plastic beads. Oh! + Tell everyone. Please link, post + share! X</div>\r\n</div>', 'Be Beauty Conscious: care for your skin + the world we live in', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'be-beauty-conscious-save-our-world', '', '', '2015-01-28 05:55:36', '2015-01-28 05:55:36', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=921', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(932, 1, '2013-08-14 20:17:26', '2013-08-14 20:17:26', 'Here''s a column I did with Cosmopolitan magazine for all the gals who are on the go... Not resting until the sun comes up!\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<br /><br /><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/20130814-161430.jpg"><img src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/20130814-161430.jpg" alt="20130814-161430.jpg" class="alignnone size-full" /></a> Gals, here''s to a very sexy September. X', 'Up All Nite Til the Sun...', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'up-all-nite-to-the-sun', '', '', '2015-01-28 05:54:39', '2015-01-28 05:54:39', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=932', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(934, 1, '2013-08-21 14:24:34', '2013-08-21 14:24:34', 'I had the pleasure of heading up a serious A-TEAM, doing both hair + makeup on 16 talent for the VMA promo video this year. So premise is a bunch of Gaga''s Little Monsters getting all crazy, running around rooftops in BK tagging + posting Gaga paraphernalia with the tag- no sleep until Brooklyn {which is when she will perform on the show this weekend!}. I was in for creating some pretty strong/visually impacting {!} hair styles + makeup...\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\nFor makeup it was all meant to be graphic + strong {dare I say it, Chola + Gaga were the inspiration}, these Little Monsters mean business. SO some gals had the Chola feel, some had the new art pop Gaga feel. Hair was very structured, young, + playful. A few shots of the styling...\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/btsladygaga.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-947" alt="btsladygaga" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/btsladygaga.jpg" width="3055" height="2182" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/btsgaga12.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-939" alt="btsgaga12" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/btsgaga12.jpg" width="2537" height="1812" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/btsgaga11.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-937" alt="btsgaga11" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/btsgaga11.jpg" width="3264" height="2448" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/btsgaga10.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-942" alt="btsgaga10" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/btsgaga10.jpg" width="2498" height="1784" /></a>\r\n\r\nGents working away...<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-938" alt="btsgaga8" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/btsgaga8.jpg" width="2449" height="1749" /> <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-936" alt="btsgaga7" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/btsgaga7.jpg" width="2990" height="2136" />We shot right next to the Williamsburg bridge, look at the sunset at the beginning of the work day {6p!}.<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-946" alt="btsgaga2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/btsgaga2.jpg" width="2448" height="3264" />Mid eve... <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-945" alt="btsgaga5" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/btsgaga5.jpg" width="3035" height="2168" /><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-940" alt="btsgaga9" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/btsgaga9.jpg" width="2294" height="1639" /><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-944" alt="btsgaga4" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/btsgaga4.jpg" width="3192" height="2280" />Above, they had a street artist do the No Sleep, only had one take to do so!  <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-935" alt="btsgaga6" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/btsgaga6.jpg" width="2747" height="1962" /> This is my major amazing team. Thank you to you gals+guys for a big job well done...<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/photo.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-955" alt="photo" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/photo.jpg" width="2982" height="1986" /></a><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-943" alt="btsgaga3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/btsgaga3.jpg" width="3041" height="2172" />+ Then the sun rose, home to bed after a long nite of beauty. I love being a part of these creative jobs. It stretches me to try new techniques + products. Can''t wait to show you the final video tomorrow! X', 'BEHIND THE SCENES: No sleep until Gaga', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'behind-the-scenes-no-sleep-until-gaga', '', '', '2015-01-28 05:54:16', '2015-01-28 05:54:16', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=934', 0, 'post', '', 1),
