(979, 1, '2013-08-28 12:01:11', '2013-08-28 12:01:11', 'One of my favorite treats, the popsicle. Truth be told, I am not much of an ice cream gal- but I may help myself to a popsicle or two any warm nite. Although summer is winding down, the heat is still up in the 80''s + I figured I would share how to make one of my favorite homemade treats...<!--more-->\r\n\r\nI love eating natural foods. Even better when they taste like real treats! Also a huge citrus fan. I was the weird one growing up that always wanted orange flavored anything {to this day I still do not get why it''s the last one to get picked? Meant I always had my way I suppose!}. + At the gelato place, lemon is always an option- so many perks! + Then the mix with fresh herbs- delightful, right? Cucumber to add a little balance to the acidity + you''re off....\r\n\r\nThese measurements are approximate. Here''s what you need:\r\n\r\nsix organic small-medium lemons\r\n\r\none organic small cucumber\r\n\r\none bunch of fresh mint\r\n\r\nthree tablespoons of agave\r\n\r\nthree cups of water\r\n\r\npopsicle mold {there are so many cute options on Amazon!}\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/homemadelemonpopsicle.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-980" alt="homemadelemonpopsicle" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/homemadelemonpopsicle.jpg" width="3264" height="2176" /></a>Firstly I cut off the lemon rinds, you don''t have to make it perfect because a little rind in the popsicle is nice. Then using a juicer, I have my Breville, juice together lemons + cucumber. Set aside.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/homemadepopsicle.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-981" alt="homemadepopsicle" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/homemadepopsicle.jpg" width="3264" height="2176" /></a> Bring three cups of water to a boil + then add mint leaves {saving two sprigs of fresh mint out} + agave, simmer for 6 minutes. You have taken all the goodness + flavor from the mint, strain them + add the mint agave liquid to the lemon + cucumber juice.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/lemonpopsicle.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-984" alt="lemonpopsicle" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/lemonpopsicle.jpg" width="3264" height="2176" /></a>\r\n\r\nLet cool. This is when you taste test! Is the sweetness, tartness to your liking? You can add a little more water or squeeze fresh lemon juice or add more agave if adjustments are needed. Just note that when it freezes, the flavor is dulled a touch, so you want it to be a little stronger than what you''d like. Then, using my pyrex for easy no-spill pours, fill up your popsicle molds. How pretty is the color?<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/lemonmintpopsicle.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-983" alt="lemonmintpopsicle" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/lemonmintpopsicle.jpg" width="3264" height="2176" /></a>\r\n\r\nFinally you''ll add one fresh mint leaf to each mold, this makes them oh so pretty! Then I set the sticks in it + freeze for 8 hours. <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/lemoncucumberpopsicle.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-982" alt="lemoncucumberpopsicle" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/lemoncucumberpopsicle.jpg" width="3264" height="2176" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/photo-2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-990" alt="photo 2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/photo-2.jpg" width="2959" height="1973" /></a>\r\n\r\nVoila! A delicious treat, quick, easy + good for you too... X', 'Cool It/ lemon cucumber mint popsicles', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'cool-it-lemon-cucumber-mint-popsicles', '', '', '2015-01-28 05:52:50', '2015-01-28 05:52:50', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=979', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(993, 1, '2013-09-05 17:53:14', '2013-09-05 17:53:14', 'Just got back from Charlotte, NC where I had the pleasure of shooting <em>NASCAR driver + major babe, Danica Patrick</em>. She is as gorgeous inside as out! Had so much fun working with her + her team on the Concord Race track {could have done with a few degrees cooler!}. All I can tell you is it''s somewhat of a beauty campaign + I cannot wait to show you the final shots! I worked with the most amazing team of people. Here are a few snaps of the day along with <em>must haves to get Danica''s 60''s inspired makeup</em>...<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/danicapatrickbts.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-994" alt="danicapatrickbts" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/danicapatrickbts.jpg" width="3264" height="2176" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/danicapatrickbeauty2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-996" alt="danicapatrickbeauty2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/danicapatrickbeauty2.jpg" width="2076" height="1384" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/photo-3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1000" alt="photo 3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/photo-3.jpg" width="3264" height="2176" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/danicapatrickbeauty.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-995" alt="danicapatrickbeauty" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/danicapatrickbeauty.jpg" width="2758" height="1532" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/photo-5.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1001" alt="photo 5" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/photo-5.jpg" width="3264" height="2174" /></a>I was going for bronzed, dewy skin with a sexy, yet still romantic eye. Here are the must haves for the look!\r\n\r\nâ€¢Caudalie <a href="http://us.caudalie.com/organic-grape-water-travel-size.html?gclid=CLmitabotLkCFcOh4Aod7zQAqA" target="_blank">Grape Water Moisturizing spray</a>\r\n\r\nâ€¢Caudalie <a href="http://us.caudalie.com/intense-moisture-rescue-cream.html" target="_blank">Vinosource Riche Intense Moisture Rescue Cream</a>\r\n\r\nâ€¢Kevyn Aucoin Sensual Balm/ <a href="http://shop.nordstrom.com/s/kevyn-aucoin-beauty-the-sensual-skin-tinted-balm/3410069?cm_cat=datafeed&amp;cm_ite=kevyn_aucoin_beauty_%27the_sensual_skin%27_tinted_balm:631094&amp;cm_pla=makeup:women:foundation&amp;cm_ven=Google_Product_Ads&amp;mr:referralID=a594e560-1653-11e3-a8bc-001b2166c62d" target="_blank"><em>SB03</em></a>\r\n\r\nâ€¢Kevyn Aucoin Creamy Glow/ <a href="http://shop.nordstrom.com/s/kevyn-aucoin-beauty-creamy-glow/3495343?cm_cat=datafeed&amp;cm_ite=kevyn_aucoin_beauty_%27creamy_glow%27:528614_1&amp;cm_pla=makeup:women:cheek&amp;cm_ven=Google_Product_Ads&amp;mr:referralID=b78c0ab4-1653-11e3-a8bc-001b2166c62d" target="_blank"><em>Liquifuschia</em></a>\r\n\r\nâ€¢Kevyn Aucoin Matte Lip Color/<a href="http://shop.nordstrom.com/s/kevyn-aucoin-beauty-the-matte-lip-color/3290518?cm_cat=datafeed&amp;cm_ite=kevyn_aucoin_beauty_%27the_matte%27_lip_color:544079&amp;cm_pla=makeup:women:lip&amp;cm_ven=Google_Product_Ads&amp;mr:referralID=d592b37d-1653-11e3-a8bc-001b2166c62d" target="_blank"><em> For Keeps</em></a>\r\n\r\nâ€¢Essence Precision Eyeliner/ <a href="http://www.essence.eu/us/products/eyes/eyeliner/gel-eyeliner.html" target="_blank"><em>Midnight in Paris</em></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/caudaliekevynaucoinmac.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-998" alt="caudaliekevynaucoinmac" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/caudaliekevynaucoinmac.jpg" width="2048" height="1365" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/sarahapplebynascar.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1006" alt="sarahapplebynascar" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/sarahapplebynascar.jpg" width="2437" height="1846" /></a> I also took up a new job for the day, FLAG GAL {do not fret, I made a quick decision to continue with makeup}! What a fun day. Always interesting to be exposed to an entirely different world {I was watching all of Danica''s races last nite before bed}, now I have to get to the track to see it for myself! She is an inspiring woman, fearless + seems this is just the beginning- check out <a href="http://www.forbes.com/sites/kurtbadenhausen/2013/09/04/a-winning-danica-patrick-is-nascars-biggest-hope-to-restart-growth/" target="_blank">this article</a> Forbes just did on her! Really fun day + being that Danica is such a beauty, made my job especially easy... X', 'BTS: ad campaign with Danica Patrick', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'bts-ad-campaign-with-danica-patrick', '', '', '2015-01-28 05:50:13', '2015-01-28 05:50:13', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=993', 0, 'post', '', 3),
(1011, 1, '2013-09-06 08:00:41', '2013-09-06 08:00:41', ' September issue of Lucky Mag has fantastic article on business bombshell Alexa Hirschfeld, co-founder of Paperless Post. What an incredible story! + A lovely gal, really enjoyed my time with her at the Paperless Post offices + doing her makeup! {Above photo + mu by me, day of} Read on for full article... <!--more--><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/sarahapplebyalexahirschfeld.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1014" alt="sarahapplebyalexahirschfeld" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/sarahapplebyalexahirschfeld.jpg" width="2393" height="3160" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/sarahapplebyalexahirschfeld1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1013" alt="sarahapplebyalexahirschfeld1" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/sarahapplebyalexahirschfeld1.jpg" width="2400" height="3167" /></a><em>Photo</em>: Jonny Valiant / <em>Styling:</em> Elle Strauss /<em> Hair</em>: Staci Child / <em>Makeup</em>: Moi\r\n\r\nX', 'Lucky Magazine/ featuring alexa hirschfeld', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'lucky-magazine-featuring-alexa-hirschfeld', '', '', '2015-01-28 05:50:29', '2015-01-28 05:50:29', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=1011', 0, 'post', '', 2);
