(1022, 1, '2013-09-16 12:06:55', '2013-09-16 12:06:55', '&nbsp;<br /><br /><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/20130916-092122.jpg"><img src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/20130916-092122.jpg" alt="20130916-092122.jpg" class="alignnone size-full" /></a>So much to see + take in this year during NYFW! I think overall, the makeup for Spring 2014 was pretty subdued.. It was a season of muted skin + only some with pops of lip, cheek, or eye. Loved it all! I love the androgyny in a handful of the looks, whether it was simply highlighting the brow or giving the skin a sheen. + Then we got our pops of color + texture every so often! Here are my favorite NYFW Makeup Trends {Hair will post tomorrow!}...\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<strong><em>Charlotte Tilbury at Prabal Gurung:</em> </strong>bleached brows, matte skin, vibrant violet matte lip. Feels very 60''s + I love!\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/PrabalGurung14.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1026" alt="PrabalGurung14" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/PrabalGurung14.png" width="604" height="483" /></a><strong><em>Tom Pecheux for Peter Som:</em></strong><em> </em>clean skin, little neutral blush, cramy contour on eyes, no brow or lash. Clean androgyny, think it played very well with the collection!<em> </em><em><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Peter-SomNYFW14.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1024" alt="Peter SomNYFW14" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Peter-SomNYFW14.png" width="578" height="591" /></a></em><strong><em>Gucci</em><em><strong> W</strong>estman for Rag + Bone:</em></strong><em> </em>brows brushed up, clear glossy eye, bold orange lip. First time Rag + Bone has gone for a bold lip like this, Gucci can do no wrong- perfection.<em> </em><em><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Rag+BoneNYFW14.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1023" alt="Rag+BoneNYFW14" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Rag+BoneNYFW14.png" width="611" height="399" /></a></em><strong><em>James</em><em><strong> Kaliardos for Nicole Miller:</strong></em></strong><em> </em>bold brows, contoured warm tone eye, highlighted nose + browbone, bold deep purple lip. I love this, so simple + clean, yet romantic + mysterious. <strong><strong> </strong><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/NicoleMillernyfw14.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1025" alt="NicoleMillernyfw14" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/NicoleMillernyfw14.png" width="471" height="432" /></a></strong><strong>James<em> Kaliardos for Rodarte:</em></strong><em> </em>matte skin, contoured temples + cheekbones, brows brushed up without definition, matte nude lip + medium graphic liner. James is so good, I love everything he does- this is simple yet striking.<em> </em><em><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Rodarte14nyfw.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1027" alt="Rodarte14nyfw" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Rodarte14nyfw.png" width="414" height="440" /></a></em>Tomorrow comes my favorite hair looks..... in the meantime I''ll be stalking my favorite sites that are capturing the LFW shows! X\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'NYFW Makeup Trends: five favorites from new york fashion week', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'nyfw-makeup-trends-five-favorites-from-nyfw', '', '', '2015-01-28 05:34:06', '2015-01-28 05:34:06', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=1022', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(1035, 1, '2013-09-17 13:29:25', '2013-09-17 13:29:25', 'This NYFW, we saw structure + texture over + over again, I am not complaining! Some clean + others a beautiful mess. Here are my favorites from the week...<!--more-->\r\n\r\nPaul Hanlon for 3.1 PHILLIP LIM:Â  <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/3.1philliplimss14.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1037" alt="3.1philliplimss14" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/3.1philliplimss14.png" width="440" height="498" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/VERAWANGSS14.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1038" alt="VERAWANGSS14" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/VERAWANGSS14.png" width="433" height="540" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong><em>Guido Palau for ALEXANDER WANG:</em></strong>Guido surprised us a little bit with such a loose texture for AWANG this season, but loved the matte texture + center part.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Alexanderwangss14.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1039" alt="Alexanderwangss14" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Alexanderwangss14.png" width="451" height="641" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<em><strong>Eugene Souleiman for DONNA KARAN:</strong></em> Sleek, structured hair, half back {hi 90''s!} + zero volume. Classic<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/DONNAKARANss14.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1036" alt="DONNAKARANss14" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/DONNAKARANss14.png" width="449" height="570" /></a><em><strong>Jen Atkin for FALLON:</strong></em> Beautiful messy, undone texture, accessorized with hair jewelry giving the hair peeks of metal, really cool.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/fallonss14.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1040" alt="fallonss14" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/fallonss14.png" width="423" height="370" /></a>\r\n\r\nOverall, really loving + inspired with all of the looks thus far. I love when artists take a really natural approach to styling + create something unique around it, whether it be the texture, finish, or accessory. Always a good time to get inspired + push me to try new things... X', 'NYFW Hair Trends: five favorites from new york fashion week', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'hair-inspiration-nyfw-favorites', '', '', '2015-02-04 05:30:27', '2015-02-04 05:30:27', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=1035', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(1049, 1, '2013-09-24 12:28:22', '2013-09-24 12:28:22', 'Here''s a really fun advertorial {HEY BCBG!} I did with the babe gals of Seventeen Magazine for their September issue. Annabet styled/Staci did the hair/I did the makeup...<!--more--><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/SEV090113BCBG005.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1056" alt="SEV090113_185" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/SEV090113BCBG005.jpg" width="983" height="1475" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/SEV090113BCBG004.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1055" alt="SEV090113_185" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/SEV090113BCBG004.jpg" width="983" height="1475" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/SEV090113BCBG003.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1054" alt="SEV090113_185" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/SEV090113BCBG003.jpg" width="1123" height="1685" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/SEV090113BCBG002.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1053" alt="SEV090113_184" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/SEV090113BCBG002.jpg" width="1073" height="1603" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/SEV090113BCBG001.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1052" alt="SEV090113_185" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/SEV090113BCBG001.jpg" width="1123" height="1685" /></a>A lip + some textured hair works every time! X', 'NEW WORK: september issue of seventeen magazine', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'new-work-september-issue-of-seventeen-magazine', '', '', '2015-01-28 05:45:17', '2015-01-28 05:45:17', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=1049', 0, 'post', '', 0),
