(1083, 1, '2013-09-04 12:15:19', '2013-09-04 12:15:19', 'As Valentine NYC prepares to launch their lingerie line, the gals have creatively turned their website into what has become somewhat of a photo journal documenting their network of creative friends. The portraits offer an intimate glimpse into the personal lives of their friends and acquaintances from around the world. What started as an alternative to a splash page, the website has become an insight into the lives of creative individuals from all walks of life, united through their hard work and perseverance in achieving their goals. A pleasure to be featured...<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1084" alt="Valentinefinal" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Valentinefinal.jpg" width="2683" height="7463" />It was a really lovely day, very different being in front of the camera giving me so much respect for the models I work with daily! Images by <a href="http://alimitton.com/" target="_blank">Ali Mitton</a> + check out <a href="http://valentine-nyc.com/" target="_blank">ValentineNYC</a> for the full blog + interview... X', 'WELCOME HOME/ valentine gals at mine chatting about life+love', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'welcome-home-valentine-gals-at-mine-chatting-about-lifelove', '', '', '2015-02-04 06:45:05', '2015-02-04 06:45:05', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=1083', 0, 'post', '', 2),
(1093, 1, '2013-09-27 14:18:52', '2013-09-27 14:18:52', 'I have had my Mum + Gram from Alberta Canada, visiting me this last week + it''s always fun to indulge on the many incredible activities NY offers... It also reminds me that I don''t explore enough. We spent an afternoon in my neighborhood {!} at the Brooklyn Botanical Gardens. How have I not spent more time there. I was so inspired by the flora, colors, textures, smells {the fragrance garden is my favorite!} + to have that oasis so close to home, in the midst of a concrete jungle is a blessing. A few snaps from the day...<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1094" alt="BKBotanicalGardens" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens.jpg" width="2418" height="1534" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1095" alt="BKBotanicalGardens1" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens1.jpg" width="2828" height="1534" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1096" alt="BKBotanicalGardens2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens2.jpg" width="2566" height="1534" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1097" alt="BKBotanicalGardens3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens3.jpg" width="2632" height="1534" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens4.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1098" alt="BKBotanicalGardens4" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens4.jpg" width="2738" height="1536" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens5.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1099" alt="BKBotanicalGardens5" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens5.jpg" width="2466" height="1534" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens6.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1100" alt="BKBotanicalGardens6" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens6.jpg" width="2354" height="1536" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens7.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1101" alt="BKBotanicalGardens7" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens7.jpg" width="2656" height="1534" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens8.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1102" alt="BKBotanicalGardens8" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens8.jpg" width="2550" height="1536" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens9.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1103" alt="BKBotanicalGardens9" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens9.jpg" width="2342" height="1534" /></a>Â  <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens11.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1105" alt="BKBotanicalGardens11" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens11.jpg" width="2702" height="1534" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/botanicalgardensbk.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1108" alt="botanicalgardensbk" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/botanicalgardensbk.jpg" width="1794" height="2046" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens12.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1106" alt="BKBotanicalGardens12" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens12.jpg" width="2362" height="1536" /></a>It is incredible to me the different shapes plants + flowers + trees have. They are all so unique + individual. + This is the tiniest sampling of what the whole world offers! I am so excited for Autumn, with all our surroundings changing... Now head over to your local gardens to enjoy the landscapes + solitude! X', 'Breathing Beauty/ brooklyn botanical gardens', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'breathing-beauty-brooklyn-botanical-gardens', '', '', '2015-01-28 05:36:35', '2015-01-28 05:36:35', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=1093', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1112, 1, '2013-09-02 13:24:41', '2013-09-02 13:24:41', 'I stole my dear friend, Alex, for an afternoon of riding our bikes {little white lightning is mine + gonzales belongs to her} around Brooklyn + then snuck in a little glam time to play with her brows + lashes. I documented it all so you could see the process... Lucky me, as she models very professionally, you''d think she had done this before {wink}! Here is how to get more refined + finished brows with feathery lashes...<!--more--><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY6.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1118" alt="ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY6" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY6.jpg" width="2448" height="2448" /></a>\r\n\r\n<em>Start out with a clean + moisturized face<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1114" alt="ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY2.jpg" width="2585" height="1723" />Beginning with the lashes! Start by curling your natural lashes, I like the <a href="http://www.japonesque.com/catalogue.cfm" target="_blank">Japonesque Power Curl Eyelash Curler</a>. Be sure to move the curler around your lash line you you don''t have one obvious bend. <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY11.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1123" alt="ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY11" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY11.jpg" width="1280" height="960" /></a></em><em>Now for mascara! <a href="http://www.stilacosmetics.com/product/glamoureyes-mascara.do?from=Search" target="_blank">Stila''s Glamoureyes mascara</a> in black is a favorite for building texture. Take your time + get right to the root of your lashes.</em><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY9.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1121" alt="ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY9" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY9.jpg" width="2202" height="1468" /></a>\r\n\r\n<em>Onto the brows! A quick trick is to brush the brows downwards before applying liner, this way you see the natural top of your brow line. I used <a href="http://www.clinique.com/product/1595/4799/Makeup/Brows/Brow-Keeper/index.tmpl" target="_blank">Clinique Brow Keeper in Warm Brown</a> + apply the liner in upward strokes. You don''t have to fill the entire brow, but make sure it''s all even. Most of us have spotty brows, + a little fill in is always good.<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1119" alt="ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY7" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY7.jpg" width="2547" height="1698" /><em>As you are filling in, you can then brush the brows up {where they will be finished} to see where you are at with shape.</em></em><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY5.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1117" alt="ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY5" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY5.jpg" width="3060" height="2040" /></a><em>Then we are going to bump up the natural lash, I love the <a href="http://www.popbeauty.co.uk/Popbeauty_Products/Lashes/Dressed_Up_Lashes/index.html" target="_blank">Pop Beauty individual lashes</a> . On the back of my hand, I put a dab of <a href="http://www.soap.com/p/duo-surgical-grade-eyelash-adhesive-284042?site=CA&amp;utm_source=Google&amp;utm_medium=cpc_S&amp;utm_term=HTU-009&amp;utm_campaign=GoogleAW&amp;CAWELAID=1581015820&amp;utm_content=pla&amp;adtype=pla&amp;cagpspn=pla" target="_blank">Duo eyelash glue</a> + then use <a href="http://www.makeupforever.com/products/tweezer.html#.Ukl3TSSls14" target="_blank">Make Up For Ever Tweezers</a> to pull an individual lash from the pack + dip it lightly {just so the very point has a spot of white glue on it}. </em>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1113" alt="ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY.jpg" width="3264" height="2176" /></a><em>Then starting with the outer corner, place the individual lash IN your lashes {they can sit on top, but for maximum natural finish, get them in between}. I used 6/7 per eye laying then 2/3 of the way in. This will draw your eye open + out. <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1115" alt="ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY3.jpg" width="3124" height="2083" /></a></em>\r\n\r\n+ The final look: full, refined brows with natural looking feathery lashes. This is a great look anytime, would look gorgeous with a poppy lip for daytime + stronger, darker lip for evening. Thank you Alex, you beauty. X<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY4.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1116" alt="ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY4" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY4.jpg" width="3264" height="2176" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'How to: refined brows + feathery lashes', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'how-to-refined-brows-feathery-lashes', '', '', '2015-02-04 06:36:49', '2015-02-04 06:36:49', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=1112', 0, 'post', '', 4),
(1129, 1, '2013-10-04 14:46:58', '2013-10-04 14:46:58', '<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/N30-24-312.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1130" alt="N30 24 - 312" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/N30-24-312.jpg" width="694" height="865" /></a>Hot off the press, new editorial for NOI.SE magazine with the striking Pauline Van der Cruysse...<!--more--><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/N30-24-318.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1136" alt="N30 24 - 318" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/N30-24-318.jpg" width="694" height="865" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/N30-24-314.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1132" alt="N30 24 - 314" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/N30-24-314.jpg" width="694" height="865" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/N30-24-315.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1133" alt="N30 24 - 315" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/N30-24-315.jpg" width="694" height="865" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/N30-24-3171.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1139" alt="N30 24 - 317" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/N30-24-3171.jpg" width="2234" height="3000" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/N30-24-3161.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1138" alt="N30 24 - 316" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/N30-24-3161.jpg" width="2230" height="3000" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/N30-24-3131.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1137" alt="N30 24 - 313" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/N30-24-3131.jpg" width="2240" height="3000" /></a><em>PHOTOGRAPHY:</em> Luzena Adams | <em>STYLING</em>: Morgan Gibbons | <em>HAIR</em>: Noah Hatton | <em>MAKEUP</em>: Moi', 'New Work: editorial for NOI.SE magazine', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'new-work-editorial-for-noi-se-magazine', '', '', '2013-10-04 14:46:58', '2013-10-04 14:46:58', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=1129', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1145, 1, '2013-10-11 15:16:03', '2013-10-11 15:16:03', 'Artist Dorothea Rockburne was born in Canada + raised in America. I spent an afternoon this week at the Moma + loved her exhibit, Drawing Which Makes Itself. As an artist, she is very minimal with her approach to every piece using materials such as paper, chipboard, crude oil, steel + carbon paper. ''She is interested in paper, not just as the ground for a drawing but as an active material, it''s inherent qualities determining the form of the artwork''. All coming together to be beautiful pieces, one I''d love to have in my home...\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1146" alt="photo 1-1" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/photo-1-1.jpg" width="2982" height="1988" />\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/photo-1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1147" alt="photo 1" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/photo-1.jpg" width="3264" height="2448" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/photo-2-1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1148" alt="photo 2-1" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/photo-2-1.jpg" width="3264" height="2448" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/photo-2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1149" alt="photo 2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/photo-2.jpg" width="3165" height="2110" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/photo-3-1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1150" alt="photo 3-1" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/photo-3-1.jpg" width="3264" height="2174" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/photo-3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1151" alt="photo 3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/photo-3.jpg" width="3264" height="2448" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/photo-4-1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1152" alt="photo 4-1" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/photo-4-1.jpg" width="3194" height="2129" /></a>\r\nIt''s inspiring to see artists work in such a minimal fashion, yet creating intricate pieces utilizing basic materials to expose depths.', 'Inspiration: Artist/ Dorathea Rockburne', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'inspiration-artist-dorathea-rockburne', '', '', '2015-01-28 05:35:25', '2015-01-28 05:35:25', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=1145', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(1164, 1, '2013-10-15 13:11:06', '2013-10-15 13:11:06', 'Tis my favorite season of all + I am readying my lips for Autumn! Truthfully, it doesn''t matter which season it is, I am always ready for a bold lip, however Fall calls for rich tones of orange + red. Here''s my how to to achieve the perfect application with my favorite products...<!--more--><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/falllipmain.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1167" alt="falllipmain" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/falllipmain.jpg" width="3186" height="2124" /></a>\r\n\r\nWhat you need:\r\n\r\n<em>â€¢CHANEL <a href="http://www.chanel.com/en_US/fragrance-beauty/Makeup-Powder-LES-BEIGES-137174/sku/137177" target="_blank">Les Beiges healthy glow sheer color</a> {NÂº30}</em> the prettiest matte bronzer\r\n\r\n<em>â€¢DERMABLEND <a href="http://www.dermablend.com/concealers/concealer-severe-flaws/quickfix.htm" target="_blank">quick fix concealer</a> {Medium}</em> a full coverage concealer with lots of pigment\r\n\r\n<em>â€¢STILA <a href="http://www.stilacosmetics.com/product/stay+all+day+liquid+lipstick.do" target="_blank">stay all day liquid lipstick</a> {Tesoro}</em> major babe matte lipstick, i sound like a broken record with this product!\r\n\r\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1165" alt="falllip" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/falllip.jpg" width="3202" height="2135" />/after applying foundation/mascara/brow etc, take the concealer + using the pad of your finger dab product around your mouth to get a clear foundation to work on. this also gives your lip color the mainstage!<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/falllip4.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1166" alt="falllip4" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/falllip4.jpg" width="3264" height="2448" /></a>\r\n\r\n/using a fluffy powder brush, contour the hollow of your cheekbone for structure + a little definition<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1172" alt="flllip2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/flllip2.jpg" width="2762" height="1841" />/with the wand of the stila liquid lipstick, make an ''X'' on the top of your lip creating the bow + most important shape of your lip + sets your lip style. throughout history, the bow says so much about which decade you are in! check out this reference image i borrowed from beauty press...<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/lip-shape-reference-decades.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1176" alt="lip shape reference decades" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/lip-shape-reference-decades.png" width="640" height="337" /></a>\r\n\r\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1168" alt="falllippost5" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/falllippost5.jpg" width="1845" height="1230" />/trace lips from corners of bottom lip to center, here you will begin to see shape + get a better idea of where you need to make balance + how to even out your lips {everyone''s lips are uneven}<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1174" alt="dalllippost8" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/dalllippost8.jpg" width="3232" height="2155" />/connect your bow down to the corner of your mouth<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/falllippost9.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1171" alt="falllippost9" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/falllippost9.jpg" width="3120" height="2080" /></a>/fill in your lips<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1169" alt="falllippost6" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/falllippost6.jpg" width="2112" height="1408" />/do connect your lips together! nothing worse than a color disconnect- your lips are joined, why shouldn''t your lipstick!... {although not an attractive photo here you can see I am using the tip of my nail to do any necessary clean up}<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/mainlipfallpost.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1173" alt="mainlipfallpost" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/mainlipfallpost.jpg" width="3264" height="2448" /></a>\r\n\r\nVoila! All you need is a steady hand with 5 minutes to get your lip on + you''re ready to take on Fall... X', 'HOW TO: perfect matte lip for fall', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'how-to-perfect-matte-lip-for-fall', '', '', '2015-01-28 05:35:07', '2015-01-28 05:35:07', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=1164', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(1184, 1, '2013-10-17 14:52:47', '2013-10-17 14:52:47', '<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/carobbitesrecipe8.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1191" alt="carobbitesrecipe8" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/carobbitesrecipe8.jpg" width="3264" height="2174" /></a>As I am often on the go + unsure what the food will be like on set, I have found it extremely helpful to carry my favorite snick snacks with me. I am a big fan of nuts + dried fruit, but it gets old + then I am reaching for the nearest chocolate. I have been experimenting with several new recipes + carob bites are by far my new favorite snack! Here''s my customized recipe on how to make...<!--more-->\n\nCarob is a versatile plant that is a fantastic non-dairy alternative to chocolate. Carob is also high in fiber, which may help lower your cholesterol. Being a chocolate lover, I know it''s hard to believe something this healthy can compare, it does! + Not only are they good for curbing your chocolate craving, they are also full of protein + energy. Here''s my take on a raw food brownie. Some recipes for Carob squares call for Cocoa powder {processed + high in sugar}, I prefer Cacao powder + adding some agave to balance sweetness. You can feel free to try other nuts/sweeteners/or add other seeds to make it interesting...\n\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1186" alt="carobbitesrecipe1" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/carobbitesrecipe1.jpg" width="2448" height="3264" /><em><strong>What you need:</strong></em>\n\n/1/2 cup walnuts, raw\n\n/1/2 cup almonds, raw + sliced\n\n/3/4 cup dates, pitted + chopped\n\n/2 tablespoons carob powder\n\n/3 tablespoons cacao powder\n\n/3 tablespoons agave\n\n/1 teaspoon vanilla bean paste\n\n/2 tablespoons unsweetened coconut\n\n<em><strong>What to do:</strong></em>\n\nIn food processor, blend nuts together on high for 15 seconds or until the nuts are chopped coarsely\n\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/carobbitesrecipe4.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1188" alt="carobbitesrecipe4" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/carobbitesrecipe4.jpg" width="3264" height="2448" /></a>\n\nAdd chopped dates, blend until dates are the same size as the nuts<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1185" alt="carobbitesrecipe" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/carobbitesrecipe.jpg" width="3264" height="2448" />Add both cacao + carob powders, blend in<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/carobbitesrecipe.jpg">\n</a>\n\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/carobbitesrecipe3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1187" alt="carobbitesrecipe3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/carobbitesrecipe3.jpg" width="3264" height="2448" /></a>Add unsweetened coconut, blend\n\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/carobbitesrecipe5.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1189" alt="carobbitesrecipe5" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/carobbitesrecipe5.jpg" width="3264" height="2448" /></a>Add agave + vanilla bean paste, blend until the mixture is dark brown + crumbly, it should hold together if pressed. If you are finding it doesn''t hold together well, add 3/4 more dates + blend in<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1190" alt="carobbitesrecipe6" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/carobbitesrecipe6.jpg" width="3264" height="2448" />\n\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/carobbitesrecipe10.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1193" alt="carobbitesrecipe10" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/carobbitesrecipe10.jpg" width="3264" height="2448" /></a>I lay out the mixture on a cutting board [above] + then using my hands press into the mixture to create a square + refrigerate for mimimum of 2 hours to harden. <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/carobbitesrecipe9.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1192" alt="carobbitesrecipe9" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/carobbitesrecipe9.jpg" width="3264" height="2448" /></a>Then chop into small squares + hope they don''t disappear too quickly!\n\nBeing aware of what you are eating + treating your body to is important. Having a healthy balance of food + drink is not only good for your insides but reflects on the outside, your weight, skin, hair, nails etc. Healthy eating is a big part of beauty, the best part is finding both healthy + delicious in the same bite...! X\n\n&nbsp;', 'Living Well/ energizing with carob bites', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'living-well-energizing-with-carob-bites', '', '', '2013-10-17 14:52:47', '2013-10-17 14:52:47', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=1184', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1196, 1, '2013-10-24 15:26:58', '2013-10-24 15:26:58', '&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThere''s a fine line for me between having cute damaged hair {you know that blond matte texture} + bad damaged hair, having your ends split + break + fall off. It is very typical for me that by the end of summer, after my hair has been bleached then sun bleached, up in a bun + unloved, I am dealing with very very thirsty hair. {Please no judgment on the photo above!} Here are my go to products + regimen how to restore + bring the life back to your locks...<!--more--><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/davinesojon.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1198" alt="davinesojon" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/davinesojon.jpg" width="2958" height="1972" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/ojonhaircare.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1203" alt="ojonhaircare" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/ojonhaircare.jpg" width="3264" height="2448" /></a>Start by using a quarter sized dollop of<em> <a href="http://www.ojon.com/product/5063/15439/giftssets/shopbycategory/Travel-Sizes/damage-reverse-Restorative-Hair-Treatment/index.tmpl" target="_blank">Ojon Restorative Hair Treatment</a>.</em> It is chunky + solid at first, but warm it in your hands + it emulsifies.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/davinesojon2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1200" alt="davinesojon2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/davinesojon2.jpg" width="1233" height="822" /></a>Apply the oil like treatment to damaged parts of your hair {*put it only where absolutely necessary, you don''t want to over condition your hair, it will become soft + break off. For my color- I have kept it just on the ends as my natural hair doesn''t need the treatment}. Keep the treatment on your hair for 15-30 minutes. If you need a major restoration, you can leave on for up to an hour with plastic wrap around your hair to keep it conditioning.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/davinesojon1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1199" alt="davinesojon1" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/davinesojon1.jpg" width="1093" height="729" /></a>+ Then continuing with my obsession keeping seasonal with all things, I have switched to<em> Davines</em> <em><a href="http://www.davines.com/en/products/view/alchemic-shampoo-tobacco" target="_blank">Alchemic Shampoo</a> + <a href="http://www.davines.com/en/products/view/alchemic-conditioner-tobacco" target="_blank">Conditioner in Tobacco</a>.</em> The perfect scent for fall! + This shampoo + conditioner makes your hair light + full + conditioned without being heavy. Not to mention smelling delicious. So I wash + condition my hair + then let air dry, fast for me as I have very fine hair, until it''s damp + then follow with a quick blow out. Here''s my hair after it''s been blown out, yes it''s naturally this straight!...<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/davinesojonhaircare33.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1207" alt="davinesojonhaircare3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/davinesojonhaircare33.jpg" width="1280" height="960" /></a>Then to smooth out the ends, I add a dime sized drop of the Davines <em><a href="http://www.davines.com/en/products/view/oi-oil" target="_blank">Absolute Beautifying Potion</a></em> to the ends. It is really light + brings the ends together, adding a subtle sheen. <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/davineshairoil.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1197" alt="davineshairoil" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/davineshairoil.jpg" width="2970" height="1980" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/davinesojonhaircare.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1202" alt="davinesojonhaircare" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/davinesojonhaircare.jpg" width="1280" height="960" /></a>+ Voila! New hair. This is the perfect quick fix for those who are growing your hair out, or don''t make time for cuts every 6 weeks but want it to look good... With all of that said, my cut is booked for next week! Happy hair don''t care! X', 'HOW TO/ dealing with damaged hair', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'how-to-dealing-with-damaged-hair', '', '', '2015-01-28 05:27:38', '2015-01-28 05:27:38', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=1196', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1212, 1, '2013-10-28 12:06:13', '2013-10-28 12:06:13', 'Here''s a new story I did with mega talented photographer + Canadian {!}, Geoff Barrenger. We worked with Latvian, Guntars, + ran around the sketchier part of Brooklyn for a day. Anthony Pedraza styled with Viktor+Rolf, Rag + Bone, Louboutin etc...<!--more--><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Guntar-by-Geoff-Barrenger-Shot-1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1213" alt="Guntar by Geoff Barrenger - Shot 1" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Guntar-by-Geoff-Barrenger-Shot-1.jpg" width="2640" height="3360" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Guntar-by-Geoff-Barrenger-Shot-1B.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1214" alt="Guntar by Geoff Barrenger - Shot 1B" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Guntar-by-Geoff-Barrenger-Shot-1B.jpg" width="2640" height="3360" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Guntar-by-Geoff-Barrenger-Shot-2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1215" alt="Guntar by Geoff Barrenger - Shot 2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Guntar-by-Geoff-Barrenger-Shot-2.jpg" width="2640" height="3360" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Guntar-by-Geoff-Barrenger-Shot-3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1216" alt="Guntar by Geoff Barrenger - Shot 3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Guntar-by-Geoff-Barrenger-Shot-3.jpg" width="2640" height="3360" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Guntar-by-Geoff-Barrenger-Shot-4.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1217" alt="Guntar by Geoff Barrenger - Shot 4" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Guntar-by-Geoff-Barrenger-Shot-4.jpg" width="2640" height="3360" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Guntar-by-Geoff-Barrenger-Shot-5.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1219" alt="Guntar by Geoff Barrenger - Shot 5" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Guntar-by-Geoff-Barrenger-Shot-5.jpg" width="2640" height="3360" /></a>In Guntar''s hair I used <a href="http://www.bumbleandbumble.com/product/spp.tmpl?CATEGORY_ID=CAT74&amp;PRODUCT_ID=224" target="_blank"><em>Bumble+bumble Thickening Hair Spray</em></a>, <a href="http://www.davines.com/en/products/view/finest-oil-non-oil-n1" target="_blank"><em>Davines Finest Oil Non Oil</em></a> + <a href="http://www.davines.com/en/products/view/defining-wonder-wax" target="_blank"><em>Davines Wonder Wax</em></a>. X', 'NEW WORK/ guntars by the bridge', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'new-work-guntars-by-the-bridge', '', '', '2015-01-28 05:27:18', '2015-01-28 05:27:18', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=1212', 0, 'post', '', 0);
