(1221, 1, '2013-11-02 14:24:14', '2013-11-02 14:24:14', 'Those who know me well are aware that in my downtime, I love to host. There is nothing better than a beautiful table surrounded by ones you love whilst enjoying copious amounts of delicious cocktails + food + wine. Living in New York, it''s tricky to make the space for a big dining table + it''s only been this last year I have been blessed enough to make it happen! I have been making attempts to build beautiful {not complex, especially if I am wearing the chef''s hat!} table settings to complement what I am serving. Here is my super easy to create, fall set up...<!--more-->\r\n\r\nI should mention, I co hosted this gals'' nite with one of my nearest + dearest, Alex. She + I are on the same page when it comes to being surrounded by beautiful things so this was easy. In keeping everything seasonally appropriate, I went to the Flower District to pick up greenery, flowers, gourds + baby pumpkins. I love everything white, so naturally went for a few of the baby white pumpkins. Then at the art supply I picked up some metallic spray paint- gold + silver.<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1226" alt="dinnerpartyblog5" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/dinnerpartyblog5.jpg" width="3174" height="2116" />Start by taping half of the pumpkins, try to get the tape {masking tape would have been MUCH easier to use, alas I didn''t have it on hand} into each crevasse on the pumpkin for the best result.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/dinnerpartyblog3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1225" alt="dinnerpartyblog3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/dinnerpartyblog3.jpg" width="3264" height="2176" /></a>Then, spray away! I wanted the bottom halves of the pumpkins metallic, the gourds + corn sprayed solid.<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1229" alt="dinnerpartyblog8" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/dinnerpartyblog8.jpg" width="3204" height="2136" /><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/dinnerpartyblog10.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1230" alt="dinnerpartyblog10" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/dinnerpartyblog10.jpg" width="2724" height="1816" /></a>For the napkins, I placed a sprig of fern + set them with a gold letter at the bottom.<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1227" alt="dinnerpartyblog6" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/dinnerpartyblog6.jpg" width="3200" height="2133" />I made a base at the table of greenery + then had two vases of Hydrangeas, I opted for the muted tones to let the golds and silvers really pop.<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1228" alt="dinnerpartyblog7" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/dinnerpartyblog7.jpg" width="3264" height="2448" /> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/dinnerpartyblog1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1223" alt="dinnerpartyblog1" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/dinnerpartyblog1.jpg" width="3200" height="2133" /></a> + Voila! Of course, the only other piece that is required for a delicious evening, is a beautiful meal to go along with it all. We served Cream of Spinach soup, then a Scalloped Potato dish with Canadian Bacon followed by an arugula/fennel/radicchio/dill salad + for the finale, made-from-scratch individual pumpkin pies with a dollop of vanilla bean whipped cream.<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1236" alt="dinnerpartymealfinal" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/dinnerpartymealfinal1.jpg" width="3264" height="1464" />It was a really fun evening, I am already scheming what I can spray paint next, oh!Â  + Dinner settings for Thanksgiving {#2!}.... X\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'FALL LOVING/ crafting a dinner party', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'fall-loving-crafting-a-dinner-party', '', '', '2015-01-28 05:27:29', '2015-01-28 05:27:29', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=1221', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(1243, 1, '2013-11-04 12:46:17', '2013-11-04 12:46:17', '&nbsp;\r\n\r\nRemember when I was <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/summer-loving-my-new-favorite-accessories/" target="_blank">OH SO EXCITED</a> about chopping a fringe. Right. Here we are not even four months later + they are so long + I am over. them. Time for another change! Seeing as 99% of gals that I know go through this frustration, + this is clearly the worst part about having a cute fringe, I thought I would share my favorite three ways to style my hair during this tricky time...<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<em>Bump up your overgrown fringe</em>. Load up your damp hair with product, I am using Davines Mattering Mousse for wizards + blow your fringe up + round in the center + then out + wispy on the corners. You can always use a straightener to make it more dramatic too. {*If you have a blunt bang cut, have your stylist cut into the center of the fringe + up a little bit + then slowly texture it outwards- this will give you a little more flexibility during this time!}<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1247" alt="fringefix4" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/fringefix4.jpg" width="3264" height="2174" />This will give you a voluminous, playful fringe that easily sweeps out of your eyes for that dreamy, 70s feel.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/fringefix3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1246" alt="fringefix3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/fringefix3.jpg" width="3264" height="2174" /></a><em>Braid it in!Â </em>Beginning just past your temple, do a little french braid in the front, all the way around your hairline, including all of your fringe in. I use a little {very little!} wonder wax in the hair that I am placing in the braid. As the hair can be short, this help weigh it down + give it some hold. Once your braid is in, gently go through + pull out the hair to give it a fuller, more romantic look. Secure the end of the braid close to the top of the ear with a few bobby pins.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/fringefix2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1245" alt="fringefix2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/fringefix2.jpg" width="3264" height="2174" /></a><em>Polish + Pin it!</em> I love the classic feel of this look, I typically don''t love the obvious bobby pins, I think it works here. Give your hair a clean part: center more edgy / side is softer + then pull back all hair in a low clip in the back. Using a color neutral pin, using one per side, twist fringe under to longer strands + carefully place pin. Keep both sides even.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/fringefix1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1244" alt="fringefix1" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/fringefix1.jpg" width="3264" height="2174" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/davinesproductfringebang.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1252" alt="davinesproductfringebang" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/davinesproductfringebang.jpg" width="2907" height="1938" /></a>As much as this process can be tedious, I enjoy the challenge of getting creative + it makes me want to try new things... What are some of the ways you style your hair when growing out your fringe? X', 'HOW TO/ in between bangs + fixing the fringe.', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'how-to-in-between-bangs-fixing-the-fringe', '', '', '2015-01-28 05:26:56', '2015-01-28 05:26:56', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=1243', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(1254, 1, '2013-11-05 06:00:13', '2013-11-05 06:00:13', '&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIf my 15 year old self knew that yesterday would come + I would be face painting queen-of-country, Martina McBride, I would have lost it! This one''s for the girls... She really is the ultimate babe. I had the most incredible day with Martina + team, she is classy + genuine + such a joy to work with. + Beautiful too, made it oh so easy for me! A few snaps from the day... <!--more--><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/martinamcbridebts3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1261" alt="martinamcbridebts3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/martinamcbridebts3.jpg" width="3928" height="1664" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/martinamcbridesarahappleby.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1255" alt="martinamcbridesarahappleby" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/martinamcbridesarahappleby.jpg" width="3968" height="2232" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/glyniscarpenter.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1257" alt="glyniscarpenter" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/glyniscarpenter.jpg" width="2208" height="1248" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/martinamcbridebts.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1260" alt="martinamcbridebts" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/martinamcbridebts.jpg" width="2208" height="1248" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/martinamcbride2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1259" alt="martinamcbride2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/martinamcbride2.jpg" width="2208" height="1248" /></a><em></em><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1256" alt="glamteammartinamcbride" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/glamteammartinamcbride.jpg" width="1280" height="725" /><em>PHOTO: Glynis Carpenter | HAIR: Christopher Naselli {above!} | MAKEUP: Moi</em><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/martinamcbridesarahapplebybts.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1262" alt="martinamcbridesarahapplebybts" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/martinamcbridesarahapplebybts.jpg" width="2048" height="1215" /></a>Such a fun team, I can''t wait to see the final images! + To end with a view like this, Brooklyn in best. X', 'BEHIND THE SCENES/ martina mcbride', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'behind-the-scenes-martina-mcbride', '', '', '2015-01-28 05:27:08', '2015-01-28 05:27:08', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=1254', 0, 'post', '', 1),
