(1293, 1, '2013-11-19 12:43:40', '2013-11-19 12:43:40', 'While in France last week I managed to find myself some new beautiful things. I used to travel + buy up the town + then face the last minute challenge of how to get it all home. Well, as time has gone by, trips become more of an experience rather than a treasure hunt, an accumulation. I find myself being much more selective with my purchases, making each one more special. Being that France is an easy place to find pretty things, I worked hard at finding the most perfect takeaways. Here are my favorite five must haves from this last trip...<!--more-->You can''t go to Paris without a stop at <a href="http://www.lebonmarche.com/" target="_blank">Le Bon Marche</a> in the 7th. The dreamy department store is filled with finely curated designer musthaves. I promised myself only one treat whilst in there, + yes, <em>Celine</em> found me. I have been eyeing these sunnies for sometime + finally scooped them up! What better place to buy Celine than in PariPari, right?<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1294" alt="celinesunglassesfrance" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/celinesunglassesfrance.jpg" width="2208" height="1248" />Then onto <a href="http://www.yelp.fr/biz/city-pharma-paris" target="_blank"><em>City-Pharma</em></a>, the pharmacie/drugstore that every beauty queen raves about. The drugstore that every product junkie loves to hate. It''s always busy, people are always pushy, but you will get the best prices on all the french beauty brands! Here are a few products that jumped into my bag:\r\n\r\nâ€¢<em>bioderma</em> | jumbo bottle | good for all skin types | toning + cleansing\r\n\r\nâ€¢<em>caudalie tinted moisturizer</em> | new product | light coverage + high in moisture\r\n\r\nâ€¢<em>dexeryl moisturizer</em> | jumbo bottle | best for dry winters | not greasy + unscented\r\n\r\nâ€¢<em>nuxe oil</em> | the unofficial scent of every pharmacie in france | moisturizing + floral fragrance<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/favoritebeautyproductsfrance1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1300" alt="favoritebeautyproductsfrance" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/favoritebeautyproductsfrance1.jpg" width="2208" height="1248" /></a>\r\n\r\nAlix Petit is a brilliant french designer + I am lucky enough to have her as a friend. She owns + designs womenswear {+ menswear as of this season!} for <em><a href="http://www.heimstone.com/fr/page/accueil.html" target="_blank">HEIMSTONE</a>, </em>with two locations: Cambon + Cherche midi. The collections are full of color + texture, + unique prints which she designs as well. I saw this suede jacket with the leopard printed collar + sleeves + knew I had to have it. Every gal needs a signature Heimstone piece {did I mention they sell online too?}!\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/heimstoneleopardjacketfrance.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1296" alt="heimstoneleopardjacketfrance" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/heimstoneleopardjacketfrance.jpg" width="2208" height="1248" /></a>Being a lover of tea, I was shocked when I discovered there was a flavor, that wasn''t ''new'', I hadn''t experienced. It was <em>Mariage Freres''</em> Â <a href="http://www.mariagefreres.com/boutique/UK/ft+lapsang-souchong-imperial-classical-black-tin-100g+TC210.html" target="_blank">Lapsang Souchong Imperial</a>. It is a smoky black chinese tea, that tastes like a campfire, an old scotch. Like my childhood. It''s so good! Many spots to buy the French tea favorite, I picked mine up at the Galeries Lafayette in the 1st, they have a cute little Tea Salon in the middle of the store. I also picked up the newest Earl Grey D''or as well as Paris Singapour. Not only am I obsessed with the tea, I love the presentation, packaging, wrapping + how much the company focuses on the history + origin of tea.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/mariagesfreres.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1297" alt="mariagesfreres" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/mariagesfreres.jpg" width="2208" height="1248" /></a>+ On Sunday, with friends, we wandered<a href="http://www.parisdigest.com/shopping/puces.htm" target="_blank"><em> Les Puces</em></a>, the flea market. I was after some old books, for creative purposes + stumbled across these old magazines dating back to 1935! I picked them up so I can use the pages to wrap all of my Christmas gifts this year. I love a beautifully wrapped gift + who doesn''t love some french history!\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/vintagemagazinesfrance.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1298" alt="vintagemagazinesfrance" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/vintagemagazinesfrance.jpg" width="2208" height="1248" /></a>Every time I leave France, I leave a little more of my heart there. I am supposed to live there at some point in life, I know that much... Someday! Until then will keep hopping across the pond to get my French fix! X', 'Favorite Five/ from france with love', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'favorite-five-from-france-with-love', '', '', '2015-01-28 05:19:20', '2015-01-28 05:19:20', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=1293', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(1310, 1, '2013-11-25 15:08:48', '2013-11-25 15:08:48', 'https://vimeo.com/80269349\r\n\r\nI recently shot an editorial for <em></em> magazine + Skingraft. We shot it at the park on Elizabeth, which is one of my favorites. Above is the video, shot + edited by Rob Grieb. + Then the editorial! Here are a few of my favorite images from the day...<!--more--><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/IMG_9518-Edit.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1314" alt="IMG_9518-Edit" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/IMG_9518-Edit.jpg" width="4752" height="3168" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/IMG_9529-Edit.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1315" alt="IMG_9529-Edit" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/IMG_9529-Edit.jpg" width="4752" height="3168" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/IMG_9411-Edit.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1311" alt="IMG_9411-Edit" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/IMG_9411-Edit.jpg" width="4752" height="3168" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/IMG_9662-Edit-Edit.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1319" alt="IMG_9662-Edit-Edit" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/IMG_9662-Edit-Edit.jpg" width="3168" height="4752" /></a><em>PHOTO</em>: molly goldrick | <em>STYLING</em>: kyle simone | <em>HMU:</em> moi | <em>MODELS:</em> miles charley watson + hildie\r\n\r\nFor the rest of the story chcek out <a href="http://relapsemag.com/blog/2013/11/20/an-exclusive-look-at-skingraft-autumnwinter-2013-with-video" target="_blank">Relapse Magazine</a>! X\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'NEW WORK/ relapseXskingraft', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'new-work-relapsexskingraft', '', '', '2015-01-28 05:08:16', '2015-01-28 05:08:16', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=1310', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1327, 1, '2013-12-04 16:44:20', '2013-12-04 16:44:20', 'It is that time of year again! Here in NYC, as the days are getting shorter + shorter + Winter, our skin is becoming dryer + duller. As with my ongoing obsession with keeping seasonal, I switch around my skincare routine, adding more layers to ensure my skin doesn''t get thirsty! Here are my favorite makeup products at the moment to ensure your skin never dulls...<!--more--><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/winterskinmacdermablendchanelmakeup.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1330" alt="winterskinmacdermablendchanelmakeup" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/winterskinmacdermablendchanelmakeup.jpg" width="3776" height="2520" /></a>After getting your skin all cleansed + toned + moisturized, start with a base foundation. I keep two options at the moment, one for day + one for nite.\r\n\r\n<em>DAY/ <a href="http://www.maccosmetics.com/product/shaded/11633/393/New-Collections/MAC-Rick-Baker/Multi-Use/Face-And-Body-Foundation-120-ML/index.tmpl" target="_blank">MAC face + body foundation</a>, super lightweight + dewy finish</em>\r\n\r\n<em>NITE/ <a href="http://www.chanel.com/en_US/fragrance-beauty/Makeup-Foundation-PERFECTION-LUMI%C3%88RE-123093" target="_blank">CHANEL perfection lumiere</a>, full coverage + matte finish</em>\r\n\r\nWhen applying, use your fingers; it is the most versatile tool you have. Not only will the warmth from your fingers bring the makeup to life, but it gives you more control with where the product is placed.\r\n\r\nChoose your foundation then mix 2 drops of <a href="http://www.maccosmetics.com/product/shaded/793/4440/Lustre-Drops/index.tmpl" target="_blank"><em>MAC lustre drops in sun rush</em>.</a> If lustre drops are used on it''s own, you will get much more of a shimmer where as I prefer it in the foundation where it reads as more of a glow.\r\n\r\nThen I apply some <a href="www.dermablend.com/concealers/concealer-severe-flaws/quickfix.htm" target="_blank"><em>DERMABLEND quick fix concealer</em></a> around my eyes, mouth + nose, wherever there is spot pigmentation or redness.\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/winterskinpapawcobigelow.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1331" alt="winterskinpapawcobigelow" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/winterskinpapawcobigelow.jpg" width="3776" height="2520" /></a>Then to add a pop of sheenÂ  + contour to the skin, I love using <a href="http://lucaspapaw.com.au/" target="_blank"><em>Lucas'' Papaw Ointment</em> </a>to my eyelids + the top of my cheekbones. It adds a glisten that makes your skin look mega hydrated. + Finally, some <a href="http://www.bigelowchemists.com/c-o-bigelow-cinnamint-supreme-2x-lip-shine-no-504.html" target="_blank"><em>C.O. Bigelow Lip Shine in cinnamint supreme</em></a> on my lips for gloss. I love the flavor + texture.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/winterskin1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1328" alt="winterskin1" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/winterskin1.jpg" width="3411" height="2274" /></a>Clean, hydrated skin goes a long way this time of year! What are your favorite winter makeup products for skin? X\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'HOW TO/ glowy winter skin', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'how-to-glowy-winter-skin', '', '', '2015-01-28 05:00:16', '2015-01-28 05:00:16', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=1327', 0, 'post', '', 2),
(1337, 1, '2013-12-09 16:10:46', '2013-12-09 16:10:46', 'Aah, I love discovering new favorite places + spaces. Last week I spent the day at dia: BEACON. It is officially my new favorite gallery. I want every piece in there! The gallery spans over 300,000 sq ft in Beacon, New York. It is a former Nabisco box printing factory, white rafters, big windows + large rooms to view some of the most beautiful collections of art. Here are some of my favorites from the day, starring Richard Serra {a give in}, Robert Ryman {newly obsessed- with all of that white how could I not be!}, Andy Warhol {''shadows'' being my favorite work of his}, Dan Flavin {white florescents make art} + Sol LeWitt {I am not plotting how I will cover my walls with pencils!}...<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/diabeacongallery.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1341" alt="diabeacongallery" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/diabeacongallery.jpg" width="2784" height="1568" /></a>Richard Serra/<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/diabeaconrichardserra.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1342" alt="diabeaconrichardserra" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/diabeaconrichardserra.jpg" width="2208" height="1248" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/diabeacon.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1338" alt="diabeacon" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/diabeacon.jpg" width="2208" height="1248" /></a>Robert Ryman/ <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/diabeaconrobertryman.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1343" alt="diabeaconrobertryman" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/diabeaconrobertryman.jpg" width="2208" height="1248" /></a>Andy Warhol/<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/dianeaconandywarhol.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1347" alt="dianeaconandywarhol" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/dianeaconandywarhol.jpg" width="2208" height="1248" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/diabeaconandywarhol2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1339" alt="diabeaconandywarhol2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/diabeaconandywarhol2.jpg" width="2208" height="1248" /></a>Dan Flavin/<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/diabeacondanflavinsarahappleby.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1340" alt="diabeacondanflavinsarahappleby" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/diabeacondanflavinsarahappleby.jpg" width="2208" height="1248" /></a>Sol Lewitt/<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/sollewittdiabeacon.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1349" alt="sollewittdiabeacon" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/sollewittdiabeacon.jpg" width="2208" height="1248" /></a>\r\n\r\nI am looking forward to my next visit, seeing other artists they bring in. It was enlightening + introspective showcasing a range of contemporary art. What are some of your favorite galleries? X', 'NEW FAVORITE: dia/ BEACON', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'new-favorite-dia-beacon', '', '', '2015-01-28 04:58:52', '2015-01-28 04:58:52', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=1337', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1352, 1, '2013-12-12 12:33:48', '2013-12-12 12:33:48', '&nbsp;\r\n\r\nHere is a new editorial that I worked on with photographer <em>Jake Chessum</em> for <a href="http://www.outsideonline.com/" target="_blank">OUTSIDE </a>magazine. We ran around NYC meeting up with notable gents that have a love for the great outdoors. From designer <em>Ikene Ijeome</em>, to Restauranteur <em>Michael Chernow</em> {<a href="http://www.themeatballshop.com/" target="_blank">The Meatball Shop</a>}, Wine buyer <em>Rob Fritz</em> {<a href="http://www.chelseawinevault.com/" target="_blank">Chelsea Wine Vault</a>} to Gardener <em>Matt Jefferson</em> {<a href="www.brooklyngrangefarm.com" target="_blank">Brooklyn Grange</a>} + more, all are very intentional about their outdoor hobbies. + They clean up well, if I do say so myself...<!--more--><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/SAP_Outside_092013-3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1355" alt="SAP_Outside_092013 -3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/SAP_Outside_092013-3.jpg" width="879" height="1200" /></a>Â  <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/SAP_Outside_092013-4.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1356" alt="SAP_Outside_092013 -4" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/SAP_Outside_092013-4.jpg" width="879" height="1200" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/SAP_Outside_092013-5.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1357" alt="SAP_Outside_092013 -5" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/SAP_Outside_092013-5.jpg" width="879" height="1200" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/SAP_Outside_092013-1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1353" alt="SAP_Outside_092013 -1" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/SAP_Outside_092013-1.jpg" width="879" height="1200" /></a> <a href="http://sa