log/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/timexsarahapplebywearetherhoads4.jpg" width="1800" height="1200" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/timexsarahapplebywearetherhoads5.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1415" alt="We Are The RhoadsClient: Timex" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/timexsarahapplebywearetherhoads5.jpg" width="1800" height="1200" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/timexsarahapplebywearetherhoads6.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1416" alt="We Are The RhoadsClient: Timex" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/timexsarahapplebywearetherhoads6.jpg" width="1800" height="1200" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/timexsarahapplebywearetherhoads3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1413" alt="We Are The RhoadsClient: Timex" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/timexsarahapplebywearetherhoads3.jpg" width="1800" height="1200" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/timexsarahapplebywearetherhoads.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1411" alt="We Are The RhoadsClient: Timex" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/timexsarahapplebywearetherhoads.jpg" width="1800" height="1200" /></a>It is always easy working with people you adore! Such a fun crew. Shout out to Kelsey Morgan {+ her magic fingers}, who helped me out with H+MU on the job... X', 'NEW WORK/ ad campaign for Timex', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'new-work-ad-campaign-for-timex', '', '', '2015-01-28 04:57:12', '2015-01-28 04:57:12', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=1410', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1429, 1, '2014-01-13 17:14:04', '2014-01-13 17:14:04', 'Here we are: AWARDS SEASON! That means it''s time for a lot of glam {good + bad!} coming down the red carpet. Last nite at the Golden Globes, we saw a lot of the latter. In keeping with my positive approach to this new year, here are my favorite/BEST five makeups + hairstyles from last nite...<!--more--> We saw a lot of messy updos + bad lashes {really?}, but alas here are my golden gals: <strong><em>1/Jennifer Lawrence.</em></strong> Girl has got it together. Her effortless short coiff complements her classic makeup. Her subtle platinum smoked out eyes with feathery lashes + rusty red lip was classic + flawless. Now about her dress....<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/jenniferlawrencegoldenglobes2014.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1430" alt="jenniferlawrencegoldenglobes2014" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/jenniferlawrencegoldenglobes2014.png" width="581" height="662" /></a><em><strong>2/Sofia Vergara.</strong></em> I love the way Sofia kept her look classic, yet casual. Her hair + makeup went well with her bold structured black dress. Her brows are my favorite, brushed up + natural looking which works with her textured lashes. A pretty winter rosy lip is the perfect choice for her skin tone. Her hair was down + loose + elegantly effortless.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/sofiavergaragoldenglobes2014.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1431" alt="sofiavergaragoldenglobes2014" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/sofiavergaragoldenglobes2014.png" width="588" height="627" /></a><em><strong>3/Kerry Washington.</strong></em> Here is a perfectly executed smoky eye. It is dramatic without being overload. I love that the sparkle + shimmer is kept to a minimum, slight contour on the cheeks with a natural lip. Again, the loose + flowy hair- absolutely radiant.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/kerrywashingtongoldenglobes2014.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1432" alt="kerrywashingtongoldenglobes2014" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/kerrywashingtongoldenglobes2014.png" width="588" height="658" /></a><em><strong>4/Olivia Wilde.</strong></em> She couldn''t be more of a babe! Love the intense plum smoky eye, diffused with a rosy shadow. Her skin was flawless + glowy, with a nude lip. Her hair color was a standout the way it was styled with the loose tousled waves.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/oliviawildegoldenglobes20141.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1435" alt="oliviawildegoldenglobes2014" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/oliviawildegoldenglobes20141.png" width="566" height="667" /></a><em><strong>5/Paula Patton</strong></em>. Love this makeup, subtle eye with a slight highlight + with the focus on gorgeous pink cheeks + lips. Her skin looks like butter. The classic slicked hair with side part is striking.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/paulapattongoldenglobes2014.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1434" alt="paulapattongoldenglobes2014" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/paulapattongoldenglobes2014.png" width="590" height="617" /></a>There you have it. I think this was just a taste of what is to come on March 2, for the glam portion of the 86th Annual Academy Awards. I hope to see a lot more of the above, hopefully others will take notes + follow suit. I don''t want to see anymore messy/curly updos or low messy buns, bad fake lashes or overly done sparkles + shimmer. It is done. Happy Monday! X', 'REVIEW/ my favorite glam at the Golden Globes 2014', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'review-my-favorite-glam-at-the-golden-globes-2014', '', '', '2015-01-27 12:14:46', '2015-01-27 12:14:46', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=1429', 0, 'post', '', 0);
