(1441, 1, '2014-01-16 15:30:31', '2014-01-16 15:30:31', '&nbsp;\r\n\r\nYesterday I had the pleasure of painting the faces of Amy Heidemann + Nick Noonan of the pop duo: <a href="http://www.karminmusic.com/us/biography" target="_blank"><em>KARMIN,</em></a> for the March Issue of <em><a href="http://flattmag.com/" target="_blank">FLATT magazine</a></em>. It was shot by the amazing, <a href="http://kelseybennett.com/#img_72610028-copy" target="_blank"><em>Kelsey Bennett</em> </a>+ styled by Fashion Director, <em><a href="https://twitter.com/Ashley_Pruitt" target="_blank">Ashley Priutt</a>.</em> Here are some snaps from the day...<!--more--> <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1447" alt="karminsarahappleby5" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/karminsarahappleby5.jpg" width="3264" height="2448" />Amy is known for her retro glam style, lots of winged liner, big bold lips + rockabilly rolls in the hair. We went for a little something different yesterday. Her bone structure lends to natural makeup- she is beautiful. I chose a creamy, subtle contoured lid with really textured but still natural feeling, feathery lashes. Then a full structured brow to frame it all. We did a diffused/smudgy red lip, keeping the saturation in the center + diffusing out {how to blog coming next week!}. Skin prep using <em><a href="http://www.murad.com/?XID=A10109&amp;affilnet=cj" target="_blank">Murad</a></em> + color <a href="http://www.clinique.com/cms/product/supercat/makeup.tmpl" target="_blank"><em>Clinique</em></a>. Damien Monzillo did the hair, seventies inspired sexy, tousled tresses..<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1442" alt="karminsarahappleby" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/karminsarahappleby.jpg" width="2616" height="1742" /><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1446" alt="karminsarahappleby4" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/karminsarahappleby4.jpg" width="3264" height="2448" /> We were shooting in this incredible townhouse in the west village, this was the wallpaper in the bathroom- it was foiled!<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1448" alt="karminsarahappleby6" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/karminsarahappleby6.jpg" width="2448" height="1836" /> <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1444" alt="karminsarahappleby2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/karminsarahappleby2.jpg" width="3264" height="2448" /> <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1443" alt="karminsarahappleby1" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/karminsarahappleby1.jpg" width="2448" height="1836" /> It is always fun working with musicians, Amy + Nick are such gems, I can''t wait to see what happens when they debut their first album in a few months! + Will be posting final layout of the shoot when it gets to print... X', 'BEHIND THE SCENES/ FLATT magazine shoot with band duo KARMIN', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'behind-the-scenes-flatt-magazine-shoot-with-band-duo-karmin', '', '', '2015-01-27 12:10:09', '2015-01-27 12:10:09', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=1441', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1453, 1, '2014-01-21 17:18:09', '2014-01-21 17:18:09', '&nbsp;\r\n\r\nI amÂ  l o v i n gÂ  the new spring/summer campaigns. The makeup is fresh + natural, + the skin is transparent. Here are my top picks at the moment...<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<strong><em>MAX MARA S/S 2014</em></strong> with Hana Jirickova/Natalia Siodmiak/Stef Van Der Laan, shot by Mario Sorrenti. The slight creamy contour on the eye, minimal {if any} lash + brow with a subtle lipstain. Makeup Artist: Aaron DeMay.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/maxmaraspring2014sarahappleby5.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1467" alt="maxmaraspring2014sarahappleby5" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/maxmaraspring2014sarahappleby5.jpg" width="722" height="960" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/maxmaraspring2014sarahappleby.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1463" alt="maxmaraspring2014sarahappleby" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/maxmaraspring2014sarahappleby.jpg" width="736" height="960" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/maxmaraspring2014sarahappleby2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1464" alt="maxmaraspring2014sarahappleby2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/maxmaraspring2014sarahappleby2.jpg" width="753" height="960" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/maxmaraspring2014sarahappleby3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1465" alt="maxmaraspring2014sarahappleby3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/maxmaraspring2014sarahappleby3.jpg" width="752" height="960" /></a>\r\n\r\n<strong><em>CARVEN S/S 2014 </em></strong>with Marte Mei van Haaster shot by: Viviane Sassen. Whomever did this this makeup is spot on. The glowy cheeks with matte nude lips. It is divine. <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/carvenss2014sarahappleby2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1455" alt="carvenss2014sarahappleby2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/carvenss2014sarahappleby2.jpg" width="721" height="940" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/carvenss2014sarahappleby3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1456" alt="carvenss2014sarahappleby3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/carvenss2014sarahappleby3.jpg" width="652" height="850" /></a> <em><strong>COACH S/S 2014</strong></em> with Freja Beha Erichson shot by: Craig McDean. Talk about a natural beauty. Love Freja, the makeup is invisible, just corrective. This is the East coast standard for beauty.<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1457" alt="coachfrejasarahappleby" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/coachfrejasarahappleby.jpg" width="800" height="529" /> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/coachsarahappleby2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1458" alt="coachsarahappleby2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/coachsarahappleby2.jpg" width="800" height="800" /></a> <strong><em>DIOR mag F/W 2013</em></strong> with Jennifer Lawrence shot by: Mikael Jansson. Well, this one is a little cheeky, I know I am late but this is exceptional. What a gorgeous take from the classic brand. I WISH they had made this campaign. Skin is stunning, flawless, buttery etc. Can we have this J-Law everyday please!<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1459" alt="diormagfw2013sarahappleby" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/diormagfw2013sarahappleby.jpg" width="770" height="936" /> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/diormagfw2013sarahappleby2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1460" alt="diormagfw2013sarahappleby2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/diormagfw2013sarahappleby2.jpg" width="800" height="774" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/diormagfw2013sarahappleby3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1461" alt="diormagfw2013sarahappleby3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/diormagfw2013sarahappleby3.jpg" width="770" height="936" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/diormagfw2013sarahappleby4.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1462" alt="diormagfw2013sarahappleby4" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/diormagfw2013sarahappleby4.jpg" width="800" height="534" /></a><em><strong>MULBERRY S/S 2014</strong></em> with Cara Delavigne shot by: Tim Walker. + One more fresh face, subtle contour of the eye + perfect pout. Would have loved to see a little more sheen on the skin, but this beauty is so good when she is natural! Stunning.<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1468" alt="mulberryss2014sarahappleby" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/mulberryss2014sarahappleby.jpg" width="683" height="1024" /> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/mulberryss2014sarahappleby2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1469" alt="mulberryss2014sarahappleby2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/mulberryss2014sarahappleby2.jpg" width="800" height="533" /></a> <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1470" alt="mulberryss2014sarahappleby3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/mulberryss2014sarahappleby3.jpg" width="683" height="1024" />I always know when we are at the beginning of the end of winter, as I am getting antsy for dewy skin with sheen + shimmer. I will however, abide by my own obsession + ruling of keeping seasonal skin + makeup! In the meantime, these gorgeous makeups + images will be posted all over my office to keep me happy... X', 'Favorite Five/ fresh faced campaigns', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'favorite-five-fresh-faced-campaigns', '', '', '2015-01-27 12:14:28', '2015-01-27 12:14:28', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=1453', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1477, 1, '2014-01-23 17:38:17', '2014-01-23 17:38:17', '&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWe all love the classic, structured, perfected, bold lip. But, to make it fresh + current, I love doing a diffused, smudgy lip. Here''s how with two of my favorite lipsticks... <!--more--><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1478" alt="CHANEL_LIP_MAC_SARAH_APPLEBY_PRODUCT" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/CHANEL_LIP_MAC_SARAH_APPLEBY_PRODUCT.jpg" width="2208" height="1248" />1/ Use a dry toothbrush {i personally love the cheap travel ones with stiffer bristles for this} + go over your dry lips with it gently. This will exfoliate your lips + get them all ready for moisture. Using a tiny amount of <a href="http://www.amazon.com/NUXE-Reve-Miel-Honey-Balm/dp/B000EVD8FY" target="_blank"><em><strong>Reve De Miel</strong></em></a>, press into your lips. I love this lip balm {from France} because it is not shiny or sticky + extremely moisturizing. Great as a base.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/REVE_DE_MIEL_SARAH_APPLEBY.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1485" alt="REVE_DE_MIEL_SARAH_APPLEBY" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/REVE_DE_MIEL_SARAH_APPLEBY.jpg" width="2208" height="966" /></a>\r\n\r\n3/ <a href="http://www.chanel.com/en_US/fragrance-beauty/Makeup-Lipstick-ROUGE-ALLURE-VELVET-122517" target="_blank"><em><strong>Chanel Rouge Allure Velvet in LA PRECIEUSEâ€¢317</strong></em></a> is the perfect red. Dab the stick all over your lips then press your lips together getting all edges {here is where are are not worried about the color bleeding over a little!}. The red will come off pink until you give it more saturation. Then using your finger blend + feather out the edges to diffuse the color.<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1482" alt="chanel_rouge_allure_velvet_sarah_appleby4" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/chanel_rouge_allure_velvet_sarah_appleby4.jpg" width="2208" height="984" />4/ Using the stick press color into the inner part of your lips, the lips need to be most saturated with color in the center + then diffuse toward the edges.<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1481" alt="chanel_rouge_allure_velvet_sarah_appleby3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/chanel_rouge_allure_velvet_sarah_appleby3.jpg" width="2208" height="1248" /><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/chanel_rouge_allure_velvet_sarah_appleby2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1480" alt="chanel_rouge_allure_velvet_sarah_appleby2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/chanel_rouge_allure_velvet_sarah_appleby2.jpg" width="2208" height="1248" /></a>Here it is again using <a href="http://www.maccosmetics.com/product/shaded/168/310/Lipstick/index.tmpl" target="_blank"><em><strong>MAC Cosmetics Amplified Creme Lipstick in UP THE AMP.</strong> </em></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/MAC_AMPLIFIED_CREME_UP_THE_AMP_SARAH_APPLEBY.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1484" alt="MAC_AMPLIFIED_CREME_UP_THE_AMP_SARAH_APPLEBY" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/MAC_AMPLIFIED_CREME_UP_THE_AMP_SARAH_APPLEBY.jpg" width="2079" height="1128" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/MAC_AMPLIFIED_CREME_UP_THE_AMP_SARAH_APPLEBY_2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1483" alt="MAC_AMPLIFIED_CREME_UP_THE_AMP_SARAH_APPLEBY_2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/MAC_AMPLIFIED_CREME_UP_THE_AMP_SARAH_APPLEBY_2.jpg" width="2208" height="1248" /></a>VOILA! A sexy + fun new take on the bold lip. Matte + Satin finishes will be best for this, as you want pigmented lipsticks to work with {not lustre/sheer etc}. Happy blurring! X', 'HOW TO/ blurred lips', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'how-to-blurred-lips', '', '', '2015-01-27 11:51:02', '2015-01-27 11:51:02', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=1477', 0, 'post', '', 2),
(1490, 1, '2014-01-30 22:06:17', '2014-01-30 22:06:17', 'https://vimeo.com/85478070\r\n\r\nI love getting to work with brilliant musicians. Yesterday I had the opportunity to work with British singer, James Blunt. He is just as funny as he is talented, + that is amazing! Along with his performance on LIVE with Kelly + Michael, here are my favorite men''s grooming products from Oribe to get his look...<!--more--><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/JAMES_BLUNT_ORIBE_SARAH_APPLEBY21.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1494" alt="JAMES_BLUNT_ORIBE_SARAH_APPLEBY2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/JAMES_BLUNT_ORIBE_SARAH_APPLEBY21.png" width="709" height="482" /></a>Firstly I sprayed James'' hair with <a href="http://www.oribe.com/index.php/products/view/50/foundation-mist/" target="_blank">Oribe Foundation Mist</a>, + blew it dry, this creates a great foundation to work off of. As we were doing a very natural style, I then used <a href="http://www.oribe.com/index.php/products/view/26/dry-texturizing-spray/related:70" target="_blank">Oribe Dry Texturizing Spray</a> to give the hair a bit of grit + texture. + Finally I used a modest amount of <a href="http://www.oribe.com/index.php/products/view/1783/fiber-groom/" target="_blank">Oribe Fibre Groom</a> just on the ends of his hair to bring it all together.\r\n\r\nYou are beautiful! X', 'NEW WORK/ James Blunt press day', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'new-work-james-blunt-press-day', '', '', '2015-01-27 11:48:42', '2015-01-27 11:48:42', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=1490', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1503, 1, '2014-02-10 17:30:36', '2014-02-10 17:30:36', 'Most of us gals have three or four makeup looks we rotate between. Our defaults if you will. Here is a go to for me, clean skin, nude lips, subtle brow + of course the classic black winged liner. Here''s what you need to know to get the look...<!--more--><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1513" alt="MAKEUPFOREVER_CLINIQUE_BLACKLINER" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/MAKEUPFOREVER_CLINIQUE_BLACKLINER.jpg" width="2031" height="951" />YOU NEED:\r\n\r\nâ€¢<a href="http://www.makeupforever.com/us/en-us/make-up/eyes/eye-shadow/aqua-black" target="_blank">MAKE UP FOR EVER Aqua Black</a>\r\n\r\nâ€¢<a href="http://www.clinique.com/product/1595/8417/Makeup/Brows/Instant-Lift-For-Brows/index.tmpl" target="_blank">CLINIQUEÂ  instant lift for brows </a>\r\n\r\nâ€¢<a href="http://www.makeupforever.com/us/en-us/make-up/brushes/eye-brush/angled-eyeliner-brush-262" target="_blank">MAKE UP FOR EVER #262 brush</a>\r\n\r\nâ€¢<a href="http://www.makeupforever.com/us/en-us/make-up/brushes/eye-brush/fine-eyeliner-brush-252" target="_blank">MAKE UP FOR EVER #252 brush </a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/MAKEUPFOREVER_CLINIQUE_BLACKLINER_2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1504" alt="MAKEUPFOREVER_CLINIQUE_BLACKLINER_2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/MAKEUPFOREVER_CLINIQUE_BLACKLINER_2.jpg" width="1998" height="948" /></a>Start by filling in your brows, using a cream stick will give you a more subtle, diffused finish- you want that! This look is not about the brow. Soft Honey is the shade I used, it is slightly lighter than my natural color.<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1505" alt="MAKEUPFOREVER_CLINIQUE_BLACKLINER_3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/MAKEUPFOREVER_CLINIQUE_BLACKLINER_3.jpg" width="2037" height="993" />I love the highlighter at the other end of the pencil, it''s a pretty sheen to add light to your browbone, blend with your finger if you need.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/MAKEUPFOREVER_CLINIQUE_BLACKLINER_4.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1506" alt="MAKEUPFOREVER_CLINIQUE_BLACKLINER_4" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/MAKEUPFOREVER_CLINIQUE_BLACKLINER_4.jpg" width="2208" height="1248" /></a>Using the big angle brush, dip just the ends into the pot, you need the slightest amount to start. <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/MAKEUPFOREVER_CLINIQUE_BLACKLINER_5.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1507" alt="MAKEUPFOREVER_CLINIQUE_BLACKLINER_5" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/MAKEUPFOREVER_CLINIQUE_BLACKLINER_5.jpg" width="2208" height="1248" /></a>As in the photo above, you start by creating a line out of your eye {essentially you are building the top line of your wing}. Then you are going to make a triangle shape to join line to the corner of your eye. + Then with a steady hand, place the angle brush to lay into the rest of your eye, towards the inner corner.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/MAKEUPFOREVER_CLINIQUE_BLACKLINER_6.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1508" alt="MAKEUPFOREVER_CLINIQUE_BLACKLINER_6" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/MAKEUPFOREVER_CLINIQUE_BLACKLINER_6.jpg" width="2208" height="1248" /></a>Using the smaller brush, you''ll now fix up edges. This brush makes it so easy to get exactly your desired shape. *Take your time, it may not be perfect the first go around, you can use a wet q-tip to erase any unwanted liner to redo. The liner should start thin in the inner corner + move to a thicker line.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/MAKEUPFOREVER_CLINIQUE_BLACKLINER_7.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1509" alt="MAKEUPFOREVER_CLINIQUE_BLACKLINER_7" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/MAKEUPFOREVER_CLINIQUE_BLACKLINER_7.jpg" width="2162" height="1004" /></a>Once you have your desired shape, to make the blackest black liner, you can use the large angle brush to go over your liner. Be sure to get in the lash line as well, pushing into your lashes so your skin doesn''t show through.\r\n\r\nAdd loads of mascara, several coats to give texture. Don''t worry if your eyes are not completely even! Our eyes aren''t even + the mascara will help with that. I love one layer on the bottom lashes, just for definition.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/MAKEUPFOREVER_CLINIQUE_BLACKLINER_9.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1511" alt="MAKEUPFOREVER_CLINIQUE_BLACKLINER_9" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/MAKEUPFOREVER_CLINIQUE_BLACKLINER_9.jpg" width="1455" height="621" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/MAKEUPFOREVER_CLINIQUE_BLACKLINER_8.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1510" alt="MAKEUPFOREVER_CLINIQUE_BLACKLINER_8" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/MAKEUPFOREVER_CLINIQUE_BLACKLINER_8.jpg" width="2208" height="1248" /></a>VOILA! Your newÂ  classic lined eye. This is a fun day time look, easily into evening by adding a little more liner, or a fun lip. X\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'HOW TO/ the quick cat eye', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'how-to-the-quick-cat-eye', '', '', '2015-01-27 11:49:32', '2015-01-27 11:49:32', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=1503', 0, 'post', '', 2),
(1521, 1, '2014-03-04 15:40:18', '2014-03-04 15:40:18', '<br /><br />It''s that time of year when we are all itching to get out of the snow, rain, + cold. I am lucky enough to be soaking up the sun in the Dominican Republic for a little winter break. To have the sun on my back + running around barefoot is the dream, but the harsh rays are no joke on my fair winter skin. Here are my go to products for keeping my skin  + hair it''s best during my winter beach getaway...\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<br /><br /><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/20140304-113030.jpg"><img src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/20140304-113030.jpg" alt="20140304-113030.jpg" class="alignnone size-full" /></a>\r\n\r\nBefore heading out for the day at the beach this is what I do:\r\n<em>INFUSIUM 23/</em> here is an old school favorite of mine. I spray this all over my hair before getting in to the sun. It is a leave in conditioner that protects the color from the sun + salt. \r\n<em>LE TAN/ </em>my all time favorite sunscreens. australian made, I use the spf30 coconut lotion all over my face + body for the first few days until I have built up a base moving to the spf15 coconut oil. after every beach day, I use a generous amount of after sun mist spray all over my face + body. \r\n<em>CAUDALIE/ </em>every morning I put this on my face first, vinexpert broad spectrum radiance fluid with spf15. \r\n<em>LABELLO/ </em>a must for the day, spf30 for the lips. the best part about having a little zinc in all of the SPF products is the nude, white tint it goes making your face + lips a little glowy!<br /><br /><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/20140304-113046.jpg"><img src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/20140304-113046.jpg" alt="20140304-113046.jpg" class="alignnone size-full" /></a>\r\n\r\nThen a cute pair of sunnies, a quick braid or two(!), floppy beach hat, a Turkish towel + you are more than prepared to take on the rays of the day! Proper SPF is so important, + as much as we all love to look a little tan, start slowly- your hair + skin will thank you. Happy beauty beaching. X\r\n\r\n<br /><br /><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/20140304-113038.jpg"><img src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/20140304-113038.jpg" alt="20140304-113038.jpg" class="alignnone size-full" /></a>', 'HOW TO/ winter beach beauty', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'how-to-winter-beach-beauty', '', '', '2015-01-27 11:46:08', '2015-01-27 11:46:08', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=1521', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(1525, 1, '2014-03-12 14:17:09', '2014-03-12 14:17:09', 'I love this editorial I did with Jasmine Tookes for Glass magazine. It is out now! I gave Jasmine pretty, dewy skin with contours + a peach lip.<!--more-->Shot by the amazing Walter Chin, styled by the beautiful Sarah Cobb, hair by Herve Bernard + makeup by moi. Such a fun day shooting collection in a beautiful brownstone in Gowanus.<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1527" alt="GLASS_MAGAZINE_EDITORIAL_2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/GLASS_MAGAZINE_EDITORIAL_2.png" width="940" height="661" /> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/GLASS_MAGAZINE_EDITORIAL_6.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1531" alt="GLASS_MAGAZINE_EDITORIAL_6" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/GLASS_MAGAZINE_EDITORIAL_6.png" width="944" height="665" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/GLASS_MAGAZINE_EDITORIAL_5.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1530" alt="GLASS_MAGAZINE_EDITORIAL_5" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/GLASS_MAGAZINE_EDITORIAL_5.png" width="945" height="663" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/GLASS_MAGAZINE_EDITORIAL_4.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1529" alt="GLASS_MAGAZINE_EDITORIAL_4" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/GLASS_MAGAZINE_EDITORIAL_4.png" width="943" height="667" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/GLASS_MAGAZINE_EDITORIAL_3.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1528" alt="GLASS_MAGAZINE_EDITORIAL_3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/GLASS_MAGAZINE_EDITORIAL_3.png" width="943" height="665" /></a>', 'NEW WORK/ editorial for GLASS magazine featuring jasmine tookes', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'new-work-editorial-for-glass-magazine-featuring-jasmine-tookes', '', '', '2015-01-27 11:45:14', '2015-01-27 11:45:14', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=1525', 0, 'post', '', 2),
(1536, 1, '2014-03-20 12:21:29', '2014-03-20 12:21:29', 'Shot by Cathrine Wessel, I did hair + makeup for her Fall collection of beautiful wool clothing, with&amp;wessel. It was such a fun day with beauty, Quinta! GET THE LOOK...<!--more-->\r\n\r\nWe chose to do a very natural, loose texture in the hair. I blew Quinta''s hair out with <a href="http://www.oribe.com/index.php/products/view/50/foundation-mist/" target="_blank">Oribe Foundation mist</a>, then wrapped 1 inch sections with a light spray of <a href="http://www.oribe.com/index.php/products/view/70/superfine-hair-spray/related:50" target="_blank">Oribe Super Fine Hair Spray</a> + letting set for 10 minutes. Then I fingercombed through the hair with a dime sized drop of <a href="http://www.oribe.com/index.php/products/view/48/creme-for-style/" target="_blank">Oribe Creme for Style</a>.\r\n\r\nFor makeup, the main focus was the skin + brows. For her skin, I used my fingers to apply <a href="http://www.sephora.com/photo-finish-foundation-primer-P9889?skuId=1349968" target="_blank">Smashbox Photo Finish Foundation Primer</a> around her t zone, nose + mouth, then with a flat foundation brush applied a conservative amount of <a href="http://www.sephora.com/liquid-halo-hd-foundation-spf-15-P380996?skuId=1526797" target="_blank">Liquid Halo HD Foundation</a> starting in the center of the face + using the brush to feather out product to the edges. A touch of <a href="http://www.sephora.com/halo-highlighting-wand-P292404?skuId=1349638" target="_blank">Smashbox Halo Highlighting Wand</a> around the top of the cheeks, nose + brow bone for a natural glowy effect. Then to finish, <a href="http://www.sephora.com/brow-tech-P260313?skuId=1241017" target="_blank">Smashbox Brow Tec</a>h on the brows to create a structured look, framing her face.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/WW_FW14_Lookbook_05.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1539" alt="W&amp;W_FW14_Lookbook_05" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/WW_FW14_Lookbook_05.jpg" width="800" height="1200" /><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1537" alt="W&amp;W_FW14_Lookbook_03" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/WW_FW14_Lookbook_03.jpg" width="800" height="1200" /></a>Â Â  <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/WW_FW14_Lookbook_06.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1540" alt="W&amp;W_FW14_Lookbook_06" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/WW_FW14_Lookbook_06.jpg" width="800" height="1200" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/WW_FW14_Lookbook_22.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1541" alt="W&amp;W_FW14_Lookbook_22" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/WW_FW14_Lookbook_22.jpg" width="800" height="1200" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/WW_FW14_Lookbook_33.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1542" alt="W&amp;W_FW14_Lookbook_33" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/WW_FW14_Lookbook_33.jpg" width="800" height="1200" /></a>', 'NEW WORK/ lookbook for with&wessel', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'new-work-lookbook-for-withwessel', '', '', '2015-01-27 11:35:29', '2015-01-27 11:35:29', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=1536', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1547, 1, '2014-03-24 16:35:07', '2014-03-24 16:35:07', 'Well, I love being on the beach. Especially amidst one of the longest winters in NYC! I had a big birthday last month + my Mother flew from Edmonton, Canada to treat me to the prettiest beach vacation {I KNOW!}. We did it all; climbed waterfalls, snorkeled, visited coffee + cocoa plantations, cliff jumped, rode horses, drank delicious cocktails out of coconuts, jumped in a blue lagoon, moto rides, explored caves, shared stories with locals, swam, boat rides, + more. Here are a few of my favorite snaps from the trip...<!--more--><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1548" alt="IMG_9532" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/IMG_9532.jpg" width="2448" height="1632" /> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/IMG_9551.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1549" alt="IMG_9551" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/IMG_9551.jpg" width="3240" height="2083" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/IMG_9582.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1550" alt="IMG_9582" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/IMG_9582.jpg" width="3234" height="1621" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/L1010806.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1551" alt="L1010806" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/L1010806.jpg" width="3697" height="2350" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/L1010807.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1552" alt="L1010807" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/L1010807.jpg" width="3485" height="2025" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/L1010832.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1556" alt="L1010832" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/L1010832.jpg" width="3662" he