(1870, 1, '2015-01-27 11:10:41', '2015-01-27 11:10:41', '<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/2015_EVENT_DR_MURAD_LONDON_HOTEL_POST_3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1840" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/2015_EVENT_DR_MURAD_LONDON_HOTEL_POST_3.jpg" alt="2015_EVENT_DR_MURAD_LONDON_HOTEL_POST_3" width="3776" height="2520" /></a>Last nite I had the opportunity to hear Skin + Dermatologist legend, <a href="http://www.murad.com/murad-insider" target="_blank">Dr. Howard Murad</a> speak over dinner at The London Hotel here in NYC. Going into the evening, I thought we were going to talk about skincare, new products + how to use them. I was pleasantly surprised to see that not only has he written a new book [<a href="http://www.murad.com/blog/stress-less-and-live-young-introducing-dr-murads-next-bestseller/" target="_blank">Conquering Cultural Stress: The Ultimate Guide to Anti-Aging and Happiness</a>], but he was wholeheartedly sharing all about it. He is the most genuine, lovely, gentleman. Such an honour to spend an evening with him + his team from California. A few thoughts + snaps from the nite...<!--more-->\n\nThe makeup look for the evening, a little cat eye + some contoured skin.Dr. Murad has 365 mantras in the book to continue inspiring you over the year. Here are some of my favorites:\n\nâ€¢Eighty percent of health leads in the brain\n\nâ€¢Turn the rest of your life into the best of your life\n\nâ€¢Increase simplicity in your life\n\nâ€¢Reality not rhetoric\n\nâ€¢Enjoy the privilege of doing purposeful work\n\nâ€¢Replenish your passion\n\nâ€¢Have intentions to improve\n\nâ€¢Happiness means finding beauty everyday\n\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/2015_EVENT_DR_MURAD_LONDON_HOTEL_POST_4.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1841" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/2015_EVENT_DR_MURAD_LONDON_HOTEL_POST_4.jpg" alt="2015_EVENT_DR_MURAD_LONDON_HOTEL_POST_4" width="3607" height="1911" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/2015_EVENT_DR_MURAD_LONDON_HOTEL_POST_5.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1842" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/2015_EVENT_DR_MURAD_LONDON_HOTEL_POST_5.jpg" alt="2015_EVENT_DR_MURAD_LONDON_HOTEL_POST_5" width="2667" height="1295" /></a>Dr. Murad + myself, so happy about new beginnings to conquer Cultural Stress. What a journey this will be! Naturally I loved this mantra above, ''treat yourself like royalty''. Done!\n\nThe nite was encouraging + inspiring. Dr. Murad focuses on us becoming our truest selves [he gave the analogy that at 1.5yrs old we were carefree, artistic + we were not phased by cultural stress]. Now, in NYC in 2015, we all feel the everyday cultural pressures: perfection, success, followers, likes, being with the latest trends, fitting in, + so much more. We are bombarded everyday by these pressures. His book, which I am excited to dive into this afternoon, is a go to for dealing with it all. Afterall, Dr. Murad has done many studies which directly link our life, stress, eating habits to our skin. Our skin is a reflection of our inside. Starting to focus on our inside self for a minute + adjusting our lifestyle accordingly, being intentional about how we are treating our bodies is the first way to better skin. Perhaps the second is following Murad''s suited skin care regime.. More on that another day.\n\nOne of my gal pals, amazing MUA Ashley Rebecca joined with me- always a good time.<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1844" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/2015_EVENT_DR_MURAD_LONDON_HOTEL_POST_ASHLEY_REBECCA_6.jpg" alt="2015_EVENT_DR_MURAD_LONDON_HOTEL_POST_ASHLEY_REBECCA_6" width="3148" height="2118" />This morning I am reveling in the goodies from last nite. All body focused products, I will be breaking down my thoughts in future posts. Can''t wait to dig in!<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/2015_EVENT_DR_MURAD_LONDON_HOTEL_1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1838" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/2015_EVENT_DR_MURAD_LONDON_HOTEL_1.jpg" alt="2015_EVENT_DR_MURAD_LONDON_HOTEL_1" width="3776" height="2520" /></a>+ Opening my book to this: the sweetest note from Dr. Murad:\n\nSarah\n\n''Find beauty everywhere'' Wishing you + yours Youth, Health, Happiness + Joy.\n\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1839" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/2015_EVENT_DR_MURAD_LONDON_HOTEL_POST_2.jpg" alt="2015_EVENT_DR_MURAD_LONDON_HOTEL_POST_2" width="3750" height="2259" />Those are some wishes to live by... XXX', 'Skin + Cultural Stress: Dr. Murad hosts event at The London Hotel in NYC', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1837-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-01-27 11:10:41', '2015-01-27 11:10:41', '', 1837, 'http://182.71.22.42/sarah/?p=1870', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
