(1898, 1, '2015-01-27 11:35:27', '2015-01-27 11:35:27', 'Shot by Cathrine Wessel, I did hair + makeup for her Fall collection of beautiful wool clothing, with&amp;wessel. It was such a fun day with beauty, Quinta! GET THE LOOK...<!--more-->\n\nWe chose to do a very natural, loose texture in the hair. I blew Quinta''s hair out with <a href="http://www.oribe.com/index.php/products/view/50/foundation-mist/" target="_blank">Oribe Foundation mist</a>, then wrapped 1 inch sections with a light spray of <a href="http://www.oribe.com/index.php/products/view/70/superfine-hair-spray/related:50" target="_blank">Oribe Super Fine Hair Spray</a> + letting set for 10 minutes. Then I fingercombed through the hair with a dime sized drop of <a href="http://www.oribe.com/index.php/products/view/48/creme-for-style/" target="_blank">Oribe Creme for Style</a>.\n\nFor makeup, the main focus was the skin + brows. For her skin, I used my fingers to apply <a href="http://www.sephora.com/photo-finish-foundation-primer-P9889?skuId=1349968" target="_blank">Smashbox Photo Finish Foundation Primer</a> around her t zone, nose + mouth, then with a flat foundation brush applied a conservative amount of <a href="http://www.sephora.com/liquid-halo-hd-foundation-spf-15-P380996?skuId=1526797" target="_blank">Liquid Halo HD Foundation</a> starting in the center of the face + using the brush to feather out product to the edges. A touch of <a href="http://www.sephora.com/halo-highlighting-wand-P292404?skuId=1349638" target="_blank">Smashbox Halo Highlighting Wand</a> around the top of the cheeks, nose + brow bone for a natural glowy effect. Then to finish, <a href="http://www.sephora.com/brow-tech-P260313?skuId=1241017" target="_blank">Smashbox Brow Tec</a>h on the brows to create a structured look, framing her face.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/WW_FW14_Lookbook_05.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1539" alt="W&amp;W_FW14_Lookbook_05" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/WW_FW14_Lookbook_05.jpg" width="800" height="1200" /><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1537" alt="W&amp;W_FW14_Lookbook_03" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/WW_FW14_Lookbook_03.jpg" width="800" height="1200" /></a>Â Â  <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/WW_FW14_Lookbook_06.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1540" alt="W&amp;W_FW14_Lookbook_06" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/WW_FW14_Lookbook_06.jpg" width="800" height="1200" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/WW_FW14_Lookbook_22.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1541" alt="W&amp;W_FW14_Lookbook_22" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/WW_FW14_Lookbook_22.jpg" width="800" height="1200" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/WW_FW14_Lookbook_33.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1542" alt="W&amp;W_FW14_Lookbook_33" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/WW_FW14_Lookbook_33.jpg" width="800" height="1200" /></a>', 'NEW WORK/ lookbook for with&wessel', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1536-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-01-27 11:35:27', '2015-01-27 11:35:27', '', 1536, 'http://182.71.22.42/sarah/?p=1898', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
