(1912, 1, '2015-01-27 11:51:02', '2015-01-27 11:51:02', '&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWe all love the classic, structured, perfected, bold lip. But, to make it fresh + current, I love doing a diffused, smudgy lip. Here''s how with two of my favorite lipsticks... <!--more--><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1478" alt="CHANEL_LIP_MAC_SARAH_APPLEBY_PRODUCT" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/CHANEL_LIP_MAC_SARAH_APPLEBY_PRODUCT.jpg" width="2208" height="1248" />1/ Use a dry toothbrush {i personally love the cheap travel ones with stiffer bristles for this} + go over your dry lips with it gently. This will exfoliate your lips + get them all ready for moisture. Using a tiny amount of <a href="http://www.amazon.com/NUXE-Reve-Miel-Honey-Balm/dp/B000EVD8FY" target="_blank"><em><strong>Reve De Miel</strong></em></a>, press into your lips. I love this lip balm {from France} because it is not shiny or sticky + extremely moisturizing. Great as a base.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/REVE_DE_MIEL_SARAH_APPLEBY.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1485" alt="REVE_DE_MIEL_SARAH_APPLEBY" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/REVE_DE_MIEL_SARAH_APPLEBY.jpg" width="2208" height="966" /></a>\r\n\r\n3/ <a href="http://www.chanel.com/en_US/fragrance-beauty/Makeup-Lipstick-ROUGE-ALLURE-VELVET-122517" target="_blank"><em><strong>Chanel Rouge Allure Velvet in LA PRECIEUSEâ€¢317</strong></em></a> is the perfect red. Dab the stick all over your lips then press your lips together getting all edges {here is where are are not worried about the color bleeding over a little!}. The red will come off pink until you give it more saturation. Then using your finger blend + feather out the edges to diffuse the color.<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1482" alt="chanel_rouge_allure_velvet_sarah_appleby4" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/chanel_rouge_allure_velvet_sarah_appleby4.jpg" width="2208" height="984" />4/ Using the stick press color into the inner part of your lips, the lips need to be most saturated with color in the center + then diffuse toward the edges.<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1481" alt="chanel_rouge_allure_velvet_sarah_appleby3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/chanel_rouge_allure_velvet_sarah_appleby3.jpg" width="2208" height="1248" /><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/chanel_rouge_allure_velvet_sarah_appleby2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1480" alt="chanel_rouge_allure_velvet_sarah_appleby2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/chanel_rouge_allure_velvet_sarah_appleby2.jpg" width="2208" height="1248" /></a>Here it is again using <a href="http://www.maccosmetics.com/product/shaded/168/310/Lipstick/index.tmpl" target="_blank"><em><strong>MAC Cosmetics Amplified Creme Lipstick in UP THE AMP.</strong> </em></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/MAC_AMPLIFIED_CREME_UP_THE_AMP_SARAH_APPLEBY.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1484" alt="MAC_AMPLIFIED_CREME_UP_THE_AMP_SARAH_APPLEBY" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/MAC_AMPLIFIED_CREME_UP_THE_AMP_SARAH_APPLEBY.jpg" width="2079" height="1128" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/MAC_AMPLIFIED_CREME_UP_THE_AMP_SARAH_APPLEBY_2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1483" alt="MAC_AMPLIFIED_CREME_UP_THE_AMP_SARAH_APPLEBY_2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/MAC_AMPLIFIED_CREME_UP_THE_AMP_SARAH_APPLEBY_2.jpg" width="2208" height="1248" /></a>VOILA! A sexy + fun new take on the bold lip. Matte + Satin finishes will be best for this, as you want pigmented lipsticks to work with {not lustre/sheer etc}. Happy blurring! X', 'HOW TO/ blurred lips', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1477-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-27 11:51:02', '2015-01-27 11:51:02', '', 1477, 'http://182.71.22.42/sarah/?p=1912', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
