(1917, 1, '2015-01-27 12:14:04', '2015-01-27 12:14:04', '<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/photo.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1438" alt="photo" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/photo.jpg" width="3264" height="1632" /></a>Here we are: AWARDS SEASON! That means it''s time for a lot of glam {good + bad!} coming down the red carpet. Last nite at the Golden Globes, we saw a lot of the latter. In keeping with my positive approach to this new year, here are my favorite/BEST five makeups + hairstyles from last nite...<!--more--> We saw a lot of messy updos + bad lashes {really?}, but alas here are my golden gals: <strong><em>1/Jennifer Lawrence.</em></strong> Girl has got it together. Her effortless short coiff complements her classic makeup. Her subtle platinum smoked out eyes with feathery lashes + rusty red lip was classic + flawless. Now about her dress....<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/jenniferlawrencegoldenglobes2014.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1430" alt="jenniferlawrencegoldenglobes2014" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/jenniferlawrencegoldenglobes2014.png" width="581" height="662" /></a><em><strong>2/Sofia Vergara.</strong></em> I love the way Sofia kept her look classic, yet casual. Her hair + makeup went well with her bold structured black dress. Her brows are my favorite, brushed up + natural looking which works with her textured lashes. A pretty winter rosy lip is the perfect choice for her skin tone. Her hair was down + loose + elegantly effortless.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/sofiavergaragoldenglobes2014.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1431" alt="sofiavergaragoldenglobes2014" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/sofiavergaragoldenglobes2014.png" width="588" height="627" /></a><em><strong>3/Kerry Washington.</strong></em> Here is a perfectly executed smoky eye. It is dramatic without being overload. I love that the sparkle + shimmer is kept to a minimum, slight contour on the cheeks with a natural lip. Again, the loose + flowy hair- absolutely radiant.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/kerrywashingtongoldenglobes2014.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1432" alt="kerrywashingtongoldenglobes2014" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/kerrywashingtongoldenglobes2014.png" width="588" height="658" /></a><em><strong>4/Olivia Wilde.</strong></em> She couldn''t be more of a babe! Love the intense plum smoky eye, diffused with a rosy shadow. Her skin was flawless + glowy, with a nude lip. Her hair color was a standout the way it was styled with the loose tousled waves.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/oliviawildegoldenglobes20141.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1435" alt="oliviawildegoldenglobes2014" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/oliviawildegoldenglobes20141.png" width="566" height="667" /></a><em><strong>5/Paula Patton</strong></em>. Love this makeup, subtle eye with a slight highlight + with the focus on gorgeous pink cheeks + lips. Her skin looks like butter. The classic slicked hair with side part is striking.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/paulapattongoldenglobes2014.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1434" alt="paulapattongoldenglobes2014" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/paulapattongoldenglobes2014.png" width="590" height="617" /></a>There you have it. I think this was just a taste of what is to come on March 2, for the glam portion of the 86th Annual Academy Awards. I hope to see a lot more of the above, hopefully others will take notes + follow suit. I don''t want to see anymore messy/curly updos or low messy buns, bad fake lashes or overly done sparkles + shimmer. It is done. Happy Monday! X', 'REVIEW/ my favorite glam at the Golden Globes 2014', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1429-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-27 12:14:04', '2015-01-27 12:14:04', '', 1429, 'http://182.71.22.42/sarah/?p=1917', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1918, 1, '2015-01-27 12:14:28', '2015-01-27 12:14:28', '&nbsp;\r\n\r\nI amÂ  l o v i n gÂ  the new spring/summer campaigns. The makeup is fresh + natural, + the skin is transparent. Here are my top picks at the moment...<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<strong><em>MAX MARA S/S 2014</em></strong> with Hana Jirickova/Natalia Siodmiak/Stef Van Der Laan, shot by Mario Sorrenti. The slight creamy contour on the eye, minimal {if any} lash + brow with a subtle lipstain. Makeup Artist: Aaron DeMay.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/maxmaraspring2014sarahappleby5.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1467" alt="maxmaraspring2014sarahappleby5" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/maxmaraspring2014sarahappleby5.jpg" width="722" height="960" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/maxmaraspring2014sarahappleby.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1463" alt="maxmaraspring2014sarahappleby" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/maxmaraspring2014sarahappleby.jpg" width="736" height="960" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/maxmaraspring2014sarahappleby2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1464" alt="maxmaraspring2014sarahappleby2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/maxmaraspring2014sarahappleby2.jpg" width="753" height="960" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/maxmaraspring2014sarahappleby3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1465" alt="maxmaraspring2014sarahappleby3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/maxmaraspring2014sarahappleby3.jpg" width="752" height="960" /></a>\r\n\r\n<strong><em>CARVEN S/S 2014 </em></strong>with Marte Mei van Haaster shot by: Viviane Sassen. Whomever did this this makeup is spot on. The glowy cheeks with matte nude lips. It is divine. <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/carvenss2014sarahappleby2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1455" alt="carvenss2014sarahappleby2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/carvenss2014sarahappleby2.jpg" width="721" height="940" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/carvenss2014sarahappleby3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1456" alt="carvenss2014sarahappleby3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/carvenss2014sarahappleby3.jpg" width="652" height="850" /></a> <em><strong>COACH S/S 2014</strong></em> with Freja Beha Erichson shot by: Craig McDean. Talk about a natural beauty. Love Freja, the makeup is invisible, just corrective. This is the East coast standard for beauty.<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1457" alt="coachfrejasarahappleby" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/coachfrejasarahappleby.jpg" width="800" height="529" /> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/coachsarahappleby2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1458" alt="coachsarahappleby2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/coachsarahappleby2.jpg" width="800" height="800" /></a> <strong><em>DIOR mag F/W 2013</em></strong> with Jennifer Lawrence shot by: Mikael Jansson. Well, this one is a little cheeky, I know I am late but this is exceptional. What a gorgeous take from the classic brand. I WISH they had made this campaign. Skin is stunning, flawless, buttery etc. Can we have this J-Law everyday please!<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1459" alt="diormagfw2013sarahappleby" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/diormagfw2013sarahappleby.jpg" width="770" height="936" /> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/diormagfw2013sarahappleby2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1460" alt="diormagfw2013sarahappleby2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/diormagfw2013sarahappleby2.jpg" width="800" height="774" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/diormagfw2013sarahappleby3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1461" alt="diormagfw2013sarahappleby3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/diormagfw2013sarahappleby3.jpg" width="770" height="936" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/diormagfw2013sarahappleby4.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1462" alt="diormagfw2013sarahappleby4" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/diormagfw2013sarahappleby4.jpg" width="800" height="534" /></a><em><strong>MULBERRY S/S 2014</strong></em> with Cara Delavigne shot by: Tim Walker. + One more fresh face, subtle contour of the eye + perfect pout. Would have loved to see a little more sheen on the skin, but this beauty is so good when she is natural! Stunning.<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1468" alt="mulberryss2014sarahappleby" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/mulberryss2014sarahappleby.jpg" width="683" height="1024" /> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/mulberryss2014sarahappleby2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1469" alt="mulberryss2014sarahappleby2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/mulberryss2014sarahappleby2.jpg" width="800" height="533" /></a> <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1470" alt="mulberryss2014sarahappleby3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/mulberryss2014sarahappleby3.jpg" width="683" height="1024" />I always know when we are at the beginning of the end of winter, as I am getting antsy for dewy skin with sheen + shimmer. I will however, abide by my own obsession + ruling of keeping seasonal skin + makeup! In the meantime, these gorgeous makeups + images will be posted all over my office to keep me happy... X', 'Favorite Five/ fresh faced campaigns', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1453-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-27 12:14:28', '2015-01-27 12:14:28', '', 1453, 'http://182.71.22.42/sarah/?p=1918', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
