(1921, 1, '2015-01-28 04:56:36', '2015-01-28 04:56:36', '<div id=":nl">\r\n<div>I can''t believe that another year has come + gone. Each January 1, like many others, I take time out to rest, reflect + make some new goals for the new year. I am certain there should be a list of rules somewhere about making a new years resolution list, because no one wants to be set up for failure. Here are a few of my {very realistic!} hopes for this new sparkly year... <!--more-->\r\n\r\n1/ <em> Love my body well</em>. No, not be at the gym 5X / week, because that isn''t happening, no matter how hard I try. But I am going to choose to exercise, fuel my body properly + give myself a full opportunity to be energized + capable of being my very best, for work, for play + in my relationships.\r\n\r\n2/ <em>Slow Down.</em> I rush. I hurry. I want to pause. I was recently given the book In Praise of Slowness by Carl Honore, it''s full of beautiful ideas that come from such a simple place. In the book Honore says: ''<em>the great benefit of slowing down is reclaiming the time + tranquility to make meaningful connections-- with people, with culture, with work, with nature, with our own bodies + minds.'' </em>We are not meant to be hustling + running around, feeling anxious. We miss out! I want to see beauty in places I work, places I walk by daily + have time to acknowledge beauty in people I don''t even know. I am generally good at having alone time, down time, but I must always remember to make space in my life + schedule forÂ  fun, for love, for rest.\r\n\r\n3/ <em>Speak well of others.</em> It is so easy to make quick remarks about how others choose to work, live, what they choose to put first. I want to be slow to speak, + acknowledge that my words are loaded. ''<em>You can mean something, but if you say it mean it, no one can hear your meaning. Have convictions, but if you don''t have compassion, you will have trials. Please, say what you believe, but please, always be love</em>'' - Ann Voskamp. I want to be a woman of my word, integrity, + for the good of people. I want to use my words to affirm, encourage, support + love people well.\r\n\r\n4/ <em>Be in touch.</em> I have friends + family across the globe, I want to be more intentional about communicating with them. I want to know what is going on in their world {+ beyond the photos I see on social media- which gives a false sense of understanding}. I want to ring them more, send more cards, notes + letters. I want to remember birthdays, + celebrate them. When I think about the people that I love, who inspire me most I can only hope they know how I feel... Time for a change!\r\n\r\n5/ <em>Balance. </em>I want it all! Sometimes it is overwhelming thinking about my hopes + dreams, goals + aspirations + how far away it all feels. I want balance + perspective. I want to play as hard as I work + love as much as I dream.\r\n\r\nIt is a new year + I can''t wait to see what 2014 has in store. What are you hopeful for this year? Where do you want to make changes? Wishing for you the very best year full of beauty... X\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'LIVE/ YOU ARE VERY WELCOME, 2014!', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1384-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-28 04:56:36', '2015-01-28 04:56:36', '', 1384, 'http://182.71.22.42/sarah/?p=1921', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
