(1932, 1, '2015-01-28 05:00:16', '2015-01-28 05:00:16', 'It is that time of year again! Here in NYC, as the days are getting shorter + shorter + Winter, our skin is becoming dryer + duller. As with my ongoing obsession with keeping seasonal, I switch around my skincare routine, adding more layers to ensure my skin doesn''t get thirsty! Here are my favorite makeup products at the moment to ensure your skin never dulls...<!--more--><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/winterskinmacdermablendchanelmakeup.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1330" alt="winterskinmacdermablendchanelmakeup" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/winterskinmacdermablendchanelmakeup.jpg" width="3776" height="2520" /></a>After getting your skin all cleansed + toned + moisturized, start with a base foundation. I keep two options at the moment, one for day + one for nite.\r\n\r\n<em>DAY/ <a href="http://www.maccosmetics.com/product/shaded/11633/393/New-Collections/MAC-Rick-Baker/Multi-Use/Face-And-Body-Foundation-120-ML/index.tmpl" target="_blank">MAC face + body foundation</a>, super lightweight + dewy finish</em>\r\n\r\n<em>NITE/ <a href="http://www.chanel.com/en_US/fragrance-beauty/Makeup-Foundation-PERFECTION-LUMI%C3%88RE-123093" target="_blank">CHANEL perfection lumiere</a>, full coverage + matte finish</em>\r\n\r\nWhen applying, use your fingers; it is the most versatile tool you have. Not only will the warmth from your fingers bring the makeup to life, but it gives you more control with where the product is placed.\r\n\r\nChoose your foundation then mix 2 drops of <a href="http://www.maccosmetics.com/product/shaded/793/4440/Lustre-Drops/index.tmpl" target="_blank"><em>MAC lustre drops in sun rush</em>.</a> If lustre drops are used on it''s own, you will get much more of a shimmer where as I prefer it in the foundation where it reads as more of a glow.\r\n\r\nThen I apply some <a href="www.dermablend.com/concealers/concealer-severe-flaws/quickfix.htm" target="_blank"><em>DERMABLEND quick fix concealer</em></a> around my eyes, mouth + nose, wherever there is spot pigmentation or redness.\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/winterskinpapawcobigelow.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1331" alt="winterskinpapawcobigelow" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/winterskinpapawcobigelow.jpg" width="3776" height="2520" /></a>Then to add a pop of sheenÂ  + contour to the skin, I love using <a href="http://lucaspapaw.com.au/" target="_blank"><em>Lucas'' Papaw Ointment</em> </a>to my eyelids + the top of my cheekbones. It adds a glisten that makes your skin look mega hydrated. + Finally, some <a href="http://www.bigelowchemists.com/c-o-bigelow-cinnamint-supreme-2x-lip-shine-no-504.html" target="_blank"><em>C.O. Bigelow Lip Shine in cinnamint supreme</em></a> on my lips for gloss. I love the flavor + texture.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/winterskin1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1328" alt="winterskin1" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/winterskin1.jpg" width="3411" height="2274" /></a>Clean, hydrated skin goes a long way this time of year! What are your favorite winter makeup products for skin? X\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'HOW TO/ glowy winter skin', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1327-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-28 05:00:16', '2015-01-28 05:00:16', '', 1327, 'http://182.71.22.42/sarah/?p=1932', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
