(1939, 1, '2015-01-28 05:11:41', '2015-01-28 05:11:41', 'While in France last week I managed to find myself some new beautiful things. I used to travel + buy up the town + then face the last minute challenge of how to get it all home. Well, as time has gone by, trips become more of an experience rather than a treasure hunt, an accumulation. I find myself being much more selective with my purchases, making each one more special. Being that France is an easy place to find pretty things, I worked hard at finding the most perfect takeaways. Here are my favorite five must haves from this last trip...<!--more-->You can''t go to Paris without a stop at <a href="http://www.lebonmarche.com/" target="_blank">Le Bon Marche</a> in the 7th. The dreamy department store is filled with finely curated designer musthaves. I promised myself only one treat whilst in there, + yes, <em>Celine</em> found me. I have been eyeing these sunnies for sometime + finally scooped them up! What better place to buy Celine than in PariPari, right?<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1294" alt="celinesunglassesfrance" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/celinesunglassesfrance.jpg" width="2208" height="1248" />Then onto <a href="http://www.yelp.fr/biz/city-pharma-paris" target="_blank"><em>City-Pharma</em></a>, the pharmacie/drugstore that every beauty queen raves about. The drugstore that every product junkie loves to hate. It''s always busy, people are always pushy, but you will get the best prices on all the french beauty brands! Here are a few products that jumped into my bag:\r\n\r\nâ€¢<em>bioderma</em> | jumbo bottle | good for all skin types | toning + cleansing\r\n\r\nâ€¢<em>caudalie tinted moisturizer</em> | new product | light coverage + high in moisture\r\n\r\nâ€¢<em>dexeryl moisturizer</em> | jumbo bottle | best for dry winters | not greasy + unscented\r\n\r\nâ€¢<em>nuxe oil</em> | the unofficial scent of every pharmacie in france | moisturizing + floral fragrance<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/favoritebeautyproductsfrance1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1300" alt="favoritebeautyproductsfrance" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/favoritebeautyproductsfrance1.jpg" width="2208" height="1248" /></a>\r\n\r\nAlix Petit is a brilliant french designer + I am lucky enough to have her as a friend. She owns + designs womenswear {+ menswear as of this season!} for <em><a href="http://www.heimstone.com/fr/page/accueil.html" target="_blank">HEIMSTONE</a>, </em>with two locations: Cambon + Cherche midi. The collections are full of color + texture, + unique prints which she designs as well. I saw this suede jacket with the leopard printed collar + sleeves + knew I had to have it. Every gal needs a signature Heimstone piece {did I mention they sell online too?}!\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/heimstoneleopardjacketfrance.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1296" alt="heimstoneleopardjacketfrance" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/heimstoneleopardjacketfrance.jpg" width="2208" height="1248" /></a>Being a lover of tea, I was shocked when I discovered there was a flavor, that wasn''t ''new'', I hadn''t experienced. It was <em>Mariage Freres''</em> Â <a href="http://www.mariagefreres.com/boutique/UK/ft+lapsang-souchong-imperial-classical-black-tin-100g+TC210.html" target="_blank">Lapsang Souchong Imperial</a>. It is a smoky black chinese tea, that tastes like a campfire, an old scotch. Like my childhood. It''s so good! Many spots to buy the French tea favorite, I picked mine up at the Galeries Lafayette in the 1st, they have a cute little Tea Salon in the middle of the store. I also picked up the newest Earl Grey D''or as well as Paris Singapour. Not only am I obsessed with the tea, I love the presentation, packaging, wrapping + how much the company focuses on the history + origin of tea.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/mariagesfreres.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1297" alt="mariagesfreres" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/mariagesfreres.jpg" width="2208" height="1248" /></a>+ On Sunday, with friends, we wandered<a href="http://www.parisdigest.com/shopping/puces.htm" target="_blank"><em> Les Puces</em></a>, the flea market. I was after some old books, for creative purposes + stumbled across these old magazines dating back to 1935! I picked them up so I can use the pages to wrap all of my Christmas gifts this year. I love a beautifully wrapped gift + who doesn''t love some french history!\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/vintagemagazinesfrance.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1298" alt="vintagemagazinesfrance" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/vintagemagazinesfrance.jpg" width="2208" height="1248" /></a>Every time I leave France, I leave a little more of my heart there. I am supposed to live there at some point in life, I know that much... Someday! Until then will keep hopping across the pond to get my French fix! X', 'Favorite Five/ from france with love', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1293-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-28 05:11:41', '2015-01-28 05:11:41', '', 1293, 'http://182.71.22.42/sarah/?p=1939', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
