(1946, 1, '2015-01-28 05:26:39', '2015-01-28 05:26:39', '&nbsp;\r\n\r\nRemember when I was <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/summer-loving-my-new-favorite-accessories/" target="_blank">OH SO EXCITED</a> about chopping a fringe. Right. Here we are not even four months later + they are so long + I am over. them. Time for another change! Seeing as 99% of gals that I know go through this frustration, + this is clearly the worst part about having a cute fringe, I thought I would share my favorite three ways to style my hair during this tricky time...<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<em>Bump up your overgrown fringe</em>. Load up your damp hair with product, I am using Davines Mattering Mousse for wizards + blow your fringe up + round in the center + then out + wispy on the corners. You can always use a straightener to make it more dramatic too. {*If you have a blunt bang cut, have your stylist cut into the center of the fringe + up a little bit + then slowly texture it outwards- this will give you a little more flexibility during this time!}<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1247" alt="fringefix4" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/fringefix4.jpg" width="3264" height="2174" />This will give you a voluminous, playful fringe that easily sweeps out of your eyes for that dreamy, 70s feel.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/fringefix3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1246" alt="fringefix3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/fringefix3.jpg" width="3264" height="2174" /></a><em>Braid it in!Â </em>Beginning just past your temple, do a little french braid in the front, all the way around your hairline, including all of your fringe in. I use a little {very little!} wonder wax in the hair that I am placing in the braid. As the hair can be short, this help weigh it down + give it some hold. Once your braid is in, gently go through + pull out the hair to give it a fuller, more romantic look. Secure the end of the braid close to the top of the ear with a few bobby pins.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/fringefix2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1245" alt="fringefix2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/fringefix2.jpg" width="3264" height="2174" /></a><em>Polish + Pin it!</em> I love the classic feel of this look, I typically don''t love the obvious bobby pins, I think it works here. Give your hair a clean part: center more edgy / side is softer + then pull back all hair in a low clip in the back. Using a color neutral pin, using one per side, twist fringe under to longer strands + carefully place pin. Keep both sides even.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/fringefix1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1244" alt="fringefix1" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/fringefix1.jpg" width="3264" height="2174" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/davinesproductfringebang.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1252" alt="davinesproductfringebang" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/davinesproductfringebang.jpg" width="2907" height="1938" /></a>As much as this process can be tedious, I enjoy the challenge of getting creative + it makes me want to try new things... What are some of the ways you style your hair when growing out your fringe? X', 'HOW TO/ in between bangs + fixing the fringe.', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1243-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-28 05:26:39', '2015-01-28 05:26:39', '', 1243, 'http://182.71.22.42/sarah/?p=1946', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1947, 1, '2015-01-28 05:26:54', '2015-01-28 05:26:54', 'Those who know me well are aware that in my downtime, I love to host. There is nothing better than a beautiful table surrounded by ones you love whilst enjoying copious amounts of delicious cocktails + food + wine. Living in New York, it''s tricky to make the space for a big dining table + it''s only been this last year I have been blessed enough to make it happen! I have been making attempts to build beautiful {not complex, especially if I am wearing the chef''s hat!} table settings to complement what I am serving. Here is my super easy to create, fall set up...<!--more-->\r\n\r\nI should mention, I co hosted this gals'' nite with one of my nearest + dearest, Alex. She + I are on the same page when it comes to being surrounded by beautiful things so this was easy. In keeping everything seasonally appropriate, I went to the Flower District to pick up greenery, flowers, gourds + baby pumpkins. I love everything white, so naturally went for a few of the baby white pumpkins. Then at the art supply I picked up some metallic spray paint- gold + silver.<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1226" alt="dinnerpartyblog5" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/dinnerpartyblog5.jpg" width="3174" height="2116" />Start by taping half of the pumpkins, try to get the tape {masking tape would have been MUCH easier to use, alas I didn''t have it on hand} into each crevasse on the pumpkin for the best result.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/dinnerpartyblog3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1225" alt="dinnerpartyblog3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/dinnerpartyblog3.jpg" width="3264" height="2176" /></a>Then, spray away! I wanted the bottom halves of the pumpkins metallic, the gourds + corn sprayed solid.<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1229" alt="dinnerpartyblog8" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/dinnerpartyblog8.jpg" width="3204" height="2136" /><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/dinnerpartyblog10.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1230" alt="dinnerpartyblog10" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/dinnerpartyblog10.jpg" width="2724" height="1816" /></a>For the napkins, I placed a sprig of fern + set them with a gold letter at the bottom.<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1227" alt="dinnerpartyblog6" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/dinnerpartyblog6.jpg" width="3200" height="2133" />I made a base at the table of greenery + then had two vases of Hydrangeas, I opted for the muted tones to let the golds and silvers really pop.<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1228" alt="dinnerpartyblog7" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/dinnerpartyblog7.jpg" width="3264" height="2448" /> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/dinnerpartyblog1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1223" alt="dinnerpartyblog1" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/dinnerpartyblog1.jpg" width="3200" height="2133" /></a> + Voila! Of course, the only other piece that is required for a delicious evening, is a beautiful meal to go along with it all. We served Cream of Spinach soup, then a Scalloped Potato dish with Canadian Bacon followed by an arugula/fennel/radicchio/dill salad + for the finale, made-from-scratch individual pumpkin pies with a dollop of vanilla bean whipped cream.<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1236" alt="dinnerpartymealfinal" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/dinnerpartymealfinal1.jpg" width="3264" height="1464" />It was a really fun evening, I am already scheming what I can spray paint next, oh!Â  + Dinner settings for Thanksgiving {#2!}.... X\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'FALL LOVING/ crafting a dinner party', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1221-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-28 05:26:54', '2015-01-28 05:26:54', '', 1221, 'http://182.71.22.42/sarah/?p=1947', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1948, 1, '2015-01-28 05:27:08', '2015-01-28 05:27:08', '&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIf my 15 year old self knew that yesterday would come + I would be face painting queen-of-country, Martina McBride, I would have lost it! This one''s for the girls... She really is the ultimate babe. I had the most incredible day with Martina + team, she is classy + genuine + such a joy to work with. + Beautiful too, made it oh so easy for me! A few snaps from the day... <!--more--><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/martinamcbridebts3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1261" alt="martinamcbridebts3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/martinamcbridebts3.jpg" width="3928" height="1664" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/martinamcbridesarahappleby.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1255" alt="martinamcbridesarahappleby" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/martinamcbridesarahappleby.jpg" width="3968" height="2232" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/glyniscarpenter.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1257" alt="glyniscarpenter" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/glyniscarpenter.jpg" width="2208" height="1248" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/martinamcbridebts.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1260" alt="martinamcbridebts" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/martinamcbridebts.jpg" width="2208" height="1248" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/martinamcbride2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1259" alt="martinamcbride2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/martinamcbride2.jpg" width="2208" height="1248" /></a><em></em><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1256" alt="glamteammartinamcbride" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/glamteammartinamcbride.jpg" width="1280" height="725" /><em>PHOTO: Glynis Carpenter | HAIR: Christopher Naselli {above!} | MAKEUP: Moi</em><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/martinamcbridesarahapplebybts.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1262" alt="martinamcbridesarahapplebybts" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/martinamcbridesarahapplebybts.jpg" width="2048" height="1215" /></a>Such a fun team, I can''t wait to see the final images! + To end with a view like this, Brooklyn in best. X', 'BEHIND THE SCENES/ martina mcbride', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1254-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-28 05:27:08', '2015-01-28 05:27:08', '', 1254, 'http://182.71.22.42/sarah/?p=1948', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1949, 1, '2015-01-28 05:27:18', '2015-01-28 05:27:18', 'Here''s a new story I did with mega talented photographer + Canadian {!}, Geoff Barrenger. We worked with Latvian, Guntars, + ran around the sketchier part of Brooklyn for a day. Anthony Pedraza styled with Viktor+Rolf, Rag + Bone, Louboutin etc...<!--more--><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Guntar-by-Geoff-Barrenger-Shot-1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1213" alt="Guntar by Geoff Barrenger - Shot 1" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Guntar-by-Geoff-Barrenger-Shot-1.jpg" width="2640" height="3360" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Guntar-by-Geoff-Barrenger-Shot-1B.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1214" alt="Guntar by Geoff Barrenger - Shot 1B" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Guntar-by-Geoff-Barrenger-Shot-1B.jpg" width="2640" height="3360" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Guntar-by-Geoff-Barrenger-Shot-2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1215" alt="Guntar by Geoff Barrenger - Shot 2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Guntar-by-Geoff-Barrenger-Shot-2.jpg" width="2640" height="3360" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Guntar-by-Geoff-Barrenger-Shot-3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1216" alt="Guntar by Geoff Barrenger - Shot 3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Guntar-by-Geoff-Barrenger-Shot-3.jpg" width="2640" height="3360" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Guntar-by-Geoff-Barrenger-Shot-4.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1217" alt="Guntar by Geoff Barrenger - Shot 4" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Guntar-by-Geoff-Barrenger-Shot-4.jpg" width="2640" height="3360" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Guntar-by-Geoff-Barrenger-Shot-5.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1219" alt="Guntar by Geoff Barrenger - Shot 5" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/Guntar-by-Geoff-Barrenger-Shot-5.jpg" width="2640" height="3360" /></a>In Guntar''s hair I used <a href="http://www.bumbleandbumble.com/product/spp.tmpl?CATEGORY_ID=CAT74&amp;PRODUCT_ID=224" target="_blank"><em>Bumble+bumble Thickening Hair Spray</em></a>, <a href="http://www.davines.com/en/products/view/finest-oil-non-oil-n1" target="_blank"><em>Davines Finest Oil Non Oil</em></a> + <a href="http://www.davines.com/en/products/view/defining-wonder-wax" target="_blank"><em>Davines Wonder Wax</em></a>. X', 'NEW WORK/ guntars by the bridge', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1212-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-28 05:27:18', '2015-01-28 05:27:18', '', 1212, 'http://182.71.22.42/sarah/?p=1949', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1950, 1, '2015-01-28 05:27:38', '2015-01-28 05:27:38', '&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThere''s a fine line for me between having cute damaged hair {you know that blond matte texture} + bad damaged hair, having your ends split + break + fall off. It is very typical for me that by the end of summer, after my hair has been bleached then sun bleached, up in a bun + unloved, I am dealing with very very thirsty hair. {Please no judgment on the photo above!} Here are my go to products + regimen how to restore + bring the life back to your locks...<!--more--><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/davinesojon.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1198" alt="davinesojon" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/davinesojon.jpg" width="2958" height="1972" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/ojonhaircare.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1203" alt="ojonhaircare" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/ojonhaircare.jpg" width="3264" height="2448" /></a>Start by using a quarter sized dollop of<em> <a href="http://www.ojon.com/product/5063/15439/giftssets/shopbycategory/Travel-Sizes/damage-reverse-Restorative-Hair-Treatment/index.tmpl" target="_blank">Ojon Restorative Hair Treatment</a>.</em> It is chunky + solid at first, but warm it in your hands + it emulsifies.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/davinesojon2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1200" alt="davinesojon2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/davinesojon2.jpg" width="1233" height="822" /></a>Apply the oil like treatment to damaged parts of your hair {*put it only where absolutely necessary, you don''t want to over condition your hair, it will become soft + break off. For my color- I have kept it just on the ends as my natural hair doesn''t need the treatment}. Keep the treatment on your hair for 15-30 minutes. If you need a major restoration, you can leave on for up to an hour with plastic wrap around your hair to keep it conditioning.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/davinesojon1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1199" alt="davinesojon1" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/davinesojon1.jpg" width="1093" height="729" /></a>+ Then continuing with my obsession keeping seasonal with all things, I have switched to<em> Davines</em> <em><a href="http://www.davines.com/en/products/view/alchemic-shampoo-tobacco" target="_blank">Alchemic Shampoo</a> + <a href="http://www.davines.com/en/products/view/alchemic-conditioner-tobacco" target="_blank">Conditioner in Tobacco</a>.</em> The perfect scent for fall! + This shampoo + conditioner makes your hair light + full + conditioned without being heavy. Not to mention smelling delicious. So I wash + condition my hair + then let air dry, fast for me as I have very fine hair, until it''s damp + then follow with a quick blow out. Here''s my hair after it''s been blown out, yes it''s naturally this straight!...<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/davinesojonhaircare33.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1207" alt="davinesojonhaircare3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/davinesojonhaircare33.jpg" width="1280" height="960" /></a>Then to smooth out the ends, I add a dime sized drop of the Davines <em><a href="http://www.davines.com/en/products/view/oi-oil" target="_blank">Absolute Beautifying Potion</a></em> to the ends. It is really light + brings the ends together, adding a subtle sheen. <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/davineshairoil.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1197" alt="davineshairoil" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/davineshairoil.jpg" width="2970" height="1980" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/davinesojonhaircare.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1202" alt="davinesojonhaircare" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/davinesojonhaircare.jpg" width="1280" height="960" /></a>+ Voila! New hair. This is the perfect quick fix for those who are growing your hair out, or don''t make time for cuts every 6 weeks but want it to look good... With all of that said, my cut is booked for next week! Happy hair don''t care! X', 'HOW TO/ dealing with damaged hair', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1196-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-28 05:27:38', '2015-01-28 05:27:38', '', 1196, 'http://182.71.22.42/sarah/?p=1950', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1951, 1, '2015-01-28 05:34:06', '2015-01-28 05:34:06', '&nbsp;<br /><br /><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/20130916-092122.jpg"><img src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/20130916-092122.jpg" alt="20130916-092122.jpg" class="alignnone size-full" /></a>So much to see + take in this year during NYFW! I think overall, the makeup for Spring 2014 was pretty subdued.. It was a season of muted skin + only some with pops of lip, cheek, or eye. Loved it all! I love the androgyny in a handful of the looks, whether it was simply highlighting the brow or giving the skin a sheen. + Then we got our pops of color + texture every so often! Here are my favorite NYFW Makeup Trends {Hair will post tomorrow!}...\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<strong><em>Charlotte Tilbury at Prabal Gurung:</em> </strong>bleached brows, matte skin, vibrant violet matte lip. Feels very 60''s + I love!\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/PrabalGurung14.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1026" alt="PrabalGurung14" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/PrabalGurung14.png" width="604" height="483" /></a><strong><em>Tom Pecheux for Peter Som:</em></strong><em> </em>clean skin, little neutral blush, cramy contour on eyes, no brow or lash. Clean androgyny, think it played very well with the collection!<em> </em><em><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Peter-SomNYFW14.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1024" alt="Peter SomNYFW14" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Peter-SomNYFW14.png" width="578" height="591" /></a></em><strong><em>Gucci</em><em><strong> W</strong>estman for Rag + Bone:</em></strong><em> </em>brows brushed up, clear glossy eye, bold orange lip. First time Rag + Bone has gone for a bold lip like this, Gucci can do no wrong- perfection.<em> </em><em><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Rag+BoneNYFW14.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1023" alt="Rag+BoneNYFW14" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Rag+BoneNYFW14.png" width="611" height="399" /></a></em><strong><em>James</em><em><strong> Kaliardos for Nicole Miller:</strong></em></strong><em> </em>bold brows, contoured warm tone eye, highlighted nose + browbone, bold deep purple lip. I love this, so simple + clean, yet romantic + mysterious. <strong><strong> </strong><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/NicoleMillernyfw14.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1025" alt="NicoleMillernyfw14" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/NicoleMillernyfw14.png" width="471" height="432" /></a></strong><strong>James<em> Kaliardos for Rodarte:</em></strong><em> </em>matte skin, contoured temples + cheekbones, brows brushed up without definition, matte nude lip + medium graphic liner. James is so good, I love everything he does- this is simple yet striking.<em> </em><em><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Rodarte14nyfw.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1027" alt="Rodarte14nyfw" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Rodarte14nyfw.png" width="414" height="440" /></a></em>Tomorrow comes my favorite hair looks..... in the meantime I''ll be stalking my favorite sites that are capturing the LFW shows! X\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'NYFW Makeup Trends: five favorites from new york fashion week', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1022-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-28 05:34:06', '2015-01-28 05:34:06', '', 1022, 'http://182.71.22.42/sarah/?p=1951', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
