(1958, 1, '2015-01-28 05:36:35', '2015-01-28 05:36:35', 'I have had my Mum + Gram from Alberta Canada, visiting me this last week + it''s always fun to indulge on the many incredible activities NY offers... It also reminds me that I don''t explore enough. We spent an afternoon in my neighborhood {!} at the Brooklyn Botanical Gardens. How have I not spent more time there. I was so inspired by the flora, colors, textures, smells {the fragrance garden is my favorite!} + to have that oasis so close to home, in the midst of a concrete jungle is a blessing. A few snaps from the day...<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1094" alt="BKBotanicalGardens" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens.jpg" width="2418" height="1534" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1095" alt="BKBotanicalGardens1" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens1.jpg" width="2828" height="1534" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1096" alt="BKBotanicalGardens2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens2.jpg" width="2566" height="1534" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1097" alt="BKBotanicalGardens3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens3.jpg" width="2632" height="1534" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens4.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1098" alt="BKBotanicalGardens4" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens4.jpg" width="2738" height="1536" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens5.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1099" alt="BKBotanicalGardens5" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens5.jpg" width="2466" height="1534" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens6.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1100" alt="BKBotanicalGardens6" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens6.jpg" width="2354" height="1536" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens7.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1101" alt="BKBotanicalGardens7" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens7.jpg" width="2656" height="1534" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens8.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1102" alt="BKBotanicalGardens8" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens8.jpg" width="2550" height="1536" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens9.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1103" alt="BKBotanicalGardens9" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens9.jpg" width="2342" height="1534" /></a>Â  <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens11.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1105" alt="BKBotanicalGardens11" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens11.jpg" width="2702" height="1534" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/botanicalgardensbk.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1108" alt="botanicalgardensbk" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/botanicalgardensbk.jpg" width="1794" height="2046" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens12.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1106" alt="BKBotanicalGardens12" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/BKBotanicalGardens12.jpg" width="2362" height="1536" /></a>It is incredible to me the different shapes plants + flowers + trees have. They are all so unique + individual. + This is the tiniest sampling of what the whole world offers! I am so excited for Autumn, with all our surroundings changing... Now head over to your local gardens to enjoy the landscapes + solitude! X', 'Breathing Beauty/ brooklyn botanical gardens', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1093-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-28 05:36:35', '2015-01-28 05:36:35', '', 1093, 'http://182.71.22.42/sarah/?p=1958', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1959, 1, '2015-01-28 05:36:42', '2015-01-28 05:36:42', 'I stole my dear friend, Alex, for an afternoon of riding our bikes {little white lightning is mine + gonzales belongs to her} around Brooklyn + then snuck in a little glam time to play with her brows + lashes. I documented it all so you could see the process... Lucky me, as she models very professionally, you''d think she had done this before {wink}! Here is how to get more refined + finished brows with feathery lashes...<!--more--><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY6.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1118" alt="ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY6" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY6.jpg" width="2448" height="2448" /></a>\r\n\r\n<em>Start out with a clean + moisturized face<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1114" alt="ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY2.jpg" width="2585" height="1723" />Beginning with the lashes! Start by curling your natural lashes, I like the <a href="http://www.japonesque.com/catalogue.cfm" target="_blank">Japonesque Power Curl Eyelash Curler</a>. Be sure to move the curler around your lash line you you don''t have one obvious bend. <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY11.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1123" alt="ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY11" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY11.jpg" width="1280" height="960" /></a></em><em>Now for mascara! <a href="http://www.stilacosmetics.com/product/glamoureyes-mascara.do?from=Search" target="_blank">Stila''s Glamoureyes mascara</a> in black is a favorite for building texture. Take your time + get right to the root of your lashes.</em><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY9.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1121" alt="ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY9" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY9.jpg" width="2202" height="1468" /></a>\r\n\r\n<em>Onto the brows! A quick trick is to brush the brows downwards before applying liner, this way you see the natural top of your brow line. I used <a href="http://www.clinique.com/product/1595/4799/Makeup/Brows/Brow-Keeper/index.tmpl" target="_blank">Clinique Brow Keeper in Warm Brown</a> + apply the liner in upward strokes. You don''t have to fill the entire brow, but make sure it''s all even. Most of us have spotty brows, + a little fill in is always good.<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1119" alt="ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY7" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY7.jpg" width="2547" height="1698" /><em>As you are filling in, you can then brush the brows up {where they will be finished} to see where you are at with shape.</em></em><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY5.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1117" alt="ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY5" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY5.jpg" width="3060" height="2040" /></a><em>Then we are going to bump up the natural lash, I love the <a href="http://www.popbeauty.co.uk/Popbeauty_Products/Lashes/Dressed_Up_Lashes/index.html" target="_blank">Pop Beauty individual lashes</a> . On the back of my hand, I put a dab of <a href="http://www.soap.com/p/duo-surgical-grade-eyelash-adhesive-284042?site=CA&amp;utm_source=Google&amp;utm_medium=cpc_S&amp;utm_term=HTU-009&amp;utm_campaign=GoogleAW&amp;CAWELAID=1581015820&amp;utm_content=pla&amp;adtype=pla&amp;cagpspn=pla" target="_blank">Duo eyelash glue</a> + then use <a href="http://www.makeupforever.com/products/tweezer.html#.Ukl3TSSls14" target="_blank">Make Up For Ever Tweezers</a> to pull an individual lash from the pack + dip it lightly {just so the very point has a spot of white glue on it}. </em>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1113" alt="ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY.jpg" width="3264" height="2176" /></a><em>Then starting with the outer corner, place the individual lash IN your lashes {they can sit on top, but for maximum natural finish, get them in between}. I used 6/7 per eye laying then 2/3 of the way in. This will draw your eye open + out. <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1115" alt="ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY3.jpg" width="3124" height="2083" /></a></em>\r\n\r\n+ The final look: full, refined brows with natural looking feathery lashes. This is a great look anytime, would look gorgeous with a poppy lip for daytime + stronger, darker lip for evening. Thank you Alex, you beauty. X<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY4.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1116" alt="ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY4" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/ALEXCOLLINSBEAUTY4.jpg" width="3264" height="2176" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'HOW TO/ refined brows + feathery lashes', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1112-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-28 05:36:42', '2015-01-28 05:36:42', '', 1112, 'http://182.71.22.42/sarah/?p=1959', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
