(1995, 1, '2015-01-28 06:03:10', '2015-01-28 06:03:10', 'I do love my almond milk. Along with being delicious, almond milk has many health benefits! + It is oh so easy to make yourself at home. Here''s my step by step to make the yummiest vanilla almond milk...<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/homemadealmondmilk7.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-871" alt="homemadealmondmilk7" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/homemadealmondmilk7.jpg" width="3263" height="2448" /></a><em>What you''ll need</em> {above}:\r\n\r\n2 cups of raw almonds {soaked for 8 hrs}\r\n\r\n1 vanilla bean {vanilla extract CAN be used, but not nearly as delicious!}\r\n\r\nA pinch of Cinnamon\r\n\r\nA pinch of Himalayan Sea Salt\r\n\r\nBlender {I love my <a href="http://www.brevilleusa.com/hemisphere-control.html">Breville</a>}\r\n\r\nNut bag {I got mine off of <a href="http://www.amazon.com/Samson-Nut-Milk-Sprouting-Bag/dp/B009AZ20FE/ref=sr_1_4?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1374112622&amp;sr=8-4&amp;keywords=nut+bag">Amazon</a>}\r\n\r\n7 cups of water\r\n\r\nI am basing these measurements on how I like my almond milk, you can adjust the measurements as to how thick, sweet, salty you like it!\r\n\r\n<strong>1/ Soak your raw almonds for a minimum of 8 hours. This gets the nuts nice + plump + for optimal milk</strong><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/homemadealmondmilk5.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-874" alt="homemadealmondmilk5" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/homemadealmondmilk5.jpg" width="3264" height="2176" /></a><strong>2/ Blend the almonds for 45 seconds + then put on liquify mode for 15 seconds</strong>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/homemadealmondmilk1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-869" alt="homemadealmondmilk1" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/homemadealmondmilk1.jpg" width="3264" height="2176" /></a><strong>3/ Pour the almond milk through the nut bag. This is a slow process, you have to be patient as the milk seeps through the bag. You can gently squeeze the bag to get the excess milk out.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/homemadealmondmilk6.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-875" alt="homemadealmondmilk6" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/homemadealmondmilk6.jpg" width="2894" height="2169" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/homemadealmondmilk.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-868" alt="homemadealmondmilk" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/homemadealmondmilk.jpg" width="3070" height="2303" /></a>4/ Then pour the almond milk back into the blender + add your vanilla bean, salt + cinnamon, blend for 30 seconds. </strong>{You can use your almond skins and extras to make almond meal, granola, muffins, cookies etc!}<strong><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/homemadealmondmilk3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-872" alt="homemadealmondmilk3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/homemadealmondmilk3.jpg" width="2448" height="2448" /></a></strong>Voila! There you have it. The milk, stored in an air tight container, will last {I use milk jars + mason jars} for 3-4 days. I love using it for breakfast, over granola, in my smoothies, to drink alone, for dessert over berries + the list goes on! <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/homemadealmondmilk2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-870" alt="homemadealmondmilk2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/homemadealmondmilk2.jpg" width="2590" height="1943" /></a>\r\n\r\nNot only does almond milk provide great health benefits; reducing the risks of heart disease, maintaining balance in cholesterol, assisting in weight loss, but! It has some amazing beauty benefits too. Vitamin E, present in almond milk, protects the skin from the harmful effects of free radicals; this makes our skin healthy and younger looking. There is also an abundance of Vitamin B2, also known as riboflavin, which helps the tissues of the skin, hair and nails to use oxygen. Therefore, healthier, hydrated hair, skin + nails! I will absolutely drink to that... X', 'Drink to Beauty/ homemade vanilla almond milk', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '876-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-28 06:03:10', '2015-01-28 06:03:10', '', 876, 'http://182.71.22.42/sarah/?p=1995', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
