(1997, 1, '2015-01-28 06:03:32', '2015-01-28 06:03:32', '&nbsp;\r\n\r\nI am not typically a huge fan of colored mascaras, perhaps the baby blue from the 80''s throws me a bit. But I have to say <em>CHANEL has done it right</em>. Oh + a <em>life changing {gals, for real!} new skin product</em> that really makes flawless so easy. Here is a 5 minute summer look...<!--more--><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/SAmakeupfavorites.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-862" alt="SAmakeupfavorites" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/SAmakeupfavorites.jpg" width="2278" height="2278" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/kevynaucoinmakeup.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-860" alt="kevynaucoinmakeup" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/kevynaucoinmakeup.jpg" width="1180" height="852" /></a>Step by step:\r\n\r\n<em>1/ Cleanse, Moisturize</em>\r\n\r\n<em>2/ Conceal+Correct</em>: Using only a dab of <a href="http://www.bergdorfgoodman.com/p/Kevyn-Aucoin-Sensual-Skin-Enhancer-Face/prod82310065_cat400803__/?icid=&amp;searchType=EndecaDrivenCat&amp;rte=%252Fcategory.jsp%253FitemId%253Dcat400803%2526pageSize%253D30%2526No%253D0%2526refinements%253D&amp;eItemId=prod82310065&amp;cmCat=product" target="_blank">Kevyn Aucoin''s Sensual Skin Enhancer</a> {I am SX10}, I use my fingers to tap + blend around my eyes, nose + mouth. This is definitely more than a concealer + not so much a foundation, it is a brilliant whipped formula that makes covering up any pigmentation, spots or darkness a total breeze! I feel crazy being so excited about this. It''s a skin revelation. The above photo is with the tiniest bit of Skin Enhancer, bedhair + early eyes!\r\n\r\n<em>3/ Curl+Color/</em> I love the <a href="http://www.japonesque.com/catalogue.cfm" target="_blank">Japonesque Lash Curler</a> to curl my lashes. I just discovered le volume de CHANEL in 30-Prune! It''s subtle {the final look does not do the color on my lashes justice, I am not a photo pro!} + pretty. I load it on! I love a textured looking eye, *not to be confused with clumpy though. This prune will bring out the yellow undertones in brown eyes + pop any blue/green eyes too! It''s a fun new way to pop a little color in the makeup.\r\n\r\n<em>4/ Define the brows</em>/ I used <a href="http://www.maccosmetics.com/product/shaded/149/263/Products/Eyes/Brow/Eye-Brows/index.tmpl" target="_blank">MAC eye brow pencil in Lingering</a> to lightly sharpen my brows, then brush through.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/chanelprunemascara.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-861" alt="chanelprunemascara" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/chanelprunemascara.jpg" width="1280" height="960" /></a>\r\n\r\nThat''s the look! Summer poppy prune eyes we love...X\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'New Obsession/ Colored Mascara', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '859-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-28 06:03:32', '2015-01-28 06:03:32', '', 859, 'http://182.71.22.42/sarah/?p=1997', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1998, 1, '2015-01-28 06:04:05', '2015-01-28 06:04:05', 'It''s time for some new summer staples, here are a few fun things I am loving + can''t live without! All suited for summer adventuring in NYC...\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<br /><br /><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/20130709-110149.jpg"><img src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/20130709-110149.jpg" alt="20130709-110149.jpg" class="alignnone size-full" /></a><em>House of Harlow flats</em>: I haven''t had a pair of HoH shoes before. Was drawn to the gold, black + white beading + patterns of lions! I love these flats, they are the perfect transitional pair from day to nite. \r\n\r\n<br /><br /><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/20130709-110527.jpg"><img src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/20130709-110527.jpg" alt="20130709-110527.jpg" class="alignnone size-full" /></a><br /> <br /><br /><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/20130709-110617.jpg"><img src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/20130709-110617.jpg" alt="20130709-110617.jpg" class="alignnone size-full" /></a>\r\n<em>Natural nails</em>: I know I know, how many beauty mags are talking about the color of nails for summer... Well, I am loving my natural nails. I''ve just started using the NailTek system which is mega strengthening + the base + top coat together gives me that healthy sheen.\r\n\r\n<br /><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/20130709-110632.jpg"><img src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/20130709-110632.jpg" alt="20130709-110632.jpg" class="alignnone size-full" /></a><em>Fujifilm Instant Mini 25S camera: This camera! Must have. The original insta pic! I have been taking photos non stop, pinning them </em>all around the apt. Best for capturing summer''s best!\r\n\r\n<br /><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/20130709-110607.jpg"><img src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/20130709-110607.jpg" alt="20130709-110607.jpg" class="alignnone size-full" /></a><br /><em>Fringe</em>! I did it. I chopped my hair, embracing my natural color. It''s good to switch it up every once in a while, + although anxious at first- I am loving the playful new do. \r\n\r\n<br /><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/20130709-110559.jpg"><img src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/20130709-110559.jpg" alt="20130709-110559.jpg" class="alignnone size-full" /></a><br /><em>Loeffler Randall Rider bag</em>: I needed a new summer bag that I could tote around, throw in my bike basket + be durable enough for the summer fun. This is the winner! Love the mint green color + really functional with so many pockets inside as well as the optional strap. \r\n\r\nWhat are you favorite summer accessories? Your can''t-live-withouts? X', 'Summer Loving/ my new favorite accessories', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '853-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-28 06:04:05', '2015-01-28 06:04:05', '', 853, 'http://182.71.22.42/sarah/?p=1998', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1999, 1, '2015-01-28 06:04:50', '2015-01-28 06:04:50', '<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/chanelbrushes1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-840" alt="chanelbrushes1" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/chanelbrushes1.jpg" width="3066" height="2044" /></a>One of the most important factors in creating beautiful makeup is investing in good tools. Like any artisan, craftsperson, creator, handicrafter, the tools you use create ease in the process + the quality reflects in the final product...<!--more-->\r\n\r\nBrushes are one thing I am willing to invest in. If you take good care of your personal brushes {wash bi-weekly, store in a good place etc.} they will last you a lifetime. At all costs, lets avoid leaving the house with the broken bristles on your face, {we''ve all been there!}. Here are some of my favorite staples...\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.chanel.com/en_US/fragrance-beauty/Makeup-Brushes-%26-Accessories-89291" target="_blank">Les Pinceaux de CHANEL</a>/ my favorite ways to use {from top to bottom}:<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/chanelbrushes2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-839" alt="chanelbrushes2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/chanelbrushes2.jpg" width="2911" height="1940" /></a>\r\n<div>Powder Brushâ€¢ powder</div>\r\n<div>Angled Powder Brushâ€¢ bronzer for contouring</div>\r\n<div>Blending Foundation Brushâ€¢ moisturizer + heavier foundations</div>\r\n<div>Blush Brushâ€¢ powder blush</div>\r\n<div>Foundation Brushâ€¢ foundation + cream blush</div>\r\n<div>Large Tapered Blending Brushâ€¢ edges of shadow to blend + diffuse color</div>\r\n<div>Precise Liner Brushâ€¢ gel liner + shadow in water line</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<div><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/chanelbrushes.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-838" alt="chanelbrushes" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/chanelbrushes.jpg" width="2832" height="2124" /></a></div>\r\nChanel makes beautiful products, these seven brushes are essential in creating your flawless face. Now get to some pretty face painting! X', 'Tool Box/ Pretty New Painters', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '837-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-28 06:04:50', '2015-01-28 06:04:50', '', 837, 'http://182.71.22.42/sarah/?p=1999', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2000, 1, '2015-01-28 06:05:01', '2015-01-28 06:05:01', 'I was sent to the land of cheese- aka Madison, Wisconsin, for work last week. Population &gt; 300K. I am always excited to check out a new city. I had my kit, a rental car + an hour drive to + from the studio everyday; far from my life + regular commute on the train here in NYC. Madison is a beautiful city; full of old buildings, beautiful architecture, parks, restaurants, + all centered around the Capitol Building as well as pretty Lake Monona {which I did my fair share of running around!}...<!--more--><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/madisonwisconsin.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-830" alt="madisonwisconsin" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/madisonwisconsin.jpg" width="3264" height="2176" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/madisonwisconsin2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-831" alt="madisonwisconsin2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/madisonwisconsin2.jpg" width="2681" height="1787" /></a>\r\n\r\nHad a lovely week, working + not! The restaurants I went to were all delicious. I will assume it''s because everything is farm-to-table fresh. Fresh produce, organic meats + don''t even get me started on the cheese! One evening I took time after work to head out to Hook''s Cheese Co. + it was everything I had imagined. It was so interesting to be in the cheese plant. So much going on! I did a major stock up. <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/madisonbeauty4.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-825" alt="madisonbeauty4" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/madisonbeauty4.jpg" width="3264" height="1934" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/madisonbeauty5.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-826" alt="madisonbeauty5" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/madisonbeauty5.jpg" width="2720" height="1812" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/madisonbeauty3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-824" alt="madisonbeauty3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/madisonbeauty3.jpg" width="3139" height="2093" /></a>\r\n\r\nThen another evening, I was delighted to find out, while walking downtown, it was concert in the square! I picked up my dinner + sat in the park with hundreds of others + listened to the Wisconsin Symphony Orchestra.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/madisonbeauty6.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-828" alt="madisonbeauty6" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/madisonbeauty6.jpg" width="3264" height="2448" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/madisonwisconsinsymphony.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-829" alt="madisonwisconsinsymphony" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/madisonwisconsinsymphony.jpg" width="1981" height="1321" /></a>\r\n\r\nIt was a long work week, but my evening adventuring made for a nice balance! Although small, the city holds a lot of beauty, I look forward to returning soon... <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/madisonbeauty.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-822" alt="madisonbeauty" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/madisonbeauty.jpg" width="2787" height="1858" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/madisonbeauty2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-823" alt="madisonbeauty2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/madisonbeauty2.jpg" width="3264" height="2174" /></a>', 'Photo Diary: Madison, Wisconsin', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '821-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-28 06:05:01', '2015-01-28 06:05:01', '', 821, 'http://182.71.22.42/sarah/?p=2000', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
