(2006, 1, '2015-01-28 06:07:16', '2015-01-28 06:07:16', 'Summer is upon us + all the gals want the bronze smudgy eyes. I just discovered the new Clinique Chubby Stick for eyes + it is the perfect partner for this makeup. So easy to use + blendable. Here is how you get the look...<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/cliniqueeyesproduct.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-759" alt="cliniqueeyesproduct" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/cliniqueeyesproduct.jpg" width="4319" height="3274" /></a> You will need:\r\n<div>â€¢<a href="http://www.clinique.com/product/1595/5634/Makeup/Brows/Brow-Shaper/index.tmpl" target="_blank">Clinique Brow Shaper </a>I use a mix of Wheat + Soft Brown</div>\r\n<div>â€¢<a href="http://www.clinique.com/cms/whats_new/chubbystick/wn_index.tmpl" target="_blank">Clinique Chubby Stick Shadow Tint for Eyes</a> in Bountiful Beige/Lots o'' Latte/Fuller Fudge</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\nâ€¢Once your skin is flawless {using foundation, tinted moisturizer, powder, whichever you prefer} I use an angle brush to <em>fill in my brows</em>. Mixing the two colors to give the brow some depth, + flicking the brush up with the product into your brows will have them looking natural. Don''t overdo it. + Don''t stress out, <em>your brows are not symmetrical</em>!<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-723" alt="cliniquebrows" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/cliniquebrows.jpg" width="4416" height="3312" />â€¢<em>Apply Lots o'' Latte all over the base of your eye</em> + blend out the top edges with your finger.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/sarahapplebymakeup3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-725" alt="sarahapplebymakeup3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/sarahapplebymakeup3.jpg" width="4416" height="3312" /></a>â€¢Using <em>Bountiful Beige color along your brow bone</em> +<em> inner corner of the eye to highlight</em>. Blend the colors together. {We love that these are so blendable + do not get muddy!}<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-722" alt="sarahapplebymakeup4" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/sarahapplebymakeup4.jpg" width="4416" height="3312" />â€¢<em>Use Fuller Fudge + color a generous line around your entire eye, along with inside your waterline</em>. Blend into the other colors. Putting the dark on last + closest to the lashline gives the eyes a diffused look.<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-721" alt="cliniquesarahappleby" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/cliniquesarahappleby.jpg" width="4416" height="3312" />â€¢<em>Curl your lashes + add some chunky mascara</em> + you are ready for your day or evening out! <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/sarahapplebymua.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-757" alt="sarahapplebymua" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/sarahapplebymua.jpg" width="2944" height="4416" /></a>Embrace the Summer of Bronze Beauty! X', 'MAKEUP/ how to: bronze/smudgy eyes', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '719-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-28 06:07:16', '2015-01-28 06:07:16', '', 719, 'http://182.71.22.42/sarah/?p=2006', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
