(2030, 1, '2015-01-28 06:20:20', '2015-01-28 06:20:20', 'Fragrance is huge for me. I may be one of those people that have a finely tuned nose or perhaps I have been around so many fragrances + now I just can''t live without it. I love it when I walk into a space; a boutique, park, spa, home etc. + I am greeted with a cloud of aroma. With that said, I also love it when you walk up to someone + find their fragrance. {Yes, at times I am surely that girl with maybe one or two sprays too many of my perfume!}. Along with being a perfume junkie, I am obsessed with products that make my home + space fragrant. Some favorites...<!--more-->\r\n\r\nâ€¢<a href="http://www.sephora.com/candelina-collection-P377322?skuId=1498393" target="_blank">Tocca Candle in Florence</a>: this candle smells like European Garden rose known aka Centifolias, combined with iris root. When I have this burning in my apartment it makes me feel like I am in a garden! There is something so magical about floral scents to me, I am obsessed.\r\n\r\nâ€¢<a href="http://balenciagafragrance.com/en/balenciaga-paris" target="_blank">Balenciaga Paris Perfume</a>: my summer staple [yes, seasons change as should your fragrance!], this week at least! It''s fresh + floral + light + airy. Notes of Violet Leaf, Pepper, Cedarwood, Patchouli, Vetiver.\r\n\r\nâ€¢<a href="http://www.sedafrance.com/product/Japanese-Quince-Classic-Toile-Liquid-Hand-Soap/Hand-Soap" target="_blank">Seda France Hand Soap in Japanese Quince</a>: Since I have been in NYC, I have loved this scent {candles + diffusers too!}. I find myself walking into so many shops that are filled with the Japanese Quince. I could never tire of this one... Notes: Rhubarb, Passion Fruit, Peach, Jasmine Petals. {FYI: the notes do not do it justice!}\r\n\r\nâ€¢Fresh Fleurs: I am an advocate for fresh flowers in the home at all times. Be it from a lovely gent, or my own stop by the florist en route home- it''s a must! I am mostly an all white flower gal, but this week I opted for a pop of pink, tulips are so pretty this time of year. Fresh flowers do something for me, visually + aromatically.\r\n\r\nIt''s all a part of living well + surrounding yourself with spaces + products that give you life. Breathe beauty.', 'A Fragrant Desire', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '620-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-28 06:20:20', '2015-01-28 06:20:20', '', 620, 'http://182.71.22.42/sarah/?p=2030', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2031, 1, '2015-01-28 06:20:57', '2015-01-28 06:20:57', 'I recently spent some time at the Ian Potter Centre in Melbourne, Australia. It was a treat of a day as I showed up solo to attend a group ''tour'' of the gallery, to find out I was the only one! I spent nearly an hour with a woman who showed me around the museum + shared with me a vast amount of knowledge about the museum, history + pieces. It was up there in one of my favorite museum experiences...<!--more--><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/NGVlivingwater2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-609" alt="NGVlivingwater2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/NGVlivingwater2.jpg" width="2314" height="1736" /></a>I especially loved the exhibit, <a href="http://www.ngv.vic.gov.au/whats-on/exhibitions/exhibitions/living-water" target="_blank">Living Water</a>, it''s the most beautiful series of pieces, each having rich meaning. An excerpt from the Exhibition about ''Living Water'': {<em>Aboriginal people from across the Western Desert use the term â€˜living waterâ€™ to describe water sources, including rock holes and soakage waters that are fed by underground springs. The path of these springs was created by the ancestral beings of the tjukurrpa (Dreaming) as they themselves journeyed underground, their entry into the earth often marking the site of current day water sources. â€˜Living waterâ€™ is revered also because it does not seem to be affected by the harsh conditions above the ground that the people themselves have to endure</em>.}. Life giving, inspiring!<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/NGVlivingwater3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-610" alt="NGVlivingwater3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/NGVlivingwater3.jpg" width="1536" height="1152" /></a>The artist''s lives + communities were built around the water wells, represented by the black circles. The colors + patterns in the paintings were very inspiring + learning the meanings behind shapes, colors + the textures the artists chose were all representative of their way of life. Not to mention how visually appealing they all are.\r\n\r\nMuseums are something I thoroughly enjoy, but too rarely make time for. I always wonder why I can''t fit more gallery/exhibit openings into my life. There are so many incredible exhibits popping up every week in Manhattan, no reason not to pop in after work once a week! You know where to find me Thursday eve...', 'Traveling + Adventuring/ Melbourne: Ian Potter Centre', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '607-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-28 06:20:57', '2015-01-28 06:20:57', '', 607, 'http://182.71.22.42/sarah/?p=2031', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2032, 1, '2015-01-28 06:21:35', '2015-01-28 06:21:35', 'For all of us beauty junkies, a good product isn''t difficult to come by. However an experience in helping create the product is the very best! I have talked about french skin care line, Caudalie, before + here is yet another reason to say ''oui!'' to their incredible products...<!--more--><img title="More..." alt="" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-includes/js/tinymce/plugins/wordpress/img/trans.gif" />\r\n\r\nI recently found myself in the flagship store on Bleecker street + while perusing the new goodies I was encouraged to try the Crushed Cabernet Scrub. So I rolled up my sleeves + got right into scrubbing my hands. They were left feeling soft + supple + smelled beyond delicious. In that moment I thought of my client''s + how delicious it would be if my hands smelled like that while working on their face! The store''s concoction was made of Rosemary + Lemon... It was divine! + Yes! All Vino inspired, using grapes + grapeseeds. They hand make each scrub for their clients; made with honey, grapeseed, sugar + scented oils [all natural of course!]. You get to choose your special mix of oils to add. As I am one that is obsessed with all things floral, I went with Geranium + Lemongrass. It is now a staple! I keep mine by the sink so I can wash my hands with it, but it is also a perfect scrub for the body. Merci Beaucoup! Make your way to Bleecker St {If you can''t get over there soon enough, you can order their<a href="http://www.sephora.com/crushed-cabernet-scrub-P100101" target="_blank"> Premade Cabernet Scrub</a>} + enjoy!<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/caudaliescrub2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-601" alt="caudaliescrub2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/caudaliescrub2.jpg" width="1561" height="2081" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/caudaliescrub1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-600" alt="caudaliescrub1" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/caudaliescrub1.jpg" width="2448" height="3264" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/caudaliescrub.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-599" alt="caudaliescrub" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/caudaliescrub.jpg" width="2175" height="2899" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Must Have/ Crushed Cabernet Scrub by Caudalie', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '591-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-28 06:21:35', '2015-01-28 06:21:35', '', 591, 'http://182.71.22.42/sarah/?p=2032', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2033, 1, '2015-01-28 06:21:51', '2015-01-28 06:21:51', 'Yesterday worked with the amazing team from Beauty High, painting + creating two gals in pretty pastels. Oh! + We shot in the cutest candy shop, CuRious Candy by Cynthia Rowley. When on the UES, you must check out...\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/20130501-140220.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full" alt="20130501-140220.jpg" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/20130501-140220.jpg" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/20130501-140339.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full" alt="20130501-140339.jpg" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/20130501-140339.jpg" /></a>I used Jurlique skincare on the girl to prep their skin, love the Radiance Serum, which really helps lock in moisture, giving you a glowy effect. Then used mainly cream color bases from MAC on their eyes + cheeks. Stila just launched Countless Color Pigments, such a beautiful range of colors, perfectly fitting for the concept of the shoot, I used to layer over the eyes. It was a day surrounded by the most delicious candy + colors, pastel hair (obsessed! Johnny styling + Zoe Wiepert coloring), + making beautiful images thanks to photographer Meghan McGarry. Can''t wait to see the final story! More from the shoot...\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/20130501-140459.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full" alt="20130501-140459.jpg" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/20130501-140459.jpg" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/20130501-140521.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full" alt="20130501-140521.jpg" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/20130501-140521.jpg" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/20130501-140540.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full" alt="20130501-140540.jpg" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/20130501-140540.jpg" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/20130501-140558.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full" alt="20130501-140558.jpg" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/20130501-140558.jpg" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/20130501-140614.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full" alt="20130501-140614.jpg" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/20130501-140614.jpg" /></a>\r\n\r\n+ Happy May! Seems I should be headed to the nearest salon for some cotton candy colored hair....', 'Behind the Scenes/ Pastel Dreaming', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '556-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-28 06:21:51', '2015-01-28 06:21:51', '', 556, 'http://182.71.22.42/sarah/?p=2033', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2034, 1, '2015-01-28 06:22:46', '2015-01-28 06:22:46', 'I love traveling for work. I''m currently on the west coast doing some work with German makeup company, Essence Cosmetics. I am definitely one to take full advantage of every hour I am not working to discover restaurants, cafes, bars whilst snapping landscapes + architecture. It is all so inspiring. It also helps that this time around, the city is warm + sunny + blooming with Spring...<!--more--> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/image2.jpg"><img src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/image2.jpg" alt="image" width="1024" height="769" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-538" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/image1.jpg"><img src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/image1.jpg" alt="image" width="1024" height="768" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-537" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/image6.jpg"><img src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/image6.jpg" alt="image" width="1024" height="768" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-542" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/image7.jpg"><img src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/image7.jpg" alt="image" width="1024" height="768" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-543" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/image4.jpg"><img src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/image4.jpg" alt="image" width="1024" height="768" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-540" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/image5.jpg"><img src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/image5.jpg" alt="image" width="1024" height="768" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-541" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/image9.jpg"><img src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/image9.jpg" alt="image" width="1024" height="768" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-545" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/image8.jpg"><img src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/image8.jpg" alt="image" width="1024" height="768" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-544" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/image10.jpg"><img src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/image10.jpg" alt="image" width="1024" height="769" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-546" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/image.jpg"><img src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/image.jpg" alt="image" width="1024" height="769" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-536" /></a> My three days have been filled strolling the Pearl District + the Eastside, consuming copious amounts of delicious coffee + juice, floral cocktails, food, + vino! Portland is a town full of wonderful people + thriving businesses that are doing food + drink right. Prasad, Maglia Rosa, Barista, Voodoo, Andina, LePigeon, Clyde Common all contributed. Now, back to work, en route to Seattle!', 'Work Trip/ portland photo diary', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '533-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-28 06:22:46', '2015-01-28 06:22:46', '', 533, 'http://182.71.22.42/sarah/?p=2034', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
