(2046, 1, '2015-01-28 06:30:08', '2015-01-28 06:30:08', '&nbsp;\r\n\r\nI am loving the new Spring/Summer 2013 campaigns out right now [most of them- here are the standouts]... All makeup is clean + pretty + the hair is natural, textured + choppy.\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<strong></strong><em>Salvatore Ferragamo/</em> love the color in the hair- ombre IS still happening + when done right, gorgeous <em>Prada/</em> pretty natural berry tint on the lip  <em>Balmain/</em> center part + texture in the hair is so good, dreaming of that leather jacket! <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/photo-52.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-494" alt="photo 5" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/photo-52.jpg" width="1823" height="1367" /></a>\r\n\r\nONDRIA + <em>CHANEL</em>! To date, one of my favorite models I have worked with. I love that not only did Karl choose her for this campaign, but it caused quite the stir due to the fact that she is still so young. I think it''s a perfect fit. This story is so good. Lips + Skin!<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/photo-23.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-492" alt="photo 2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/photo-23.jpg" width="1868" height="1402" /></a>\r\n\r\n<em>Marc Jacobs/</em> Still strong with the bleach blonde + touch a root showing through <em>Fendi/</em> I am into the glossy + slick hair, minimal makeup <em>Louis Vuitton/</em> 60''s vibe + beehive, vibrant color + bold patterns<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/photo-13.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-491" alt="photo 1" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/photo-13.jpg" width="1935" height="1451" /></a>\r\n\r\n<em>Giorgio Armani/</em> Obsessed with the short slick hair, inspiring my personal styling <em>Chloe/</em> Again, texture in the hair + the contoured eye is magic, very 70''s feeling here<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-490" alt="photo 3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/photo-32.jpg" width="1956" height="1467" /><em>Isabel Marant/</em> Daria! Natural + flawless <em>Celine/</em> Daria! Aside from the classic no makeup makeup, I love this whole collection. Phoebe, you can do no wrong. <em>Balenciaga/</em> Any woman who needs some short hair inspiration, obsess. The short choppy bob is back.\r\n\r\nAll so good. This season has made the muted hair + makeup so desirable. I love these campaigns, all tying mood + beauty + pieces together cohesively. Very inspiring.', 'S/S13: Campaign Inspiration', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1719-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-28 06:30:08', '2015-01-28 06:30:08', '', 1719, 'http://182.71.22.42/sarah/?p=2046', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2047, 1, '2015-01-28 06:30:37', '2015-01-28 06:30:37', '&nbsp;\r\n\r\nToday, I worked with one of my favorite clients, Saks 5th Ave, on an upcoming editorial for D+G. Gorgeous Nika modeling, made it easy for beauty. A few sneak peek shots from the day...<!--more-->\r\n\r\nFresh face; cleansed, moisturized.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/nika.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-469" alt="nika" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/nika.jpg" width="2176" height="3264" /></a>\r\n\r\nThe look: a neutral brown contour on the eyes, light fill of the brows, lots of mascara + a poppy creamy pink lip.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/nika11.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-478" alt="nika1" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/nika11.jpg" width="1854" height="2780" /></a>Frocks for days...<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/nika3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-470" alt="nika3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/nika3.jpg" width="2176" height="3264" /></a><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-479" alt="nika4" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/nika42.jpg" width="2176" height="3264" />Then a more sultry look, I am such a fan of the deep purple shade on the lip.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/nika51.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-480" alt="nika5" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/nika51.jpg" width="2176" height="3264" /></a>Final Images to come!', 'Behind the Scenes/ Saks 5th Avenue', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1717-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-28 06:30:37', '2015-01-28 06:30:37', '', 1717, 'http://182.71.22.42/sarah/?p=2047', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2048, 1, '2015-01-28 06:31:22', '2015-01-28 06:31:22', 'If I had a penny for every time someone asked me what my beauty ''rules'' are... I don''t really have rules. With makeup, hair, or fashion. I love the creative freedom of others + appreciate how they interpret beauty. However, there has been one consistent exception. Love your skin well. Which to me, means [+ not limited to] washing your face every evening + putting it to bed. Nearly half of your life is spent sleeping + the thought of it being caked with makeup, layered with dirty dusty air, + more, makes it not ok to not get this bedtime routine down!<!--more-->\r\n\r\nI love to switch up my products + try new skincare routines, but as of late, here is the go to...<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/photo-2-1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-496" alt="photo 2-1" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/photo-2-1.jpg" width="3264" height="2174" /></a>â€¢Makeup or no makeup day, I start with <a href="http://www.dermalogica.com/precleanse/1,default,pd.html" target="_blank">Dermalogica''s Precleanse</a>, it''s a gentle [plant based!] oil that lifts makeup, unwanted environmental pollutants, skincare products + more.\r\n\r\nâ€¢I apply <a href="http://www.sephora.com/deep-cleansing-exfoliator-P374574" target="_blank">Caudalie Deep Cleansing Exfoliator</a> with my hands, all over my damp skin + 3-4 times a week I use it with the <a href="http://www.clarisonic.com/for_professionals/clarisonic_pro_cleansing/technology/" target="_blank">Clarisonic Pro</a> for the suggested three minutes. It feel so good to get all that extra grit sluffed off my skin. The Clarisonic is great because it is gentle, yet leaves your skin feeling deeply cleansed + exfoliated as if you''ve just had the best facial. (Post a VinoSource Facial at the Caudalie Spa in the plaza, I immediately purchased the Clarisonic).\r\n\r\nâ€¢Moisturize! I use my ring finger to dab on <a href="http://www.sephora.com/ultimate-lift-eye-gel-P42344?om_mmc=Googlepla,_requestid=42976,cm_mmc=us_search-_-GG-_-pla-_-,ci_src=17588969,ci_sku=966200" target="_blank">Ole Henriksen Ultimate Eye Lift Gel</a> around my eyes + then generously apply the <a href="http://www.sephora.com/wild-rose-vitamin-c-advanced-brightening-sleeping-facial-P306883" target="_blank">Korres Wild Rose + Vitamin C Brightening Sleeping Facial</a> all over the face + neck. It is extremely hydrating + you wake up feeling completely rejuvenated\r\n\r\nâ€¢ Finishing off with a little <a href="http://us.amorepacific.com/en/product/MOISTURE_BOUND_LIP_TREATMENT" target="_blank">Amore Pacific Moisture Bound Lip Treatment</a>, perhaps my favorite lip treatment of all time- smooth texture leaving your lips supple.\r\n\r\nâ€¢I always sleep with water next to my bed in the case I need to hydrate throughout the nite! I blow my <a href="http://www.candleluxury.com/calvin-klein-delicate-blossoms-candle.html?utm_source=GoogleProducts&amp;utm_medium=shopping%2Bengine&amp;utm_term=Calvin+Klein+Delicate+Blossoms+Candle&amp;utm_campaign=GoogleProducts&amp;gclid=CNC94J-bzrYCFQef4AodHlkAXw" target="_blank">Calvin Klein candle in Delicate Blossoms</a> out + turn the lights off.\r\n\r\nSleep well + sweet dreams! S.', 'Good Night Skin', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1718-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-28 06:31:22', '2015-01-28 06:31:22', '', 1718, 'http://182.71.22.42/sarah/?p=2048', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2049, 1, '2015-01-28 06:32:25', '2015-01-28 06:32:25', '&nbsp;\r\n\r\nYesterday, had the pleasure of working with a very talented crew + my new favorite photographer. We ran around NYC shooting all sorts of amazingness. Second shoot day is tomorrow! Helicopters + BK oh my! I will keep the details to myself until images are released, but here are a few snaps from the day...<!--more--><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/photo-1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-429" alt="photo 1" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/photo-1.jpg" width="2139" height="3209" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/photo-4.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-432" alt="photo 4" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/photo-4.jpg" width="2176" height="3264" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/photo-3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-431" alt="photo 3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/photo-3.jpg" width="2080" height="3119" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/photo-5.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-433" alt="photo 5" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/photo-5.jpg" width="2176" height="3264" /></a>', 'Behind the Scenes: Working NYC', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '509-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-28 06:32:25', '2015-01-28 06:32:25', '', 509, 'http://182.71.22.42/sarah/?p=2049', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2050, 1, '2015-01-28 06:33:09', '2015-01-28 06:33:09', 'Every girl wants to believe they do not need any makeup. That is nice. However, loving your skin well, you understand your flaws + take a minute [or three] to perfect them. So the next time you are rushing out, take three minutes, here is your routine...<!--more-->\n\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/photo-21.jpg"><img class="aligncenter  wp-image-445" alt="photo 2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/photo-21.jpg" width="391" height="960" /></a>After moisturizing your face [SPF too!], apply <a href="http://www.bergdorfgoodman.com/p/Kevyn-Aucoin-Sensual-Skin-Tinted-Balm/prod84720052/?ecid=BGCIGoogleProductAds&amp;ci_src=17588969&amp;ci_sku=prod84720052skuSB02" target="_blank">Kevyn Aucoin''s Sensual Skin Tinted Balm</a>. I am loving this new product, it''s smooth + velvety, with light coverage leaving your skin with a dewy glow [please note the gorgeous packaging]. *Leave all tint off of your eyelids, it will give you a beautiful natural contour. Then open your eyes up with the <a href="http://www.ulta.com/ulta/browse/productDetail.jsp?skuId=2116560&amp;productId=prod2116560&amp;navAction=push&amp;navCount=1&amp;subdoc=98augbonuspoints&amp;categoryId=cat970001%20cat80086" target="_blank">Japonesque Power Lash Curler</a> + lightly fill in your brows with <a href="http://www.essence.eu/us/usa/products/eyes/eye-pencil.html" target="_blank">Essence Brow Pencil</a>. A little <a href="http://www.bigelowchemists.com/c-o-bigelow-mentha-lip-shine-spearmint-no-1191.html" target="_blank">C.O. Bigelow Mentha Lip Shine</a> + you are out the door! Flawless + Spring ready.</p>', 'Three Minute Makeup/ Au Natural', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '510-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-01-28 06:33:09', '2015-01-28 06:33:09', '', 510, 'http://182.71.22.42/sarah/?p=2050', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
