(2069, 1, '2015-01-28 07:00:45', '2015-01-28 07:00:45', 'I love my weekends. Living in Brooklyn, one of my favorite things to do is spend time shopping at my local farmers market. Stocking up on freshness to carry me through the week with copious amounts of green juices + smoothies. <!--more-->\r\n\r\nReasons this is a priority:\r\n\r\nâ€¢ Getting to know the farmers + supporting local agriculture\r\n\r\nâ€¢ Organic meats/produce are significantly less expensive\r\n\r\nâ€¢ You will eat seasonally! Produce is going to be fresh + ripe...\r\n\r\nâ€¢ The markets are beautiful! The colors of fresh flowers, fruit, veggies- so pretty + I need that fix this time of year while the trees + parks are so bare. <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/photo-32.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-355" alt="photo 3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/photo-32.jpg" width="2840" height="2130" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/photo-22.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-354" alt="photo 2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/photo-22.jpg" width="2746" height="2060" /></a>\r\n\r\nAs the Winter is early over, the variety of goods available is slimmer than the summer months. Yesterday I stocked up on greens [kale, spinach, collard], carrots, squash, onions, garlic, apples, + fresh flowers of course!\r\n\r\n+ Now I juice. This morning''s concoction:Â 5 stems of kale / 2 carrots / chunk of fresh ginger / 1 honey crisp apple / squeeze of fresh lemon <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/photo2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-359" alt="photo" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/photo2.jpg" width="2584" height="1938" /></a>\r\n\r\nI know when the nutrition [clean foods/juices] in our diet changes for the better, the skin is one of the first places we will see results. Here''s to delicious green juice + a glowy canvas to work our beauty on. Get into it!', 'Markets  +  Juicing/ For your skin''s sake', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '505-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-28 07:00:45', '2015-01-28 07:00:45', '', 505, 'http://182.71.22.42/sarah/?p=2069', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2070, 1, '2015-01-28 07:01:13', '2015-01-28 07:01:13', '<p style="text-align: center;">There were so many incredible beauty moments throughout NY, MIL, LDN, PAR for Autumn/Winter 2013. Here are a few of my favorite makeup looks, all designed by the best makeup artists in the world. Top L to Bottom R. Kenzo/AaronDeMay [Love the glossy texturedlid/unbalanced smoky eye] â€¢ Giorgio Armani/LindaCantello [Beautiful Matte skin/always a fan of inner nose+brow contour] â€¢ Lanvin/PatMcGrath [obsessed with the graphic eye/simple with blacks+greys/no brow = love] â€¢ Jean Paul Gaultier/LloydSimmons [all for the severe brow! + with nothing else, perfect] â€¢ Givenchy/PatMcGrath [pretty floral coloring on the eyes very autumn, with highlighted inner rim] â€¢Â  Celine/DickPage [Phoebe+Dick can do no wrong, flawless skin with a bronzer in blush placement, natural but a statement ]. Feeling inspired!</p>', 'Fashion Week A/W 2013: Inspiration', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '503-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-28 07:01:13', '2015-01-28 07:01:13', '', 503, 'http://182.71.22.42/sarah/?p=2070', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2071, 1, '2015-01-28 07:01:34', '2015-01-28 07:01:34', 'Just got home from a fun event at the NARS boutique on Bleecker street in the West Village. Being that it is just blocks from my old apartment, although wet + rainy, I love strolling that neighborhood + was happy to venture over that way to get inspired with NARS newness...<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-251" alt="photo 2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/photo-21.jpg" width="2362" height="1575" /> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/photo-31.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-252" alt="photo 3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/photo-31.jpg" width="2176" height="3263" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/photo-4.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-253" alt="photo 4" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/photo-4.jpg" width="2043" height="3064" /></a>NARS has just launched the new <a href="http://www.narscosmetics.com/the-latest/collections/newest-collections-from-nars/satin-lip-pencil-collection" target="_blank">Satin Lip Pencil</a> in 13 gorgeous shades. I am all about a lip, all the time. While sipping on Champagne, I perused the tiny boutique, running into both friends + peers. The new Lip Pencil is creamy in texture with full coverage [high impact color!] + the classic Satin finish. It gives me the coverage + saturation that I want in a lip pencil with a natural texture to finish. These are amazing on their own or topped off with a gloss. I picked up Floralies, Isola Bella, Rikugien, Hyde Park + Palais Royal.I have a feeling I will be heading back that way to pick up the rest of the shades very soon... S.', 'Champagne/ Satin Lips', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '499-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-28 07:01:34', '2015-01-28 07:01:34', '', 499, 'http://182.71.22.42/sarah/?p=2071', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
