(2077, 1, '2015-01-28 07:04:41', '2015-01-28 07:04:41', 'Welcome! This is my stream of [beauty related] consciousness... I hope you will find many reasons to keep checking back. I want to share with you my favorite techniques to creating faces from the inside out + all that inspires me along the way. Thanks for coming by, I would love for you to be in touch, comment + connect. Looking forward to it! S.', 'Let the Beauty Musings Begin.', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '177-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-01-28 07:04:41', '2015-01-28 07:04:41', '', 177, 'http://182.71.22.42/sarah/?p=2077', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2078, 1, '2015-01-28 07:04:53', '2015-01-28 07:04:53', '<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/photo-1-1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-222" alt="photo 1-1" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/photo-1-1.jpg" width="2448" height="2448" /></a>I am fresh off the long haul from MEL&gt;AKL&gt;LAX&gt;NYC, where I spent a few weeks both working + playing [more to come..]. When you are in the air, with no fresh air for that length of time, you need a great skincare regimen. It makes all the difference. I am not a huge fan of wearing makeup when I travel, less is more- your skin will thank you...<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/photo-2-1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-223" alt="photo 2-1" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/photo-2-1.jpg" width="720" height="720" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/photo.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-224" alt="photo" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/photo.jpg" width="827" height="827" /></a><!--more-->When I am up, up, + away: I use my <a href="http://www.skyniceland.com/product-23-nordic-skin-peel" target="_blank">Skyn Nordic Skin Peel</a>, they are pads that have Lactic acid, a gentle AHA (alpha hydroxy acid) derived from corn sugar, which helps exfoliate the skin. I leave that for half an hour or so + then follow up with the Amore Pacific <a href="http://us.amorepacific.com/en/product/MOISTURE_BOUND_Skin_Energy_Hydration_Delivery_System" target="_blank">Moisture Bound Skin Energy Hydration Delivery System</a>, spraying all over my face. I moisturize with <a href="http://us.caudalie.com/moisturizing-sorbet.html?gclid=CLb0mJL59LUCFYje4AodrR8AHw" target="_blank">Caudalie Moisturizing Sorbet</a> all over the face- use liberally! + <a href="http://us.caudalie.com/premier-cru-the-eye-cream-1.html" target="_blank">Caudalie Premier Cru The Eye Cream</a> around the eyes [be gentle!]. For the lips, <a href="http://us.nuxe.com/en/reve-de-miel-ultra-nourishing-lip-balm-160/reve-de-miel" target="_blank">Reve de Miel Lip Balm</a>, it has a lovely creamy, matte texture + a nice subtle flavor. If I have any spots, or need a little brightening under the eyes, I will apply a touch of<a href="http://www.lauramercier.com/store/shop/Concealers_Secret%20Concealer_prod220006" target="_blank"> Laura Mercier Secret Concealer</a>, medium coverage + super creamy texture.\r\n\r\nThroughout the flights, along with drinking copious amounts of water, I try to stay away from the airplane food which is packed with unnecessary sodium + will opt for packing a sandwich or salad if available.\r\n\r\nIt''s worth it to take the extra time to make sure your body + skin are all taken care of, upon landing you will feel the difference + be ready for an adventure!\r\n\r\nHappy hydrated travels!\r\n\r\nS.', 'Planes Trains + Beauty Mobiles', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '496-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-28 07:04:53', '2015-01-28 07:04:53', '', 496, 'http://182.71.22.42/sarah/?p=2078', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
