(2082, 1, '2015-01-28 07:06:16', '2015-01-28 07:06:16', ' Tonite I had the pleasure of attending an amazing event at the Plaza Hotel, thrown by French skincare line, Caudalie [they run the beautiful spa there]. If you know me well, you have already heard my continuous praises for Mathilde + Bertrand, the husband + wife power duo behind the line. The products are absolutely delicious. <!--more--><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/photo-2-2.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-235" alt="photo 2-2" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/photo-2-2.jpg" width="2283" height="3044" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/photo-3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-236" alt="photo 3" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/photo-3.jpg" width="2372" height="3162" /></a>It all began on their family vineyard in Bordeaux, France- as if that is not dreamy enough! It is the perfect fit for me, as I have so much love for France, Parisian culture, Wine + Skincare! It was an evening of Vino [off of the family''s vineyard <a href="http://www.smith-haut-lafitte.com/en/" target="_blank">Chateau Smith Haut Lafitte</a>], education on the new launches of skincare [specifically the newly formulated <a href="http://us.caudalie.com/products-best-sellers/collections/vinosource.html?utm_source=Google&amp;utm_medium=cpc&amp;utm_term=vinosource%20caudalie&amp;utm_content=Skincare&amp;utm_campaign=Vinosource&amp;gclid=CM2LwKqc9bUCFVKf4AodREMAsw" target="_blank">Vinosource line</a>] + even a quick facial, thanks Oxsana!\r\n\r\nMy kit, as well as my personal cabinet is stocked with their products, I can''t live without. I hope to be back to the spa sooner than later, in the meantime I am doing my own ''Vinotherapie''- out of the tube + glass! S.', 'Once Upon a Vine...', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '497-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-28 07:06:16', '2015-01-28 07:06:16', '', 497, 'http://182.71.22.42/sarah/?p=2082', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2083, 1, '2015-01-28 07:06:36', '2015-01-28 07:06:36', 'Spending some playtime on the beaches in + around Melbourne, Australia. Diamond Bay, Moggs Creek, Lorne etc. They are all stunning. I love taking the time to dig in the sand, explore the beachscape + make my own adventure. I am always in awe at the range of texture + color: shells, sandstone [Aus has a lot of this!], seaglass, clay, rocks, etc...<!--more--> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/2mar5.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-268" alt="2mar5" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/2mar5.jpg" width="2448" height="1632" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/3mar5.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-269" alt="3mar5" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/3mar5.jpg" width="2392" height="1595" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/4mar5.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-270" alt="4mar5" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/4mar5.jpg" width="1287" height="858" /></a>The colors are dreamy. It is no wonder why so many makeup lines get their collections from beaches, both textures + colors. I look at the beach + see eyeshadow palettes! It is as if the ocean is decorated with all of these lovely accessories. The beach is one of my favorite places to be, but not for too long, the concrete jungle has my heart.', 'Australia/ Beach DÃ©cor', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '501-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-28 07:06:36', '2015-01-28 07:06:36', '', 501, 'http://182.71.22.42/sarah/?p=2083', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2084, 1, '2015-01-28 07:08:48', '2015-01-28 07:08:48', 'This compilation has been a long time coming... I am blessed to work with some of the most talented musicians in the world [Lykke Li, Duran Duran, Sleigh Bells, Mark Ronson + more]. I love it. There is something about working with other artists + being with them in such an intimate space [often doing vocal warm up] while I am getting them ready that is so liberating! Inspiring! I have such fun memories of applying makeup to Lykke Li while she''s singing a Stevie Nicks song, amazing. Or jushing [it''s in the urban dictionary!] Simon Le Bon''s hair while he belts out Girl Panic ! Here is a video reel that I put together housing some of my very favorite moments. Song on the reel is done by my dear friend [grew up with this one!] Megan James, Purity Ring. Get into it. ENJOY X\r\n\r\nhttps://vimeo.com/61669529', 'Reeling: Music Muses', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '500-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-01-28 07:08:48', '2015-01-28 07:08:48', '', 500, 'http://182.71.22.42/sarah/?p=2084', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
