(2242, 1, '2015-02-09 09:11:12', '2015-02-09 09:11:12', '[symple_column size="one-half" position="first" fade_in="false"]\r\n<p style="line-height:1.3; text-align: justify;">Based in New York, by way of her native Canada, Sarah Appleby paints faces daily for musicians, models, celebrities, artists and more. Her passion and involvement in the beauty industry allows Sarah to be uniquely informed on the newest products, techniques and upcoming trends. \r\n<br />\r\nSarahâ€™s work can be found in an ever growing range of publications, from Vanity Fair to Glamour, Nylon to Rolling Stone and her extensive client list includes Victoriaâ€™s Secret, Saks 5th Ave, Lord and Taylor, Mercedes Benz and Atlantic Records. Making noise in the industry, Sarah has recently begun working with select international cosmetic companies: consulting on the development of product lines, speaking at press events and acting as spokesperson.   \r\n<br />\r\nHer technical skill and unique perspective for color, texture and detail has firmly established Sarah within the beauty and fashion industry as one to watch. \r\n<br />\r\nSarah is continually inspired by the world around her: faces, spaces and places. She blogs regularly, a home to her daily musings and all she finds beauty in.\r\n</p>\r\n[/symple_column]\r\n\r\n[symple_column size="one-half" position="last" fade_in="false"]\r\n<a href="http://182.71.22.42/sarah/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/about.png"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-66" src="http://182.71.22.42/sarah/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/SARAH_APPLEBY_JANET_KIM_BIO_PHOTO-1.jpg" alt="about" width="100%"  data-id="66" /></a>\r\n[/symple_column]', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '5-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-02-09 09:11:12', '2015-02-09 09:11:12', '', 5, 'http://182.71.22.42/sarah/?p=2242', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(2244, 1, '2015-01-28 17:04:10', '2015-01-28 17:04:10', '<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/2015_MOISTURE_CAUDALIE_JURLIQUE_OJON_01.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1865" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/2015_MOISTURE_CAUDALIE_JURLIQUE_OJON_01.jpg" alt="2015_MOISTURE_CAUDALIE_JURLIQUE_OJON_01" width="2208" height="1248" /></a>I think this is redundant on beauty platforms, but it is always so fascinating to me how my skin changes + needs for different things through different seasons. Most products I use are based on which perform the very best with what my skin needs while the weather fluctuates. Right now my focus is hydration. Here are my best tips to help your skin drink in all of the moisture you are giving it + my three products that will help nourish...<!--more-->\r\n\r\nI know several dermatologists talk/write about how our body doesn''t really NEED 8 glasses of water per day. It is in fact possible + more likely that you can EAT your water, maybe with less effort. There are plenty of raw foods that are filled with water + this will hydrate your skin + body just the same, but more beneficial than water because of the roughage + vitamins that come along with say, a head of kale. Don''t get me wrong, I am a huge water fan. My newest discovery as of late is the SodaStream, which I use solely for sparkling water + I can drink glass after glass with that [Make a bottle + fill your water jug with cucumber, mint, lemon or similar for some fresh flavor].\r\n\r\nI went for a facial this past weekend at the Caudalie Urban spa on Bleecker Street in the West Village + the esthetician told me it is very rare to see skin so hydrated. WELL! I give a lot of credit to the fact that I have been fasting alcohol this month + substituting the sparkling H2O! Along with that goodness, here are my three favorite products right now to nourish your face, body + hair.\r\n<div><a href="http://www.jurlique.com/skin-balancing-face-oil-new.html" target="_blank"><em>â€¢ JURLIQUE SKIN BALANCING OIL</em></a> is a new favorite. After cleansing my skin I apply this all over my face + neck. It is all natural + packed with delicious ingredients like Safflower, Rose Hip, Avocado, Macadamia Oil which is moisturizing, smoothing + protecting. I follow with a generous amount of eye cream which seals the oil.<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1867" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/2015_MOISTURE_MID_WINTER_JURLIQUE_SKIN_BALANCING_FACE_OIL.jpg" alt="2015_MOISTURE_MID_WINTER_JURLIQUE_SKIN_BALANCING_FACE_OIL" width="2168" height="1085" /><a href="http://www.ojon.com/products/4726/Shop-by-Product/Shop-by-Product-Type/Treatment/index.tmpl" target="_blank"><em>â€¢OJON DAMAGE REVERSE </em></a>is a staple in my cabinet. Twice a week I put onto my dry hair + massage into body of hair. I will leave on 20-30 minutes + then get into the bath to shampoo out. The texture is like a balm at first but emolliates with the warmth of your fingers into a oil like texture which makes it easy to apply evenly.<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1868" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/2015_MOISTURE_OJON_DAMAGE_REVERSE_HAIR_PRODUCT_02.jpg" alt="2015_MOISTURE_OJON_DAMAGE_REVERSE_HAIR_PRODUCT_02" width="2208" height="1248" /><em><a href="http://us.caudalie.com/vine-body-butter-3.html" target="_blank">â€¢CAUDALIE VINE BODY BUTTER</a> I love this whipped souffle body butter. The texture is amazing + the body butter is natural + full of grape + shea butters. A beautiful result of supple, enriched skin. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1872" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/2015_MOISTURE_CAUDALIE_WINE_BODY_BUTTER2.jpg" alt="2015_MOISTURE_CAUDALIE_WINE_BODY_BUTTER" width="2208" height="1248" /></em></div>\r\n<div>Do not be afraid to layer products as well. The more moisture you can lock into your skin the better! X</div>', 'USE: MID WINTER moisturizing musthaves', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'use-mid-winter-moisturizing-musthaves', '', '', '2015-02-09 10:38:07', '2015-02-09 10:38:07', '', 0, 'http://sarahappleby.com/blog/?p=1864', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2245, 1, '2015-02-02 14:49:10', '2015-02-02 14:49:10', '<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/2015_CAUDALIE_EYE_SWOON_PUTNAM_FLOWERS_02.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1875" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/2015_CAUDALIE_EYE_SWOON_PUTNAM_FLOWERS_02.jpg" alt="2015_CAUDALIE_EYE_SWOON_PUTNAM_FLOWERS_02" width="1856" height="1223" /></a>Â The end of last week I found myself in the <a href="http://us.caudalie.com/?gclid=Cj0KEQiA3bymBRC19IrD7O_NrYsBEiQAb2dpA9O3XeHt8UeCVdgFPibgXZy56DnnjOe7Klb6o8hnv5YaArcI8P8HAQ" target="_blank">Caudalie </a>boutique in the West Village, amidst some of my very favorite things . Sipping the delicious wine from Mathilde''s Vineyard in France, we indulged in food all sourced from ingredients that Caudalie uses in their skin care; grapes, lemon, pear, coriander. Founders of Caudalie, Mathilde + Bertrand spoke about their newest product, ''the rolls royce'' of facial serums, <a href="http://us.caudalie.com/premier-cru-elixir.html" target="_blank">Premier Cru The Elixir</a>...<!--more-->\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1885" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/2015_CAUDALIE_EYE_SWOON_PUTNAM_FLOWERS_ELIXIR_10.jpg" alt="2015_CAUDALIE_EYE_SWOON_PUTNAM_FLOWERS_ELIXIR_10" width="2172" height="1041" />Poppy''s Catering is my favorite in NYC, they source local as much as possible + have amazing taste, quite literally. Not only are all of the bites delicious, but they look beautiful too...<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/2015_CAUDALIE_EYE_SWOON_PUTNAM_FLOWERS_ELIXIR_06.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1879" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/2015_CAUDALIE_EYE_SWOON_PUTNAM_FLOWERS_ELIXIR_06.jpg" alt="2015_CAUDALIE_EYE_SWOON_PUTNAM_FLOWERS_ELIXIR_06" width="2208" height="1248" /></a> Mathilde Thomas speaking about the properties + performance of <a href="http://us.caudalie.com/premier-cru-elixir.html" target="_blank">The Elixir</a>. Lifestyle blogger + interior genius, Athena Calderone from <a href="http://eye-swoon.com/" target="_blank">Eye Swoon</a> co-hosted the event.<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1877" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/2015_CAUDALIE_EYE_SWOON_PUTNAM_FLOWERS_ELIXIR_01.jpg" alt="2015_CAUDALIE_EYE_SWOON_PUTNAM_FLOWERS_ELIXIR_01" width="1919" height="926" />Â Â  <a href="http://www.poppyscatering.com/" target="_blank">Poppy''s Catering</a> made a delicious grape + meyer lemon jelly.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/2015_CAUDALIE_EYE_SWOON_PUTNAM_FLOWERS_ELIXIR_EVENT_04.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1880" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/2015_CAUDALIE_EYE_SWOON_PUTNAM_FLOWERS_ELIXIR_EVENT_04.jpg" alt="2015_CAUDALIE_EYE_SWOON_PUTNAM_FLOWERS_ELIXIR_EVENT_04" width="2208" height="1248" /></a>Â  The new power Premier Cru duo! <a href="http://us.caudalie.com/premier-cru-elixir.html" target="_blank">The Elixir</a> is a beautiful product that is half oil + half serum. The formula is silicon free + anti-aging + when used under the Premier Cru, <a href="http://us.caudalie.com/premier-cru-the-cream-2.html" target="_blank">The Cream,</a> will leave your skin soft, supple + plump. After using it for a couple of months [love a preview of a good product!], I find it is enhancing my moisturizer, really locking in all of the moisture.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/2015_CAUDALIE_EYE_SWOON_PUTNAM_FLOWERS_ELIXIR_EVENT_08.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1882" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/2015_CAUDALIE_EYE_SWOON_PUTNAM_FLOWERS_ELIXIR_EVENT_08.jpg" alt="2015_CAUDALIE_EYE_SWOON_PUTNAM_FLOWERS_ELIXIR_EVENT_08" width="2208" height="1248" /></a> Mathilde + Bertrand + Alix, my dear friend + designer of French Women''s line, <a href="http://heimstone.com/" target="_blank">Heimstone,</a> enjoying the vino.<a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/2015_CAUDALIE_EYE_SWOON_PUTNAM_FLOWERS_HEIMSTONE_09.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1883" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/2015_CAUDALIE_EYE_SWOON_PUTNAM_FLOWERS_HEIMSTONE_09.jpg" alt="2015_CAUDALIE_EYE_SWOON_PUTNAM_FLOWERS_HEIMSTONE_09" width="2208" height="1248" /></a> <a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/2015_CAUDALIE_EYE_SWOON_SMITH_HAVT_LAFITTE_03.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1884" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/2015_CAUDALIE_EYE_SWOON_SMITH_HAVT_LAFITTE_03.jpg" alt="2015_CAUDALIE_EYE_SWOON_SMITH_HAVT_LAFITTE_03" width="2208" height="1248" /></a><a href="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/2015_CAUDALIE_EYE_SWOON_PUTNAM_FLOWERS_05.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1876" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/2015_CAUDALIE_EYE_SWOON_PUTNAM_FLOWERS_05.jpg" alt="2015_CAUDALIE_EYE_SWOON_PUTNAM_FLOWERS_05" width="2208" height="1248" /></a> I was sent home with one of the bouquets! Being a flower girl that loves to have fresh flowers in my home, this was a treat. Flower Masters of the best Floral shop in NYC, Matthew + Derek co-founders of <a href="http://putnamflowers.com/" target="_blank">Putnam+Putnam</a>, put together the most beautiful arrangements. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1881" src="http://sarahappleby.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/2015_CAUDALIE_EYE_SWOON_PUTNAM_FLOWERS_ELIXIR_EVENT_07.jpg" alt="2015_CAUDALIE_EYE_SWOON_PUTNAM_FLOWERS_ELIXIR_EVENT_07" width="1983" height="1179" />I need a lot more of all of this in my life! A delicious evening indeed... X', 'LIVE/ A nite with CAUDALIE X EYE SWOON X PUTNAM FLOWERS X POPPY''S', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'live-a-nite-with-caudalie-x-eye-swoon-x-putnam-flowers-x-poppys', '', '', '2